title: mini quiche lorraines
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut pastry dough with fluted cutter about 1 1/4-inches in diameter, cut out 18 rounds.
Line 18 tartlet or mini muffin pans with dough rounds.

Break eggs into bowl, add nutmeg, salt and pepper and beat with fork until blended well. Continue to beat and add cream in a thin steady stream. Distribute bacon evenly among pastry lined pans, then pour in cream mix.
Bake until filling sets and crusts are golden, about 15 minutes.
Serve hot or warm.

title: finish pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into well-greased pans.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top with butter and sugar.

title: cherry angel dessert
directions: Place half of cake pieces in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Reserve 1/3 cup cherry pie filling and spread remainder over cake cubes in pan.
Top with remaining cake cubes.
Combine pudding mix, milk and sour cream; beat until smooth and spoon over cake cube layer. Chill for five hours or overnight.
Cut in squares and garnish with reserved cherry pie filling.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees.

title: spinach salad
directions: Tear spinach into bite size bits; place in salad bowl. Arrange crumbled bacon, eggs, scallions and croutons over the spinach and mushrooms.
Combine all remaining ingredients; mix well.
Just before serving, or at table, pour dressing over salad and toss lightly.
Serves 4.

title: pork chop oven dinner
directions: Trim the fat from the pork chops.
Place the fat in a large skillet and fry until approximately 2 tablespoons of grease accumulates.
Remove the trimmings.
Coat the pork chops in a mixture of the flour, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Place chops in skillet and brown well, about 10 minutes per side.
In a 3-quart casserole, combine water and next 5 ingredients.
Place carrots that have been halved and cut lengthwise and potatoes that have been halved.
Generously sprinkle with salt; place in the casserole.
Arrange pork chops on top of carrots and potatoes; place onion slices on top of pork chops.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Mix together all ingredients except sausage, blending well. Add sausage.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Use baking dish that can be used from refrigerator to oven.

title: orange tuna macaroni salad(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Blend mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper.
Mix with orange pieces, tuna and macaroni.
Mix lightly.
Add celery and onion. Mix lightly, but thoroughly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put in layers and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mushroom beef pie
directions: In large skillet, cook ground beef and chopped onion.
Pour off fat.
Layer crescent roll dough in bottom and up sides of 9-inch pie pan, forming a pie crust edge.
Add 1/2 can mushroom soup to cooked beef mix.
Add egg, bread crumbs and seasonings.
Press into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the next 4 ingredients together and spread over the top of the batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries, pineapple, sugar and marshmallows together. Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, add whipping cream (already whipped).

title: mom's pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Dissolve margarine and brown sugar in bottom of cake pan. Pour in drained pineapple.
Prepare cake batter as directed on box, substituting pineapple juice for water.
Pour into pan and bake as directed on box.

title: infallible nut cake
directions: Rub sugar and butter to a cream.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add milk and dry ingredients to sugar mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nut meats.
Beat egg whites until stiff froth, then fold into rest of ingredients.
Bake in a medium oven.
It will require about an hour to bake and should rise to full height before browning.
I use oleo and pecans.

title: cathedral windows
directions: Melt
chocolate with oleo.
Remove from heat.
Add egg. Add marshmallows, nuts and confectioners sugar.
Pour onto two pieces of wax paper sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Roll as jelly roll.
Chill well.	Slice and serve.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Cook linguine according to directions on package.
In pan, add oil and garlic; saute.
Add clams and saute.
Add wine, broth, basil, pepper, parsley and oregano.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Toss with pasta and top with cheese.

title: banana slush
directions: Mix ingredients, except 7-Up.
Freeze until very slushy.
Add 7-Up, stir and serve.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter or margarine; add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs one at a time (mix well after each egg); add sifted cake flour, 1 cup at a time.
Add 7-Up, 1/4 cup at a time and mix well.
Add vanilla flavoring or your choice and mix completely.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done in Bundt cake pan or round spring cake pan.
Check cake with toothpick to make sure middle is done.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil 3 cups of water; add Noodles; cook for 10-12 minutes; drain, and rinse.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: reba's tennessee style corn bread
directions: Mix corn muffin mix according to package directions.
Spread half batter in greased oblong (about 11 x 7-inch) baking pan. Sprinkle with cheese, however spicy you like it.
Mix creamed corn into the remaining cornbread batter and pour on top of the cheese. Bake 30 to 35 minutes until cornbread is set in center and browned.
Makes 8 servings.

title: toasted oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium skillet, over medium heat, heat butter until lightly browned.
Add oats.
Stir constantly until golden, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool. Meanwhile, sift flour with cinnamon, salt and soda.
Set aside.
In large bowl combine sugar, egg and vanilla.
Beat until light with wooden spoon or mixer at medium speed.
Stir in oats and flour mixtures and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and enjoy; they are delicious. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: oven-grilled potatoes
directions: Can be cooked in oven or over the grill.

title: taco dip
directions: Cut peppers into small pieces.
In square baking dish, layer the cream cheese spread over bottom, the peppers in sauce and top with the two cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cheese should be bubbly and edges light brown.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: tamale pie(my husband's favorite food.)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown meat. Add onion, garlic and bell pepper.
Cook until onion is golden. Stir in tomatoes, corn, chili powder and 2 teaspoons salt. Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 cup corn meal mixed with water. Simmer, covered, 10 minutes. Add olives and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spaghetti all'olio
directions: Heat oil and garlic in frying pan.
Cook until garlic is brown.
(If using olive oil, add about 1/4 cup water slowly to thin it out.)
Add parsley, pepper and broccoli (optional) and simmer about 5 minutes.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Spoon into baking dish. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot.

title: summer peach salad
directions: Drain peaches (use juice in jello).
Mix jello by box directions with juice being a part of the liquid.
Chill in refrigerator until slightly jelled.
Blend peaches in blender, then mix with softened cream cheese; fold into jello.
Fold the Cool Whip into jello mixture.
Makes one large mold.

title: boiled dinner
directions: Peel and wedge, then quarter potatoes.
Place in large pot. Slice ham into thin slices and layer ham, then green beans and pepper until gone.
Top with pepper and add water.
Cook on medium heat, covered, until it comes to a boil.
Turn down and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Whip cream cheese, milk and lemon juice.
Add rest of the ingredients to first mixture.
Blend well and refrigerate.

title: crispy coconut-oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat shortening and sugars at medium speed of electric mixer until blended; add eggs and vanilla, beating well.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing well. Stir in oats and remaining ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place 2 inches apart on a lightly greased cookie sheet. Flatten slightly with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Transfer to wire racks to cool.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: pineapple delite
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix the juice, sugar, egg and flour.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Fold in pineapple, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Let set overnight.

title: grandma f's sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll out dough and cut into desired shapes.
Bake approximately 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes about 150 cookies.
Decorate with powdered sugar icing and sprinkles, red hots, etc.

title: chocolate suicide cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, sugars and vanilla until blended.
Add eggs and milk.
Beat well.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add to butter mixture, blending well.
Stir in chips.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 11 minutes.
Cool 1 minute and remove to wire rack.
Unwrap Kiss and place/press into center of each cookie.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: english muffin loaves
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda. Heat liquids until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add dry mixture; beat well.
Stir in enough flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon into 2 loaf pans (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch) that have been greased and cornmealed.
Sprinkle tops with cornmeal; cover.
Let rise in warm place for 45 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately and cool.

title: chicken enchilada pie
directions: Combine soups,
tomatoes and chilies and chicken broth. Preheat oven
to
Cover
bottom
of a 3-quart casserole with corn chips.
Spread
1/2 of chicken over this layer, then 1/2 sauce
and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese. Bake for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: squash supreme
directions: Mash cooked squash then add soup, onion, carrots, sour cream, salt and pepper. Butter bottom of a baking dish. Sprinkle crumbs on bottom of bowl. Add squash mixture. Cover squash with crumbs and butter on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot olive cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese and butter.
Stir in flour, salt and paprika. Mix well.
Wrap 1 teaspoon cheese dough around each olive, completely covering olive.
Arrange on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: barbecue sauce for ribs
directions: Salt ribs.
Put into a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Drain fat from pan.
Pour sauce over ribs.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours.
Baste ribs every 15 minutes.
If sauce gets thick, add more water to thin.
Bake until ribs are done.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice peeled apples and arrange in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix egg, flour, baking powder and sugar (should be crumbly).
Spread over apples.
Melt butter and pour over crumbly mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: boxty(potato pancakes)
directions: Squeeze grated potatoes in cloth to remove moisture.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Mix potatoes and dry ingredients well together with beaten eggs.
Add milk to make a dropping batter.
Drop by tablespoon onto a hot buttered frying pan.
Cook over a moderate heat, allowing 4 minutes on each side. Serve hot with butter.

title: oven stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a large covered casserole.
Bake in slow oven at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
It makes its own gravy.
It is good with rice.

title: malted milk cookies(makes about 4 dozen)
directions: In mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
In separate bowl, combine flour, malted milk mix and crushed candies.
Add to creamed mixture with vanilla and blend (mixture will be crumbly). Knead dough with hands and shape into a smooth ball.
Wrap in plastic wrap or foil; refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.

title: mom's french apple cake
directions: In large bowl, mix eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add apples to dry mixture and stir gently. Add to first mixture and blend well.
Add nuts.
Batter will be very stiff.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 375° for approximately 1 hour.
Cake will be crusty and shiny when done.
Cool in pan.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, water and salt.
Bring to a boil, then turn down on low for 1/2 hour with lid.
Mix egg, sugar and vanilla. Combine with rice and bring to a boil, then turn off.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juices of canned fruit.
Mix all together except for fresh strawberries, bananas and walnuts.
Add those just before serving.

title: slushies
directions: In blender, combine Kool-Aid, water and sugar; blend. Add all the ice and blend. Pour into a cup and enjoy.

title: amaretto rice pudding
directions: Combine eggs and sugar in a medium mixing bowl.
Slowly add scalded milk,
stirring
constantly.
Stir in rice, cinnamon, Amaretto
and
vanilla.
Spoon mixture into a buttered 1 1/2 quart
baking
dish.
Place dish in a larger shallow pan; add 1 inch
of
water
to pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour; stir mixture.
Sprinkle	evenly with nutmeg and bake an additional 30 minutes.
Remove dish from pan; let cool.

title: chili meat balls
directions: Combine beef with bread crumbs, minced onions, salt, egg and 1/4 cup of tomato soup; shape into 1-inch balls.
Brown in shortening.
Mix remaining soup, chili and water; pour over meat. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute green pepper, onion, pimento and mushrooms.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients; pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle top with American cheese.
Bake another 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and onion; place in baking dish.
Add butter, salt and pepper.
Blend soup with 1 can of milk; pour over other ingredients.
Top with shredded cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant until mushy and drain.
Add 1/2 of margarine, while hot.
Add all ingredients, reserving 1/4 cup cheese and 1/4 crumbs; mix well. Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese, cracker crumbs and margarine. Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes 6 servings.
Tastes like scalloped oysters.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and butter; add sugar and beat and cream until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and dry ingredients together three times.
Add to other mixture alternately with milk, to which vanilla has been added.
Blend thoroughly.
Turn into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes and medium speed 1 minute.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: creamy penuche fudge
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in 2-quart saucepan and stir to mix well. Add undiluted evaporated milk and stir. Bring slowly to the boiling point over medium heat and stir constantly. Boil exactly 5 minutes after it reaches the boiling point, stirring so it will not stick to bottom of pan. Cook to soft-ball stage. Remove from heat and add butter, marshmallow cream, maple flavoring and nuts. Beat until it loses its shine, about 5 to 10 minutes. Pour into 9 x 9-inch buttered pan.

title: dried beef hot dip
directions: Mix ingredients together, spreading in 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Blend together the butter, flour and powdered sugar.
Put mixture into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Put mixture into bottom only.
Bake for 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Meanwhile mix filling.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine beaten egg yolks and sugar.
Add flour and cocoa. Beat well.
Add milk and oleo.
Cook in double boiler until thick. Divide.
Pour into baked shells.
Makes 2 pies.

title: the big cookie
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread into ungreased pizza pan.
Cook 20 minutes at 300°.
Will look undercooked but will be done.
Cool and then break into pieces or cut into squares.

title: goober haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter in top of double boiler over hot (not boiling) water.
Stir to blend.
Add peanuts and noodles; stir until well covered.
Form little clusters on waxed paper.
Let sit to harden.

title: rib and chicken sauce
directions: After adding all ingredients, simmer and stir often until fairly thick, almost like ketchup.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Brush on ribs and chicken when barbecuing.

title: breakfast bundt cake
directions: First, grease inside of Bundt pan with Crisco and sprinkle some ground nuts on the inside of pan, not too close to edge of pan.
Combine cake mix, corn oil and water. Mix well, adding eggs one at a time and mix well after each egg.
Beat high speed, 6 to 8 minutes.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and 1 teaspoon butter extract near end of beating time.
Layer batter and nut mixture 3 times, batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack for 8 minutes.
Remove from pan and glaze while still warm. Use all the glaze and apply with pastry brush.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 Tbsp. milk, and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.

title: magic rolls
directions: *If using cottage cheese put the 1 cup of buttermilk in blender then add the cottage cheese and blend until smooth.

title: date pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased 9 1/2 x 13 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Pour over this the topping shown below.
Then bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: impossible apple pie
directions: In a bowl mix, eggs, sugar, vanilla, oleo, flour and milk. Add shredded apples and mix well. Pour into a greased floured 10 inch
pie pan. Bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes. Lower to 350 and cook another 40 minutes. Serve with cool whip.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup and milk.
Stir well. Spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle margarine over crumbs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Yield:
6 servings.

title: raspberry cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom and sides of 9 x 10-inch spring-form pan.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup. Combine flour and 3/4 cup sugar.
Using pastry blender, cut in margarine.
Reserve 1 cup of crumb mixture.
To remaining crumb mixture, add baking powder, soda, salt, sour cream, 1 egg and almond extract; blend.
Spread batter over bottom and 2 inches up sides of pan.

title: boneless chicken bake
directions: Lightly grease glass baking dish.
Lay chicken flat in dish. Top each with slice of cheese.
Mix soup and milk together.
Pour over cheese and chicken.
Mix stuffing and butter together. Sprinkle on top to cover completely.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: ground beef stew
directions: Saute the meat and onions until brown, drain off fat.
Place in pot, add the potatoes and sliced carrots.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Heat oven
to 375° in 8-inch square baking dish.
Layer sauerkraut, caraway
seed, 1 cup cheese, 1000 Island dressing, corned beef
and
remaining
cheese.
Toss	bread
cubes
with melted butter.
Sprinkle
over
top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until
heated through.
Before serving, sprinkle with parsley. Makes 6 servings.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix together 2 cups cake mix, 2/3
cup melted margarine and 2/3 cup milk.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Heat water and milk until steaming.
Add sugar and stir until cool.
Equals 14 ounce can Eagle Brand milk.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1 cup sour cream over meat mixture.
Sprinkle 1 cup Mozzarella cheese on top.
Roll out 1 package crescent rolls on top and pinch edges together.
Spread butter or margarine over crescent rolls and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: golden punch
directions: Boil sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Chill all ingredients and mix together when ready to serve.
Makes 2 1/2 gallons of punch.

title: kabob marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Marinate 1 1/2-inch chunks of beef (sirloin) for 4 to 24 hours.
Place beef on skewers.
Baste kabobs while grilling (cooking) with marinade.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In large kettle over medium heat, cook celery, onion and carrots in margarine until tender; add remaining ingredients except noodles.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer covered 30 minutes. Remove bay leaf; add noodles.
Cook 6 minutes longer or until noodles are tender.
Makes about 4 quarts.

title: double fruit pie
directions: Mix strawberry yogurt with 1/2 Cool Whip; add strawberries and blend.
Spoon into pie crust.
Mix blueberry yogurt with remaining Cool Whip; fold in blueberries and blend.
Spoon over strawberry layer.
Garnish as desired.
Freeze 4 hours.
Remove and place inside refrigerator 45 minutes before cutting.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add vinegar and water.
Cook 5 minutes; add beets.
Let stand 30 minutes before serving.
Heat to boiling point and add butter.

title: chicken in a skillet
directions: I use skinless chicken breasts.

title: pineapple glaze for ham
directions: Spoon glaze over ham last 30 minutes of baking time.

title: sausage and pepper hero
directions: Cut fennel sausages into 3 pieces each.
In a large non-reactive large frying pan, heat oil over medium heat.
Add sausages and cook, turning every 10 minutes or until browned and cooked through.
Spoon off fat from pan.
Add onion and peppers. Cook, stirring every 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, water, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in parsley.
Spoon sausages with peppers and sauce onto split rolls.
Serves 6.

title: rice peruvian-style
directions: In deep pot, saute garlic in oil and salt.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Add rice and return to a boil.
Reduce to a simmer, cover and cook 20 minutes or until rice is cooked.
Mix in onions, bacon and eggs.
Add a little soy sauce, mix well and serve.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Drain the pineapple and save the juice.
Mix together the sugar, pineapple, cheese and the flour.
To this mixture, add the juice.
On top of this mixture, crumble the crackers and drizzle over the top the margarine.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute all fresh vegetables in seasoned fat.
Add all other ingredients and cook at 300° for 2 hours.
Do not cook too dry. Juices will thicken when removed from oven.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix together by hand.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 300° for 1 hour.

title: burgundy beef
directions: *Broth may be made by dissolving 1 cube or teaspoon of instant beef bouillon in 3/4 cup boiling water or use canned beef broth.

title: amish raisin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line bottom of pie pan with half of pastry.
In a medium saucepan, simmer the raisins and 2/3 cup of the water over medium heat for 5 minutes.
In a small bowl combine the next 6 ingredients.
Gradually stir in the remaining 1 1/3 cups water.
Add to the raisins, stirring until mixture bubbles up.
Add vinegar, butter and orange rind.
Continue cooking until butter is melted.
Cool to lukewarm.
Pour into the uncooked pie shell.
Top with second crust; cut slits to allow steam to escape. Bake for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: baked mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sprinkle mushrooms with lemon juice.
In medium skillet, saute mushrooms with onion in butter.
Sprinkle with flour, salt, pepper and cheese.
Cover; simmer for 3 minutes. Put mushrooms into baking dish.
Combine cream and egg yolks; pour over mushrooms.
Cover with bread crumbs and touch of paprika. Bake until golden, 10 to 20 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: fritter batter
directions: Mix egg yolks, water and milk.
Add lemon juice and melted butter.
Resift flour, salt and sugar.
Combine the liquid and the dry ingredients with a few swift strokes.
Add 1/8 teaspoon salt to the egg whites.
Whip them until they are stiff.
Fold them into batter.
Fry the fritters until they are a golden brown. Sprinkle with some confectioners sugar before serving or top with your favorite jam or jelly.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in egg until crumbly.
Melt butter and add 1/4 cup hot water.
Put apples in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover apples with flour mixture.
Spoon butter mixture over until flour is dampened.
Bake at 400° until crust is golden brown and crispy.
Serve with ice cream.

title: pistachio nut swirl cake
directions: Combine sugar, nuts and cinnamon; set aside.
Combine the remaining ingredients in a large mixer bowl.
Blend and beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour 1/3 of the batter into greased and floured 10-inch fluted tube or tube pan.
Sprinkle with half the sugar mixture.
Repeat layers and top with remaining batter. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick is inserted and comes out clean.
Cool in pan about 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Add to beef along with egg, seasonings and onion.
Form into small balls.
Roll in flour. Saute in butter until brown.
Add small amount of water (1/2 cup) and soup or stock.
Cook a few minutes (10) on low heat.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: miso soup
directions: Cook shrimp in water for 10 minutes.
Bring water to a boil and let simmer.
Put miso in strainer (over a pot) and pour shrimp water through until all miso is dissolved.
Cut tofu into 1/2-inch cubes and add to stock.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from fire and add finely chopped green onions.
Saimin noodles may also be added at the same time as the tofu for a heavier soup.

title: red velvet cake #2
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add vinegar and food coloring.
Sift flour, soda and cocoa to the mixture.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into pans.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Combine and press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cool.

title: saltimbocca ala simboli
directions: Flatten each side of veal with meat mallet.
Sprinkle each side of veal with sage, rubbing it into the meat until it is lightly green in color.
Season with pepper.
Put a slice of Prosciutto ham on each slice of veal.
Secure with a toothpick.
In large skillet, saute veal in butter over medium heat for about 3 minutes each side.
Serve in warmed chafing dish (dinner plates should also be warmed).

title: chili cheese dip no. 2
directions: Crumble sausage and brown.
Drain well on paper towel.
Cut Velveeta in cubes.
Combine all ingredients in top of double boiler.
Heat and stir until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Can also be cooked in crock-pot or in microwave.

title: strawberry cheesecake trifle
directions: In a large bowl, cream together cream cheese and sugar; add sour cream and vanilla.
Set aside.
Whip the cream; add vanilla and sugar.
Fold whipped cream into cream cheese mixture.
Add cake pieces; set aside.
Combine strawberries, sugar and vanilla. Layer together in a large glass bowl, starting with strawberries, then adding cake mixture.
Continue layering; finish with strawberries.

title: creamy egg nog
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar in large bowl until light and fluffy. Blend in remaining ingredients; chill.
Top each serving with whipped cream.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: beefy baked beans
directions: Combine beef, green pepper and onion in skillet.
Cook until meat is browned.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased 10 x 6 baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: double pudding pie
directions: Bake the graham cracker crust for six minutes.
Mix 1 box of pudding and pour into pie shell.
Then mix the other box of pudding and pour into pie shell.
Re-whip the bowl of whipped cream and apply to top of pie.
Garnish with cherries for the professional look.
Tastes best chilled.

title: dilly green tomatoes
directions: Select small firm green tomatoes.
Leave stems on.
Pack in sterilized quart jars.
To each quart, add garlic, celery, green pepper and dill or dill seed.
For about 8 quarts combine water, vinegar and salt.
Cook 5 minutes.
Fill jars to 1/2-inch from top.
Seal.
To seal boil Mason jar lids 10 minutes.
While hot add to quart jars and put on rings.
No processing needed.

title: never-fail beef bourguignon
directions: Roll beef cubes in flour.
Brown beef, sliced onions and garlic in butter.
Transfer all to a large Dutch oven.
Add bay leaves, thyme, parsley, salt and pepper.
Pour enough wine over meat to cover.
Simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Add whole onions and cook to tender.
Add mushrooms the last 15 minutes.
If sauce needs thickening, add flour and water to mixture.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, topping with the Cheddar cheese and/or cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: jean ferguson fulghum shrimp
directions: Melt butter and cheese in double boiler.
Whip with hand beater to get rid of lumps.
Add shrimp and onions.
Let stand overnight. Reheat in double boiler and then put into chafing dish.
One recipe serves about 10.
Serve on Melba rounds.

title: jello mold(a la margueritte hartwell, serves 6 to 8)
directions: Prepare jello and gelatin by directions.
Use juice from fruit in place of cold water.
When thickened, add cherries, pineapple, nuts and cream cheese.
Pour into ring mold.
Serve with mayonnaise if desired.

title: cranapple delight
directions: Roll diced apples and cranberries in the sugar.
Set aside 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix butter, nuts, brown sugar, oats and flour. Place fruit into greased glass baking dish.
Sprinkle dry mixture over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This is good as a side dish or dessert.
Delicious served hot with ice cream!

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Salt and pepper tomato slices to taste. Dip in eggs and dredge in flour. In a skillet, heat bacon drippings over medium heat and fry tomato slices until golden brown on both sides.

title: pumpkin casserole
directions: Melt
oleo
in 2-quart casserole.
Pour mixture of rest of ingredients
over
oleo.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or 12 minutes in microwave.	(This is excellent served with dinner or served as a dessert.)

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute in butter the bell pepper and onions.
Mix all ingredients in one large bowl.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with a little cheese on top of casserole.
Bake at 400° for approximately 35 to 45 minutes.
Test for doneness.

title: firemen zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased pie plate at 350° for 30 minutes until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: easy corn bread
directions: Grease 9-inch pan. Combine ingredients and pour into pan. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400° or until light golden brown. Check with a toothpick; when it comes out clean, it's ready!

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Prepare broccoli as label directs; drain.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook all together. Serve with grated cheese, sour cream and tortilla chips.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Take chicken off the bone and cut into bite size pieces; put in casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.

title: chicken in cream sauce
directions: Saute peppers, onions and mushrooms in butter.
Stir together flour, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over cooked vegetables.
Stir until flour thickens.
Add cooked chicken and pimento.
Simmer until heated.
Serve over rice or biscuits.

title: apple betty(crisp!)
directions: Mound apples in buttered 9-inch pie plate (or casserole dish). Sprinkle with orange juice. Combine sugar, flour, spice and dash of salt. Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly. Sprinkle over apples and bake at 357° for 45 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is crisp. Serve warm topped with ice cream! Serves 6.

title: sealeg casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.	Line
bottom
with 1/2 of bread strips.
Mix together sealegs, onion, green pepper and celery. Spoon over bread.
Add rest
of
bread
to form another layer. Beat eggs, add to milk.
Stir
soup
into
milk mixture.
Pour soup/milk mixture over bread
layer.
Top
with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: marinated peppers
directions: Place the whole peppers in shallow pan, 4-inches from heat. Broil 12 to 15 minutes, turning to broil all sides.
Cool, cut in half, peel off thin skin and remove seeds and hard pulp.
Cut peppers lengthwise into 1/4-inch strips and place in bowl. Combine all other ingredients in jar and shake.
Pour over peppers. Serve at room temperature.

title: egg nog
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender except 6 ice cubes.
Blend until smooth.
Add remaining 6 ice cubes.
Blend until cubes are chopped fine.
Makes 3 cups.

title: cranberry relish salad
directions: Place the gelatin and hot water in blender.
Blend a few seconds to dissolve gelatin and add the remaining ingredients, except pecans.
Blend until chopped.
Add the pecans and blend. Turn into mold.
Unmold on bed of greens (lettuce, spinach, etc.). Serve with a dressing made from equal parts of mayonnaise and whipped cream.

title: quiche
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Insert knife or toothpick in the middle.
It should come out clean, not runny.

title: oatmeal pecan fudge
directions: Boil sugar, butter and milk 4 minutes (softball 232°).
Place oatmeal, coconut, chocolate chips, vanilla and pecans in large bowl.
Add milk mixture and stir well.
Drop from teaspoon on waxed paper.
Chill until firm.

title: hanky-pankys (snack)
directions: Brown and drain meats.	Add chunks of
cheese and melt, stirring together.	Add the rest of
the
ingredients.
Spread on rye bread rounds or very thin bread, cut in quarters.

title: mexi-dip
directions: Cook and stir ground beef in 10-inch skillet until brown; drain.
Stir in mustard, chili powder, onion, green pepper, beans, tomato sauce and seasoning mix.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Spread into ungreased 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate. Spread Sour Cream Topping over ground beef mixture.
Sprinkle with lettuce and cheese.
Serve with corn chips, if desired.

title: egg tarts
directions: Bake pastry shells for 10 minutes in 375° oven.
Beat eggs. Mix eggs, milk, sugar and oil together in a bowl.
Pour mix into pastry shells.
Bake 20 minutes in 375° oven until light golden brown.

title: deep dish apple pie(diabetic)
directions: Combine sugar substitute, cornstarch, lemon juice, nutmeg, cinnamon and apple slices.
Place in 9-inch deep dish pie plate; set aside.
Combine flour and salt.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Blend in water with fork until all dry ingredients are moistened.
Shape dough into ball.
Roll out dough on a floured surface and place on top of apple filling. Bake at 425° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: pineapple dump cake
directions: Dump first 6 ingredients into bowl.
Mix well.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cream the next 4 ingredients.
Ice cake immediately with cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle walnuts on top.
Refrigerate.

title: butter buttons
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese with sugar.
Add vanilla and flour.
Shape into balls and flatten on ungreased cookie sheet. Place 3 chocolate chips on each cookie (or decorate with Christmas sugars).
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: frozen banana orange push-ups(low calorie)
directions: Peel and slice bananas in a blender or the work bowl of a food processor fitted with a metal blade.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and process until foamy.
Pour evenly into 6 small paper cups.
Freeze.
To eat, squeeze bottom of cup.
Yields 6 servings.

title: apple turnover(easy)
directions: Cook first five ingredients in a saucepan until apple is tender.
Cool.
Remove crusts from bread and roll very thin. Place 1/2 of the apple mixture on each slice of bread and fold diagonally.
Moisten edges.
Press together with a fork.
Bake at 425° until golden brown or for a longer time at 350° for crispier texture.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a 3-quart bowl with wet hands. Shape into about 50 (1 1/2-inch) balls.
Put into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
Bake near center of oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Drain.
Put meatballs in electric skillet with sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes.
May be cooked in crock-pot on low for 1 1/2 hours.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Mix 35 crushed Oreos with melted butter.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese with confectioners sugar.
Fold in 1/2 of the Cool Whip container.
Spread over crust.
Mix chocolate pudding and vanilla pudding with milk.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding.
Crush a few more cookies on top.
Refrigerate overnight for better flavor.

title: nana's carrots and pineapple
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add the 1/3 cup pineapple juice, vinegar and soy sauce and bring to a boil.
Add cooked carrots and crushed pineapple.
Heat and serve.

title: pat's cheese balls
directions: Form a small ball.
Put in a piece of nut and date.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned.
Makes 50 servings.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, saving 1/2 can of soup.
After spreading cheese, take remaining soup mix with water and pour over top.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: fish creole
directions: Arrange fish in greased shallow baking pan or casserole. Saute onion and green pepper in margarine.
Add seasonings and tomatoes.
Pour over fish.
Bake at 375°
for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: ro's cheese cake tarts
directions: Place papers in 12 cupcake holes in muffin tin.
Put one tablespoon graham crackers in bottom of each cupcake.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, almond extract and egg.
Spoon mixture over graham crackers.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Top with pie filling.
Yields 12 tarts.

title: hamburger and cheese casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in oil with onions.
Cook shells according to directions and drain, thoroughly.
Add milk, butter and cheese. Stir until cheese is melted.
Add hamburger, salt and pepper.

title: bridal punch
directions: Mix lemon juice, 7-Up and pineapple juice and chill.
When ready to serve, add sherbet and 1 bottle of ginger ale at a time.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Fold all ingredients together.
Pour into large dish.
Cover and freeze.
Keeps well.

title: red lobster cheese-garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Mix Bisquick, water and cheese. Drop large spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until lightly browned. While biscuits are baking, melt butter in microwave, then stir in seasonings. When biscuits are done, immediately brush with butter/garlic mixture and serve hot.

title: mom sands' sausage dressing
directions: Fry sausage; add onion(s) while browning, then bring to boil with chicken broth, water, butter and seasonings.
Remove from heat and add the toasted white bread (in pieces).
Stir in 2 eggs. Bake in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with hunks of butter on top.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: joe's salsa de mare(enough for 4 to 6 main courses or 6 to 8 first course servings.)
directions: *If no mussels, use 2 pounds small clams (well scrubbed).

title: charcoal grilled fillets in foil
directions: Cut fillets into serving-size portions.
Cut 4 pieces of aluminum foil 12 x 12-inches each.
Grease lightly.
Place fish skin side down on foil.
Top with green pepper and onion.
Mix and pour sauce over fish.
Bring foil up over fish and close all edges with tight double folds.
Place package on grill about 5 inches from hot coals.
Cook for 25 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes or turns shiny white.
Serves 4.

title: hot chicken salad #4
directions: Day 1:
Cook chicken breasts; skin, bone and cut into bite size pieces.
Toss in Italian dressing; refrigerate overnight.

title: bacon cheese wreath
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.

Cut a 12-inch square of foil; press into bottom and up sides of 9-inch pan. Place a 3 1/2-cup custard cup inverted in center of pan. Lightly grease pan and cup. Melt cheese and margarine in small pan. Beat until smooth. Pour into prepared pan evenly around cup.
Cut each biscuit into 1/4.

Fit pieces on top of cheese around custard cup. Bake at 450° for 14 minutes (top will be brown). Turn over into serving platter. Remove foil and cup. Sprinkle with crumbled bacon. Makes about 40 appetizers.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: And different pie fillings:

title: o'henry bars
directions: Melt over hot water.
Spread over top of oatmeal mixture while still hot.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Place milk and cheese (chopped up) in top of double boiler. Heat until melted.
Add pimento and pickle relish.
Can be served hot as a dip.
Refrigerate until firm to spread for sandwiches.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients; spread pint of mayonnaise on top. Seal like a lid; sprinkle on sugar, cheese and Bac*Os.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or 8 hours.
This is also good with broccoli.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar, water and pineapple juice.
Chill.
Add cold ginger ale when serving with raspberry sherbet dips on top.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Pour sugar over pears; let set 1 hour.
Add nuts to pear mixture.
Beat eggs; add eggs and oil to pear mixture.
Sift flour, salt and soda to the mixture, a little at a time.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Mix all together and freeze.

title: carrot salad
directions: Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain; cool.
Combine ingredients and mix thoroughly with macaroni.
Chill and serve.

title: hot corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookies in slices; layer around pan.
Cook at 350° until light brown.
Cream together Cool Whip, sugar and cream cheese until it reaches the consistency of butter.
Spread over cookies. Add fruit on top.

title: san antonio chicken
directions: Chop pepper.
Sprinkle both sides of chicken with 1 teaspoon cumin and garlic salt.
Heat oil in 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken; cook 3 minutes.
In medium bowl, combine beans, corn, sauce, pepper and remaining 1 teaspoon cumin. Turn chicken; spoon bean mixture evenly over chicken.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook, uncovered, 6 to 7 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mound apples in buttered pie pan.
Pour on orange juice.
In separate bowl, combine sugar, spices, salt and flour.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: appalachia cherry salad
directions: Mix and freeze.
Makes 16 individual molds.

title: barbecue beans and bacon
directions: Empty 1 can of beans into 1 1/2-quart, heavy casserole dish. Combine brown sugar and mustard; sprinkle half of the mixture over beans.
Top with second can of beans; sprinkle with remaining brown sugar mixture.
Top with bacon.
Spread ketchup over all.

title: daddy's brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken, beef and pork until "stewed."
Drain fat off meat when done.
Add all ingredients and cook until thick, stirring constantly, about 45 minutes, then simmer.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased 1-1/2 quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon if desired. Place in pan of water and bake at 350 for 50 minutes.

title: chicken nancy
directions: Flour chicken strips and saute in hot oil until golden brown. Remove to baking dish. Discard oil from pan.
Melt butter. Add chicken broth, lemon juice, lemon rind, Proscuitto,
wine and garlic.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour over chicken and serve.

title: p.k.'s mostaccioli and sausage
directions: Chop onion, mushrooms and garlic.
Brown in olive oil in large skillet.
Add white wine and simmer until reduced.
Slice Italian sausage and brown with mixture.
Add red wine.
When reduced by half, add mostaccioli and marinara or tomato sauce.
Add basil or oregano, salt and pepper to taste.

title: tex-mex tailgater's chili
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan or large skillet, cook and stir the ground beef or pork and stir until no longer pink; drain. Add salsa and 1/2 cup water. Heat to boiling. Meanwhile, in a small bowl, blend the gravy mix with 1/2 cup cool water and stir in the cumin. Pour gravy mixture into boiling mixture; heat and stir until thickened. Stir in beans, peppers (if desired) and garlic. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. May garnish with cilantro leaves on the serving plate.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump the ingredients in the order given into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread evenly layer upon layer.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until nuts are brown and cake is firm.
May be served hot or cold with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: mary weaver's oyster cracker mix
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Add oyster crackers; stir well.
Then stir every 30 minutes (3 more times).
Store in airtight container.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a glass bowl, place salad greens.
Add celery, green peppers, and peas.	Cover with a layer of red onion.
Add thin layer of light Miracle Whip to cover ingredients.
Put cheddar cheese on top of Miracle Whip and sprinkle parmesan cheese over top.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill 6 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat in frying pan on medium.
Add chopped garlic and spices.
Add chopped pepper.
Add burrito mix, follow directions on package for amount of water needed.
Spray tortillas with Pam or butter; wrap in foil and heat in oven 10 minutes while meat is cooking.
Grease casserole dish.
Put one tortilla on bottom.
Spoon on some crushed tomatoes, some green chilies and picante sauce.
Spread, next some meat mixture.
Add layer of chopped fresh vegetables.
Next some refried beans.
Put tortilla on top.
Continue to layer.
Add one layer of cheese.
Put 2 tortillas on top.
Put remaining ingredients on top of casserole. Cover; cook in preheated oven about 35 minutes.
Cool about 10 minutes.
"Don't forget the sour cream."

title: berried delight
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter.
Press firmly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 15 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip and spread over crust.
Top with strawberries (hulled and halved).
Prepare pudding with 3 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over berries.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding and top with strawberries.
Chill overnight.

title: fruit salad
directions: Blend together the first 3 ingredients; don't whip.
Drain and pat dry the pineapple, cherries and grapes. Cut the bananas. Stir fruits in Cool Whip mixture. Refrigerate until ready to serve. May add 1/2 cup walnuts.

title: mesquite grilled chicken(for a crowd)
directions: Twenty-four hours ahead of cooking time, rinse and dry chicken pieces; set aside.
Combine all ingredients in food processor until smooth.
Place chicken pieces in large Ziploc bags and pour marinade in each.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Soak mesquite wood with lighter fluid 30 minutes before lighting.
Light and allow coals to become red-hot.
Remove chicken from marinade and place over open grill.
Baste with remaining marinade and cook until no longer pink.
Can serve 10 to 12 healthy appetites.

title: banana crush punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Add juices and bananas.
Mix well and freeze in milk carton.
Place frozen block into punch bowl and pour in the ginger ale.
Punch will be slushy.
Serves 60.

title: chicken wings
directions: Snip wings and joints.
Discard tip end of wings.
Put wings in a shallow pan in a single layer.
Combine whiskey, brown sugar and soy sauce; spoon over wings.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until brown and sticky.
Turn several times to get good all around cooking.
Finger food.
Pass on tray.

title: mexican super supper
directions: Stew
chicken
and
remove
from
bone, in chunks.
Mix chicken
with all other ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into a 3 quart casserole.	Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for
30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.
tags: cream of mushroom soup and chicken soup

title: clam chowder
directions: Melt butter in large boiler and cook carrots about 2 minutes. Add onions and cook about 1 minute.
Add potatoes, clams, juice and water.
Cook over low heat until potatoes are soft.

title: pavlova(australian)
directions: Beat eggs and salt until very stiff.
Mix sugar and cornstarch and gradually add to eggs while beating.
Gently fold in vinegar and vanilla.
Beat to blend.
Pile on a baking sheet.
Spread around, making a wall around the edges.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak in 1/2 cup salt water for 3 hours.
Drain.
Heat through in hot vinegar mixture and seal in hot jars.

title: frozen lemonade pie
directions: Partly thaw frozen lemonade.
Using wire whip, fluff ingredients together.
Place in graham cracker crust and keep refrigerated.

title: mashed potatoes and spinach
directions: Beat all together.
Serve like mashed potatoes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats; stir and let sit.
In separate bowl cream shortening, sugars, and eggs, all four spices and baking soda.
Add oatmeal.
Pour into 13 x 9 pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry ice cream sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add boiling water and salt. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens (about 2 minutes).
Add blueberries.
Return to boiling.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: fluffy orange pie
directions: Chill pie crust.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy; gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then juice until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pile into crust.
Chill 2 hours or until set.

title: raisin puff cookies
directions: Cook raisins in water until water disappears.
Cream together margarine and brown sugar.
Mix remaining ingredients together in a bowl, then add hot raisins.
Let set until cool.
Shape into small balls.
Roll the balls in granulated sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheets at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: tuna cheese braid
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Mix celery, onions and relish.
Stir in mayonnaise (1/4 cup).
Mix Bisquick and wine until soft dough forms.
Turn dough on floured cloth. Knead lightly 20 times.
Roll dough into rectangle; 14 x 11-inches, place on cookie sheet.
Spoon tuna mixture on lengthwise down center, sprinkle with cheese.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream the butter. Gradually add sugar at medium speed until light and fluffy. Stir in chocolate. Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each.
Fold in the Cool Whip. Spoon into crust.
Top with whipped cream. Garnish with chocolate shavings. Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: old fashioned coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until firm, approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, 1/3 cup of coconut, olives, onion, bacon, Worcestershire sauce, curry powder and pepper.
Blend thoroughly.
Shape into a ball.
Add for coloring to 1 cup coconut; toss with fork or shake in a bag.
Roll ball in coconut. Chill until ready to serve.

title: helen corbitt's christmas stollen
directions: Cover raisins, currants and fruit with cognac for at least 1 hour.
Drain; mix with nuts and knead into bread dough.
Cut dough in half; roll each piece into an oval about 1/2-inch thick.
Fold over almost in half, so that bottom edge extends beyond the top. Lightly roll to set.
Place on a buttered baking sheet; allow to rise until puffy.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 375° about 45 minutes until loaves are golden brown.
Brush again with melted butter while loaves are warm.
Decorate with sugar icing, whole toasted almonds or pecan halves and candied fruit.
Wrap in clear plastic until needed or freeze.

title: summer okra and rice casserole
directions: In large skillet, fry bacon over medium-high heat until crisp. Drain on paper towel, crumble bacon and set aside.
Reserve 1/2 cup of bacon grease.
Fry okra and onion over medium-high heat until brown but not dry.
Add rice and crumbled bacon, reserving some bacon for garnish.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Serve from skillet or in casserole dish.
Garnish with crumbled bacon. Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Fry the meat in a skillet until it turns brown.
When brown, simmer it with ketchup or barbecue sauce for only one minute and stir the whole minute.
Put the meat in a pan and cover the top of the meat with cheese, and cover the cheese with the biscuits.
Cook in oven according to the time on the biscuit can.
If you like onions, fry them with the meat.

title: zesty salisbury steaks
directions: Measure corn flakes.
Crush to 3/4 cup and place in a large mixing bowl.
Add egg, 1/4 cup of the barbecue sauce, salt and pepper and mix thoroughly.
Add ground beef.
Mix only until combined.
Shape into 6 oval patties about 3/4-inch thick.
Place on lightly greased or foil-lined shallow baking pan.
Brush patties with remaining barbecue sauce.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes for medium doneness.
Shorten or lengthen baking time according to preference.
Do not turn patties while baking.

title: green tomato chutney
directions: Slice tomatoes thinly and place in bowl with salt between layers.
Leave overnight.
Next day, rinse, drain and put in large pot with all remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly, uncovered, until tomatoes are tender and vinegar is nearly absorbed.
This will take close to 5 hours.
Makes anywhere from 2 1/2 to 4 pints.

title: carrot casserole
directions: In a saucepan cover carrots with water and cook until very tender.
Drain and mash.
In a large bowl beat eggs; add onion, celery, parsley, butter and salt.
Stir in carrots, add bread cubes and mix well.
Pour into
greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: church windows(no bake cookies)
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate chips.
Cool.
Add marshmallows (looks awful).
Place small amount of coconut into a 9-inch round pan or 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Pour in chocolate mixture. Cover with a layer of coconut, patted down.
Cool.
Cut.
Looks lovely.

title: dirt and sand cups
directions: Use vanilla pudding and vanilla wafers for sand cups.
Use any candy you want to decorate.

title: pineapple buttermilk salad
directions: Bring to a boil the pineapple and sugar, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add jello, stirring until dissolved.
Cool.
Add buttermilk and stir well.
Fold in Cool Whip and pecans.
Pour in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish and chill until firm.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and add orange juice.
When mixture has thickened, add pineapple, cranberry sauce, celery and nuts; chill until set.

title: italian rice
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add tomato paste when onion is softened.
Add 2/3 broth; stir.
Add all of rice; mix.
As rice swells and cooks up the broth, keep adding small amounts of broth gradually until the rice is done.

title: mississippi river cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar in a large bowl; beat in eggs one at a time.
Sift cocoa powder, salt and flour, then add to egg mixture.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Take out and spread marshmallow cream over cake.
Let cool for 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugar; add eggs, vanilla and sour milk; blend thoroughly.
Sift together flour, salt, cocoa, soda and cinnamon.
Blend with creamed mixture.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, then sprinkle with more chocolate chips while it is hot.

title: tunaburger bernice
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Divide mixture into 6 equal portions.
Form patties with press in the hamburger containers.
Stack and seal tunaburgers.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Mix flour and brown sugar together.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.
Makes 2 (8-inch) pies.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Remove skin from chicken and debone.
Dice into large pieces. Put aside in bowl.
Place Doritos in bowl and pour chicken broth over them.
Let them stand for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Grease large casserole dish.
Layer 1/3 Doritos, 1/2 green peppers, 1/2 onions, 1/2 chicken and 1/3 cheese, ending with Doritos on top.
Mix 2 cans cream of chicken soup, tomatoes and peppers, garlic and chili powder; pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese after taking out of the oven.

title: deluxe cheese cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add crumbs.
Pat into bottom and sides of a 9-inch metal pie pan.
Chill while preparing filling.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients, then add the remaining. Shape into 2 inch round balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet 2 to 3 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: meringue shell(makes 8 to 10 shells)
directions: Beat the egg whites until they are foamy.
Add the cream of tartar; continue beating.
Add 1 tablespoon of sugar at a time, until the egg whites are stiff and glossy.
Do not underbeat.
On brown paper cut to the size of the cookie sheet, shape 8 to 10 meringue shells.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in a preheated 275° oven. Turn the oven off; let the shells cool for 1 hour.
Remove from oven; let the shells cool away from drafts.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients; pour into 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle morsels over top.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown the meat in a little oil.
Mix all together and cook 3 hours.
May be thickened a little.

title: pasta salad with ham and cheese
directions: Cook the pasta in boiling, salted water until just done (10 to 12 minutes).
Drain; rinse in cold water and drain again. Transfer to a bowl.
Cut the ham and cheese into cubes and add to pasta.
Slice the scallions and add to the pasta, along with the parsley.
Stir in the mayonnaise and toss all ingredients until well mixed.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Combine and heat.
Serve in chafing dish with Fritos to dip.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Mix well.
Put in a tightly covered vessel in oven.
Cook at 275° for 5 hours.
Do not peek!

title: florence fix's rice hot dish
directions: Cook the celery in the 3 cups water until partially cooked; do not drain.
In a 3 to 4-quart casserole, combine rice, hamburger, soup, mushrooms and soy sauce.
Add celery and all of the cooking water.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until rice is cooked. (Dish should be covered while baking.)
If you need, you may add more water during the baking time.
Do not add extra salt, as the soy sauce will take care of the seasoning.
You may pass extra soy sauce at the table if you like.

title: mom's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together and pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes, then at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Mix well; bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in a 13 x 9 pan. When cake is cooled, pour icing over cake.

title: rocky road dessert
directions: Put cake in large mixing bowl; melt chocolate.
Beat egg yolks and blend in chocolate.
Beat egg whites quite stiff; add sugar and vanilla.
Fold in whipped cream; add nuts.
Fold in chocolate mixture well.
Pour over cake crumbs.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dripper.
Chill at least 2 days before.
Put whipped cream on top with tiny cherry bits, if desired.

title: deep chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Add water.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly in pan.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut over sugar.
Mix cake as directed. Pour over sugar mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Cool 5 minutes. Turn upside down onto large platter. Serve with whipped cream.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Beat cheese, mayonnaise, onion and chili sauce with mixer. Stir in crabmeat.
Refrigerate.
Take out of refrigerator 1 hour before serving.
Serve on crackers.

title: french toast
directions: Melt butter or margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add sugar and syrup.
Place sliced French bread in dish.
Beat eggs, milk and vanilla together; pour over sliced bread, covering bread well.
Cover with Saran or other wrap; place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
To serve, lift out of baking dish and turn over so syrup will be on top side.

title: laurie's salad
directions: Mix all together and marinate overnight.
Keeps well refrigerated.

title: watergate salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together and chill.
Can be made several days ahead.

title: icebox lemon cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg and milk. Bring to boil and boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add cracker crumbs, nuts and coconut. Line bottom of 8 x 15-inch pan with whole graham crackers. Pour mixture over crackers; top with more whole crackers. Top with Butter Icing.

title: brownie cheesecake bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In mixer bowl, beat flour, sugar, 2/3 cup melted butter, cocoa, 2 eggs, milk, 2 teaspoons vanilla and baking powder until well blended. Stir in nuts.
Spread in pan.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Add first 5 ingredients to cake mix.
Pour 2/3 batter into pan.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Put 1/2 this mixture on the 2/3 batter in pan.
Pour rest of batter on top of this.
Then the remaining topping.
Bake at
350° for 50 minutes.

title: banana pineapple dessert
directions: Mix graham crackers, sugar and butter and press into 9x13 pan.

title: seafood dip
directions: Stir the cream cheese until softened.
Blend in remaining ingredients except walnuts and paprika.
Spread mixture in 9-inch pie plate.
Top with walnuts and paprika.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 25 minutes, until lightly brown.

title: no-mix blackberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir 1/2 cup sugar into fruit; set aside.
Melt butter in baking pan.
Sift the next 4 ingredients together, then add milk.
Pour batter into pan of melted butter, but do not mix!
Pour fruit over, but do not mix!
Bake for 50 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: porcupine
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomato juice.
Form into balls and brown in oven at 425°.
Bring tomato juice to a boil and drop in browned meatballs.
Cook for 30 minutes, then serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: In a saucepan, cook flour, sugar, egg and juices until thick. Cool slightly and add to fruit and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill thoroughly.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions together.
Drain the fat off and add the Spanish rice, refried beans and jar of salsa; mix well.
In the bottom of a large casserole dish, put a layer of Doritos chips in the bottom and add the hamburger mixture for the next layer.
Top with cheese and bake in 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: next best thing to robert redford
directions: Mix all and place in pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or flaky. Cool.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients; stir in potatoes.
Combine milk and butter; add to potato mixture.
Pour in shell and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on box.
Mix all ingredients in greased casserole.
Top with grated cheese and almonds.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pineapple pig-out cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool cake.
Poke holes in cake with a toothpick and pour the can of crushed pineapple (juice too) over cake.
Let juice soak into cake about 30 minutes.
Make the pudding according to package directions and pour over cake and pineapple layer.
Once pudding has set up, spread with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: cheese ball
directions: In Mixmaster, blend all, except pecans.
Put in refrigerator until almost hard.	Roll into ball and then into finely crushed pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate pecan frosting
directions: Melt butter with milk.
Stir in cocoa over low heat.
Add to powdered sugar.
Add nuts (optional).

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Bake in shallow pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Continue baking and baste with sweet and sour sauce.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Sprinkle top with a little grated cheese and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fried rice
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add rice and stir.
Turn to low heat and cover; let stand 20 minutes.
Fry, boil, bake or broil steaks. Cut into bite size pieces.
Fry eggs individually.
When everything is done, mix together all ingredients in large frying pan in butter and soy sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
Fry mixed vegetables and use as a topping for rice.

title: stromboli
directions: Slice meats and cheeses
very
thin or shred.
Roll out bread to fit a cookie
sheet
(let
edges
of
dough hang over sides). Layer meat and
cheese
down
the middle.
Fold dough over.
Whip egg and brush over entire loaf.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sesame crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place biscuits on cookie sheet; form into crescents and taper ends.
Brush lightly with egg white. Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake about 15 minutes.

title: soft cornmeal taco shells
directions: Beat the ingredients until smooth.
Cook about 1/4 cup (small) or 1/3 cup (large) batter at a time over medium heat for about 2 minutes, turning once.
You can help the batter spread out after pouring batter onto pan by rolling your pan.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Combine soup, milk, chicken, cheese, creamettes and onion.
Put in a large bowl and place in refrigerator overnight.
Add eggs just before placing in oven.
Bake in a buttered pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes, then boil until soft.
Drain and place in casserole dish.
Put butter on top of potatoes, then mushroom soup.
Place Velveeta chunks on top.
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Boil sugar, Karo, salt and water until forming hard mass in cold water.
Beat whites of eggs until stiff and gradually pour on the hot syrup.
Beat constantly.
When mixture begins to stiffen, add nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonful onto plate oiled with Mazola.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar, white sugar, eggs and salad oil together. Combine in another bowl the flour, baking powder, salt and soda. Stir to mix well.
Add and stir in quick oats, chopped walnuts, coconut, chocolate chips and raisins.
Combine the 2 mixtures in a large bowl on dishpan.

title: peanut butter milk drink
directions: Beat all ingredients together until smooth.
Refrigerate. Serve cold.
This is a very delicious and nutritional drink. Serves 6.

title: rich double chocolate cream torte(makes 12 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour one 9-inch round layer pan.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll cookie dough out on cookie sheet or in pizza pan.
Bake until done.
Let cool.
Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip together; spread on cookie dough.
Mix strawberries with glaze.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: mama's christmas turkey and gravy(guaranteed success even for beginners)
directions: Take giblets out of turkey.
Rub turkey inside and out with salt.
Push apples into body cavity.
Place bird in large Brown-in-serve Bag.
Tie securely.
Turn him/her upside down in granite roaster or pan of choice and cook 2 to 4 hours at 300° to 350°.
Makes its own juice.
The suculents from the backbone run down into the breast while cooking, thereby enhancing the moistness of the breast.
Never cook your bird breast up!

title: seafood casserole
directions: Melt margarine on medium-high heat in Dutch oven. Add onion, shallots and bell pepper. Saute until clear. Add seafood and cook several minutes. Add both cans of soup and seasoning to taste. Cook several minutes longer.
Turn off heat.
Cook rice separately with 20 ounces of water.
Add cooked rice to mixture, mixing well. Spread in oblong glass Pyrex dish.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 4 to 5.

title: devil dogs
directions: Sift together first 6 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and beat together.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool and fill with the following filling.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut thin slice from stem end of each green pepper.
Remove all seeds and membranes.
Cook peppers in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Cook and stir meat and onion until tender.
Stir in salt and garlic salt, rice and half of tomato sauce.
Heat thoroughly.
Stuff green peppers.
Stand peppers upright in baking dish.
Put remaining sauce over peppers.
Bake 45 minutes, covered.
Uncover.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat 2
eggs
and
add 1 can of pumpkin.
Add sugar and spices.
When
blended
well,
add
condensed
Pet milk.
Pour contents in
2 pie shells and bake at 350° about 45 minutes to 1 hour (until center rises round).

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water on high temperature.
Mixture is done when you drop a small amount in 1/2 cup water, if string breaks like toothpick, then it is ready.
Pour hot mixture into beaten egg whites (very slowly).
Then add vanilla and chopped nuts.
(Do not stir anymore.)
Let set until firm and spoon drop onto waxed paper.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring water, cocoa, oil and oleo to a boil.
Sift flour, sugar and salt in mixing bowl.
Pour liquid ingredients into dry ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients, eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla, while mixing.
Grease and flour cake pan.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: chicken stroganoff
directions: Mix flour and seasonings together.
Roll chicken in flour. Keep remaining flour for later.
Melt butter; brown chicken in butter.
Add more butter if needed.
Remove chicken; add mushrooms and fry for 5 to 8 minutes.
Remove mushrooms; drain and set aside. Pour remaining drippings into baking dish.
Add chicken, skin side up.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove chicken.
Put on warm platter.
Pour drippings from pan into cup; let fat rise to top.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain.
Add the rest of the ingredients; bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer until thickened.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Line pie plate with crescent rolls.
Preheat oven to 375°. Saute zucchini and onions in butter.
Mix all other ingredients together in large bowl and add zucchini and onion mixture.
When ready, pour into pie plate.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Check after 10 minutes to see if crust is brown; if it is, cover with foil for remaining 10 minutes.

title: nachos
directions: On each tortilla chip (flat and round works best), place refried beans (about a tablespoon), then onions (optional), taco or picante sauce, 1 or 2 sliced jalapenos (optional) and sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave until cheese melts.
Top with sour cream and black olives (optional).

title: pasta primavera
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients except spaghetti. Cook uncovered over medium heat until vegetables are tender (approximately 12 minutes).
Stir in spaghetti.
Heat through.

title: hatties icing
directions: I usually make a white cake, 2 layer and slice into 4 layers. After making the cake and frosting it, refrigerate.

title: fruit cupcakes
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add eggs and sour cream; sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix in nuts, dates and candied fruit.
Fill cupcakes 1/2 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except crusts, folding gently rather than stirring.
Pour into crusts and refrigerate overnight.

title: chili con carne
directions: In a skillet or large pan, brown meat and onion.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for at least 1 hour (longer is better).

title: seafood dip
directions: Chop the seafood legs into small pieces.
Soften cream cheese. Add to seafood.
Combine with all other ingredients Serve with crackers.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Crush chocolate wafers.
Add 1 stick of melted butter and press into spring-form pan.
Set in freezer one hour.
Soften coffee ice cream and layer on top of chocolate wafers.
Freeze 1/2 hour.
Add 1 crushed candy bar.
Follow with vanilla ice cream. Freeze 1/2 hour; add 1 crushed candy bar.
End with chocolate ice cream.
Freeze 1/2 hour; top with 2 crushed candy bars.
Freeze at least 3 hours.
Enjoy.

title: rocky road bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt. Add sugar, egg, butter and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 cup walnuts.
Turn into greased 9-inch square pan. Bake for 15 minutes until top is lightly browned and springs back when touched lightly. Remove from oven.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Whisk together egg and yolk, sugar, cornstarch and mustard. Combine vinegar and water, then pour into egg mixture.
Whisk constantly over medium heat until sauce thickens.
Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine and mayonnaise.
Chill.
Toss remaining ingredients together and pour dressing over; mix.

title: seafoam salad
directions: First, mix jello and water.
Set aside.
Mix cottage cheese, salad dressing, evaporated milk and pineapple.
Beat them together, then add jello mixture and refrigerate.

title: lemon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease Bundt or tube cake pan. Combine all ingredients in large bowl of electric mixer and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour batter in prepared pan. Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until tester inserted comes out clean. Cool cake in pan on rack 10 minutes.
Invert on serving platter.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Spoon icing over cake while still warm.

title: cole slaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, sugar and salt.
Add cabbage, carrots and green pepper.
Toss well to coat. Cover and chill.

title: quick 'n easy seafood salad
directions: Prepare
somen	noodles by boiling until tender.
Drain noodles; let sit to evaporate excess water.
After noodles are cool,
add	the crab flakes and the ocean salad; mix together. Add the Tropics dressing to your taste.

title: easy brownies
directions: In medium size saucepan, melt butter.
Add sugar and eggs; stir well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake in buttered 8 x 10-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini coconut bread
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add oil, then mix other ingredients. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours until brown and toothpick comes out dry.

title: pasta al fredo
directions: Prepare pasta according to directions.
Drain.
In large pan, heat cream and margarine on low heat.
Do not boil.
Add pasta, cheese, parsley, salt, pepper and garlic.
Toss gently to coat. Serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 25 to 30 minutes.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Quarter tomatoes.
Place in a large pot with onions and peppers.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup salt.
Mix. Cover with ice and let stand for 1 hour. Cook vinegar and sugar to a boil.
Drain tomato mixture.
Pour syrup over tomatoes and mix well. Put into jars. Place in a boil bath for 15 minutes.

title: rotkohl(red cabbage)
directions: Melt butter.
Add apple and onion.
Cook until soft.
Add cabbage.
Stir to blend.
Add vinegar, sugar, garlic and wine. Cook covered until cabbage is tender, about 12 minutes.
Thicken sauce with flour first, adding a little of the liquid to the flour to make a paste.
Simmer until sauce is smooth.
Makes 4 servings.

title: marshmallow peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and milk in a medium size cooker.
Bring to a boil, stirring continuously.
Boil for 9 minutes, stirring. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, Marshmallow Creme and vanilla.
Pour immediately into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.

title: bacon & cheddar dip
directions: Mix together & serve.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in milk slowly.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Turn heat to low, cover and let cook 10 additional minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: clouds at sunrise(serves 12 to 15)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar.
Then gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff.

title: cheese cake brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare brownies as directed.
Bake 20 minutes.
Beat vanilla, egg, canned milk and cream cheese in bowl until smooth.
Pour over brownies.
Bake 25 minutes longer until set but not browned.
Chill.
Serve topped with pie filling fruit.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli in the bottom of greased dish, adding pieces of chicken breasts on top.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over broccoli and chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 375` for 1 hour or until lightly browned.

title: glazed ham
directions: Drain pineapple and cherry juice, but save it.
Mix sugar, Coke and butter with juice.
This will make sauce.
Pour sauce over ham and cook at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: susan's italian grilled chicken
directions: Place chicken in a container.
Squeeze lemon juice over chicken.
Season with garlic salt to taste.
Pour Italian dressing over breasts, marinate in refrigerator for two hours.

title: weird salad
directions: One hour prior to serving, mix vegetables.
Saute sesame seed and almonds until golden brown and add to vegetables.
Add dressing.
