Immediately before serving, add broken noodles.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes, peel and slice in serving bowl.
Fry bacon until crisp, remove bacon, save bacon drippings.
Add onion and bacon pieces to bowl of potatoes.

title: crustless apple pie
directions: Mix together the egg, sugar, apples and pecans.
Sift together the flour and cinnamon.
Blend together and pour into greased glass pie plate.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes or until browned.

title: apple crisp
directions: In a buttered casserole dish, place apples, cinnamon, water and salt.
Mix sugar, flour and butter into crumbs.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in oven at 350° about 30 minutes or until apples are soft.
Serve with cream or ice cream.

title: peppermint brownies
directions: Combine butter and 5 oz. chocolate in saucepan.
Melt over low heat.
Cool to room temperature.
Combine eggs and sugar, beat on high two minutes.
Add cooled chocolate mixture, vanilla, and peppermint extract.
Blend well.
Sift flour and salt.
Add dry ingredients to chocolate mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans. Pour into jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1 inch.
Bake in 325 degree oven for 25 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Frost with peppermint frosting.
Melt 1/2 oz. chocolate and drizzle over frosting.

title: cape cod oatmeal cookies
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in the rest of ingredients.
Arrange by teaspoon on buttered cookie sheets.
Bake until the edges are brown (about 12 minutes).
For thicker cookies, increase the oatmeal to 2 cups and the flour to 1 3/4 cups.

title: low-fat crispy oven-fried okra
directions: Wash okra, trim ends and cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Combine cornmeal, salt and pepper in a medium bowl.
Stir well and set aside.

title: cornbread
directions: Sift together the meal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Add milk, melted shortening and egg; mix until batter is smooth. Pour into greased pan.
Have oven preheated.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Simmer first 3 ingredients together until tender, about 3 minutes. Then add rest of ingredients. Simmer until heated through. You can use cauliflower instead of broccoli if you desire.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease bottom of 8 or 9-inch loaf pan.
Mix sugar and butter together.
Stir in eggs, then add remaining ingredients except the nuts until moistened.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours for 8-inch loaf or 55 to 60 minutes for 9-inch loaf.
Cool 5 minutes.
Loosen sides and remove.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add sugar, then remaining ingredients in order.
Dough may be kept in refrigerator.
Just pinch off the amount needed.
Work in a small amount of flour to keep from being sticky.
Bake as any other biscuits.

title: chocolate-nut brownies
directions: Melt the unsweetened chocolate and shortening in a saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Add sweetener, vanilla and beaten eggs.
Stir until well blended.
Add flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: mom m's chili sauce
directions: Wash and quarter tomatoes.
Cook (boil) 15 minutes.
Drain off half or more juice.
Puree in blender the tomatoes.
Add all ingredients.
Put in largest roaster.
Cook in slow oven at 325° until thick, 2 to 3 hours.
Seal in hot sterilized jars and seal. Makes 11 pints.

title: applesauce
directions: Peel and core apples.
Cut into chunks; put in 3-quart saucepan with apple cider.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover; simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Stir in 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Mash in the pot (or cool and puree in a food processor).
Cool, then store in clean jars. Refrigerate up to 2 weeks.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in 2 cups boiling water; add the 4 1/2 quarts water and stir well.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Serve over ice.
Yield:
50 (6 ounce) servings.

title: old fashioned peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Toss sliced peaches with lemon juice. Stir in sugar, flour, lemon peel and nutmeg.
Roll half the pastry into an 11-inch circle; fit into a 9-inch pie plate.
Roll out remaining pastry for top crust.
Spoon peach mixture into pie shell.
Cover with top crust; trim, fold edge under and crimp. Cut a round hole in the top; make leaves out of extra pastry and place at top of hole.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with ice cream if you like.

title: tahitian brunch cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, water, eggs, pineapple, juice and nuts. On low speed, mix until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed. Pour into pan.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool upright 25 minutes. Invert onto plate.
Cool completely.
Glaze cake.

title: microwave swiss steak(cooking time 55 to 60 minutes)
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces.
Arrange in 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole.
Top with onion, mushrooms, tomato soup, salt and pepper.
Cook on Defrost, covered, 55 to 60 minutes or until meat is tender.
Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: baked red snapper(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Line an 8 x 12-inch rectangular baking dish evenly with spinach.
Sprinkle mushrooms and then scallions over spinach.
Pour half the salsa over all.
Lay fish in single layer on top of salsa and vegetables.
Top fish with remaining salsa.
Bake, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes, or until fish is just opaque throughout.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven for 2 to 3 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Wash, peel and slice potatoes.
Layer cheese between potato slices.
Add remaining ingredients in casserole dish or 2 quart Pyrex dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Toss together bread crumbs and pineapple chunks. Place in a greased 2-quart baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over pineapple. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Casserole can be made up and refrigerated overnight before baking. Reheats well.

title: cranberry cinnamon tea
directions: Simmer in a crock-pot and serve hot.

title: spaghetti ala carbonara
directions: Fry bacon and chip.
Fry ham cubes.
Return bacon and ham to fat to keep hot.
Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Beat egg yolks lightly.
Cook spaghetti until tender; drain well.
Toss spaghetti in bacon chips, ham cubes and all the bacon fat.
Then, toss in egg yolks and whites.
Add remaining ingredients and toss well. Serve hot.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cut marshmallows into quarters.
Layer pineapple, marshmallows and cream cheese until all are used.
Pour over sauce.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese on top melts.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Press firmly into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 15 minutes.

title: key lime tart
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: lasagna d'italia
directions: Cook noodles in salted water about 15 minutes; drain. Spread out on oiled cookie sheet; layer between wax paper and oil. Set aside.

title: turkey wings delight
directions: Preheat oven temperature to 375°.
Wash turkey wings.
Pour 1 cup water in roast pan.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon seasoned salt in water.
Place turkey wings in a pan.
Sprinkle chopped celery, onions and pepper on wings.
Place cut up bell peppers on top of wings.
Sprinkle seasoned salt on wings to your delight.
Cook for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Baste wings with juices every 20 minutes. Make sure wings are not too dry in oven.
If a lot of juice is in pan, drain 3/4 of juice.
Remove after 1 hour and 15 minutes. Place on stove top burners (2 burners).
Fry for about 10 to 15 minutes, turning for an even brown color.

title: sweet and sour chinese cabbage
directions: Rinse and drain trimmed cabbage.
Cut into 1 inch crosswise strips.
Heat oil in skillet or wok.
Add the cabbage and ginger and cook uncovered 5 minutes.
Add the leafy parts of cabbage and cook 2 more minutes.
Cover and cook 1 minute.

title: peanut butter sandwich cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and brown sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Blend in peanut butter and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt. Stir into creamed mixture.
Form mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until golden brown.
When cooled, spread one cookie with Peanut Butter Filling.
Place another cookie on top.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Wash shrimp and devein.
Mix together and beat well.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine and boil for a few minutes the brown sugar, butter and milk. Set aside.

In a large bowl, mix cinnamon and white sugar. Cut 2 cans of biscuits into quarters. Toss them in the sugar and cinnamon mixture and drop into tube pan. Sprinkle some of the mixture over the biscuits, then pour 1/2 syrup and 1/2 nuts. Repeat with the other 2 cans of biscuits, but sprinkle on nuts first, then pour on syrup.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Turn out on place to cool at least 5 minutes before serving.
Do not cut, pull apart.
Use tube or Bundt pan.

title: hickory smoked beans
directions: Fry bacon in a large skillet.
Remove bacon, drain thoroughly and dice.
Saute onions in some bacon drippings.
Drain.
Put together in casserole dish all the ingredients and bake for one hour at 325°.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, milk, eggs and spice; pour into pie shell. Bake for 15 minutes at 425°, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream sugar, cream cheese and peanut butter together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in graham cracker crust and freeze 2 hours, then refrigerate.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix ingredients; bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan and freeze overnight.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving. Store in freezer.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Enjoy!!

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Brown onion and bell pepper.
Add Velveeta cheese until melted.
Add mushroom soup, chicken soup, Ro-Tel and chicken. Pour sauce over cooked, drained spaghetti.

title: broccoli, rice and cauliflower casserole
directions: Heat water, margarine, soup, milk and cheese in saucepan until cheese melts.
Add rice.
Slightly cook broccoli and cauliflower in small amount of water. Drain. Add to mixture. Pour in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Let cool.
Poke holes in cake with straw.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Drain broccoli well.
Combine broccoli, onion, bell pepper, mushrooms and place cheese on top.
Beat milk, eggs, salt, pepper and Bisquick.
Pour over other ingredients.
Spray baking dish with Pam.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Slice.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O.
Use juice of pineapple and oranges as part of the water.
Add pineapple and orange Jell-O.
Put Jell-O in refrigerator and when jelled, dissolve instant pudding in milk. Top the Jell-O before the pudding has time to set up.

title: criss-cross potatoes
directions: Scrub potato; cut in half lengthwise.
Make diagonal slashes about 1/8-inch deep in cut surface of potato, forming crisscross pattern.
Brush cut surface with butter; season with salt or seasoned salt.
Place in small shallow pan or on piece of foil. Bake in hot oven (400°) for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle potato with paprika (optional).
Bake 10 minutes more or until done.
Serves 2. (You can wrap potato in foil and place on your grill; turn every 5 to 10 minutes until done.)

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Remove	12
large
outer leaves from cabbage.
Trim off thick part
of
each
leaf.
Add leaves and 1 teaspoon salt to boiling water.
Allow
to stand five
minutes, so they become pliable. Drain.
Combine
onions,
garlic, ground meat, rice, eggs, pepper and 1 teaspoon salt.
Place mound of meat mixture (1/2 cup) in hollow of each leaf.
Fold the sides of leaf over stuffing.
Roll up	from
the thick end of leaf to make roll. Arrange
cabbage rolls
seam
side
down
in lightly buttered shallow
quart baking pan.
Combine tomato sauce, tomatoes, lemon juice, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Pour
over cabbage
rolls.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Cover.	Bake
at
375° for
minutes.	Uncover and cook 10 minutes
longer.
Remove to	a
warm
serving platter;
spoon sauce over all.
Serves 8.

title: spanish cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour batter in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Spread the beaten egg whites to which was added 1 cup brown sugar. Sprinkle 1 cup chopped nuts on top. Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: stuffed turkey burgers
directions: Mix turkey, onion, salt and pepper.
Divide into 12 equal portions.
Flatten into patties and fill six patties with 2 tablespoons dressing.
Cover with other 6 patties.
Fry in deep skillet in 2 tablespoons oil until done on both sides.
Add mushroom soup, which has been mixed with milk and simmer 30 minutes, adding nutmeg last.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: To prepare pastry, in a medium bowl, mix together flour and salt.
Using a pastry blender or 2 knives, cut butter into flour until coarse crumbs form.
In a small bowl, beat together egg and water.
Add to the flour mixture; mix lightly until a soft dough forms.
Shape into dish, wrap in plastic wrap, and chill in the refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: custard
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in double boiler top.
Mix in egg.
Gradually add milk.
Stir well.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until mixture is slightly thickened, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Remove from boiling water.
Stir in vanilla.
Makes 1 quart.

title: mushroom berkeley
directions: Mix together mustard, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce to form a smooth paste.
Add wine and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Wash mushrooms and cut in half (unless they are too small).
Wash and seed bell peppers and cut into 1-inch squares.
Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Add mushrooms and peppers and saute, stirring often.
As mushrooms begin to brown and reduce in size, add wine sauce.
Simmer mixture over medium heat for about 45 minutes or until sauce is much reduced and thickened.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.
Great over rice or as an accompaniment to meat.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Break cake into small pieces; place half in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pie filling over the pieces of cake, saving some cherries for garnish.
Put remaining cake over filling.
Beat the pudding mix and milk.
Add the whipped topping; mix until smooth and blended.
Spread over cake; garnish with the saved cherries from the filling.
Refrigerate.
Better if made the day before served.
May use other fruit.

title: sugar snap peas with basil and lemon
directions: Heat oil in a nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add peas; stir-fry 3 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Sprinkle with basil and next 3 ingredients.
Stir-fry one minute.
Serve immediately with lemon wedges.
Yields 2 servings with 95 calories (25% from fat) per serving.

title: spaghetti casserole(serves 8)
directions: Prepare your usual recipe of spaghetti sauce with meat.
In a large casserole dish (at least 2-quart), begin with a layer of cooked spaghetti, add layer of meat sauce.
Add 1/2 of soup, a layer (1/2) of olives and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spicy wine pot roast
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper and place in crock pot. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over meat.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours.
Remove meat and slice.
Thicken sauce with flour and water if desired.
Yields:
6 to 7 servings.

title: fairy salad
directions: Dice all but bananas and place in colander to drain.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry perk
directions: Put spices, cinnamon stick and brown sugar in coffeemaker basket. Add water to the juices to make 10 cup level in coffeemaker.
Perk on regular coffee cycle. Serve hot.

title: gob cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as on package, then add pudding, eggs and oil.
Mix well and bake in 2 long cake pans.
Line pans with wax paper; divide batter.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: company shrimp casserole
directions: Saute onions, pepper and celery in butter until tender.
Mix soup and shrimp; add to mixture.
Mix and place in butter casserole and bake at 300° until thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.

title: onion and cucumber dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate before serving with chips or fancy crackers.

title: "get-together" deviled eggs
directions: Cut hard-boiled eggs in half lengthwise.
Set whites of eggs aside.
Mash all the yolks with a fork.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients.
Refill the whites with the egg yolk mixture.
(Heap it up slightly.)
For more color, garnish the deviled eggs with parsley or sprinkle with paprika.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs. Add margarine, sugar and vanilla. Mix flour, cocoa, baking powder, salt and soda; add this mixture to the first mixture, alternating with water. Stir in sauerkraut; mix. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until center is barely set. This is very moist.

title: white christmas pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Mix in saucepan the 1/2 cup sugar, salt, flour and milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring mixture until it boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in dissolved gelatin.
Cool.
When mixture is partially set, beat with beater until smooth.
Blend in vanilla and almond extract.
Whip cream until stiff.
Beat until fluffy the egg whites.
Add cream of tartar and 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat until stiff and glossy.
Fold into custard.
Fold in coconut.
Put in baked pie shell.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Chill until set.

title: olive cheese salad
directions: Mix together.
Package in paper cups or in oblong cartons. Freeze.
Unmold on lettuce leaf and serve with mayonnaise or French dressing to which grated onion has been added.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: pickled okra
directions: Mix vinegar, 1/2 cup salt and water.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to simmer for 5 minutes.
Put 1 clove garlic and 1 hot pepper in hot jars.
Pack with okra and put in 1 teaspoon of dill seed; pour in vinegar while hot.

title: ten minutes healthy cookies
directions: Mix in large pot the syrup and sugar, heat just enough to dissolve the sugar.
Add peanut butter and stir until color is even.
Add Rice Krispies and coat cereal well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: blackened beef stir-fry
directions: Trim separable fat from beef; partially freeze meat.
Cut meat across the grain into thin, bite size strips.
In a medium bowl, stir together paprika, garlic powder, thyme, black pepper, salt and red pepper.
Add steak strips; toss to coat well.
In a small bowl, stir together the 2/3 cup beef broth, tomato paste and cornstarch.
Set aside.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Arrange fruit in layers in buttered 3-quart casserole. Sprinkle each layer with brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg; dot with butter.
Bake in a 300° oven for about 30 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate on low heat.
Blend in sugar, salt and eggs.
Stir in flour and vanilla.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Very good.

title: sandy's potato salad
directions: Pour Italian dressing over hot diced potatoes until well coated.
Marinate several hours or overnight.
Mix remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: fettuccine with shrimp and creamy herb sauce
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, blend soup mix and milk thoroughly. Bring just to boiling point, stirring frequently.
Add shrimp. Simmer 3 minutes.
Toss shrimp, hot noodles and cheese.

title: cheese potatoes in the microwave
directions: Pierce potatoes with a fork.
Do not peel.
Place in microwave on a paper towel.
Cook on High for 20 minutes or until done. Cool slightly; do not peel.
Slice and set aside.
Place margarine in glass microwave-safe bowl.
Cook at High for 2 to 3 minutes to melt.
Remove from oven and stir in cheese.
When cheese melts, add sour cream, salt, pepper and onions.
Gently stir cheese mixture into potatoes.
Spoon in microwave-safe 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Top with paprika.
Cook, uncovered, on High power for 7 to 8 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: sweet potato fritters
directions: Spread potatoes and onion on clean dish towel; roll up, twisting towel to extract excess moisture from vegetables.
In a bowl, whisk eggs, flour, 1/2 teaspoon of salt and 1/4 teaspoon of pepper until smooth.
In a large, nonstick skillet, heat 1/4 cup of oil over medium-high heat.
Add vegetables to batter; mix. Spoon mixture into skillet, allowing 1 heaping tablespoon for each fritter.
With back of spoon, flatten slightly.
Fry six fritters at a time; cook 4 minutes.
Turn, then cook 2 to 4 minutes more. Drain on paper towels.
Keep warm while frying remaining fritters. Add more oil if necessary.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Combine carrots, soup and cheese in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Mix bread crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lairs rice
directions: Throw it into a covered dish.
Bake 50 minutes in oven. Add 1/2
cup
cashew
nuts,
crushed.
Mix and bake another 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: chinese scallops and veggie stir-fry
directions: Heat oils in wok or frying pan.
Add scallops; saute for about 2 minutes.
Remove.
Add vegetables; stir-fry until tender-crisp. Add hoisin sauce and ginger; return scallops to pan.
Heat through.
Serves 2.

title: beef salad with blue cheese
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon oil and 2 tablespoons vinegar.
Cook onion, covered, for 2 minutes.
Add onions to other vegetables.

title: lemon angel pie
directions: Beat egg yolks for 3 minutes. Gradually add sugar. Beat on low speed for 2 minutes. Blend in lemon juice for 1 minute. Cook over hot water in double boiler until the mixture is thick. Cool.

title: crispy fried chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients and set aside.

title: lemon ginger rice
directions: In a 2 to 3-quart pan bring ginger ale and water to a boil over high heat.
Stir in rice, lemon peel and ginger; cover and turn heat to low.
Cook until rice is tender to bite and liquid is absorbed, about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and fluff rice with a fork, then mix in the wheat germ and serve with salt if wanted. Yields 4 to 5 servings.

title: four fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3/4 cup juice. In saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch. Add pineapple juice, orange juice and lemon juice. Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat. Set aside. Combine pineapple chunks, oranges, apples and bananas.
Pour warm sauce over fruit.
Stir gently to coat. Cover and refrigerate.

title: cobbler
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and milk; then pour into a 2-quart baking dish.
Melt butter and pour over mixture.
Top with fruit.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Pastry:
Combine 1 1/4 cups flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt; cut in shortening.
Stir in fine pecans.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon water. Toss with fork; add water until all is moistened.
Dough forms ball.
Roll out and put in 9-inch pie plate.

title: summer chicken salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise and Cool Whip.
Add all other ingredients. Mix well and serve on lettuce leaf.
Can also be served spooned into tomatoes, cantaloupes or pineapple.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring to boil 1/2 strawberries, sugar and cornstarch.
Put other half of drained berries in bottom of pie crust, adding cooked glaze on top.
Top with whipped cream, sugar and vanilla mixture.

title: coconut cake
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar and oil.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Add vanilla extract and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in Bundt pan.
Remove cake from oven and make fork holes all over top of cake.

title: almond bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and 1 cup flour; mix well.
Add oil or butter. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Remove from pans and slice as needed.

title: donuts
directions: Mix all together; mix well.
Roll 1/3 to 1/2-inch thick on a floured board.
Do not try to roll out whole recipe at once.
Cut with donut cutter or biscuit cutter; make hole with finger.
Fry at 400° approximately.
Turn once until done; drain.
Cool, dust with confectioners sugar when cool or frost with any kind you wish.
Yield: 4 dozen.
Recipe from Marilyn Priebe in Triplett.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix together and chill for several
hours.
Roll very thin. Cut with cookie cutter.
Top with topping.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine carrots, oil, eggs and sugar.
In another bowl, combine all dry ingredients, except nuts.
Blend both carrot mixture and flour mixture together, then add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and salt. Mix sugar, butter or margarine, egg and molasses.
Mix dry ingredients with molasses mixture.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes in a 12 x 15-inch pan.

title: beef dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Chill for several hours.
Spoon into hollowed-out round Hawaiian bread loaf.
Serve with bread pieces for dipping.
Yield:
4 cups.

title: tooey's coffeecake
directions: In bowl, sift flour, salt, soda and powder.
In large bowl, mix butter, sugar and eggs on medium speed.
Alternate sour cream and sifted mixture, mixing in bowl.
Add vanilla.
Place half the mixture in a lightly greased and floured tube pan.
Sprinkle half the walnut/cinnamon mixture evenly on top of the cake.
Add remaining batter and sprinkle with remaining walnut/cinnamon mixture.

title: pineapple nut bars
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Mix butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add dry ingredients to mixture, stirring well.
Add pineapple and nuts; mix well.
Pour into greased pan and bake 45 minutes at 350° or until nice and brown. Cool, cut into bars and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: puffed baked fish
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Arrange fish fillets in buttered baking dish.
Combine salad dressing, cheese and well-beaten egg white. Spread over fish.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes without opening oven door.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Wash,
peel
and
slice
eggplant into 1/2-inch slices. Grease a baking dish.
Arrange eggplant slices in baking dish. Cover with stewed tomatoes, green pepper and onion.
Sprinkle with salt,
pepper, garlic salt and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: chili pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375° and butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix the chilies and mushrooms together and put on bottom of pan. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Mix eggs together with milk and pour over cheese.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes until brown around edges.
Cut into squares and serve on Ritz crackers.

title: basic cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add vanilla and eggs and blend well. Add flour and baking soda and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on foil lined cookie sheet or roll out and cut with a cookie cutter. Bake at 400° 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cheese until soft and fluffy. Beat in sugar and peanut butter. Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly. Fold topping into peanut butter mixture. Pour into pie crusts. Sprinkle with peanuts and chill until firm.

title: garlic grits(vegetables)
directions: Put salt in water and bring to boil.
Add grits and cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and cheese. Stir until this is melted.
Place eggs in measuring cup and beat slightly.
Add milk to make 1 cup.
Stir and add to grits mixture. Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Add grated cheese on top for the last 2 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach as directed on box.
Melt butter and saute onions.
Add
flour;
do
not brown.
Add cheese and mix well. Add the rest of the ingredients and heat to a boil.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and pecans.
Drain pineapple and save juice.
Add pineapple to Jell-O mixture.
Stir until cranberry sauce is dissolved.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into dish and refrigerate until Jell-O is set.
Mix cream cheese and pineapple juice together.	You may not need all of the juice.
Mixture should be the consistency of cake icing. Spread cream cheese mixture over first layer of Jell-O.
Pour remainder of Jell-O mixture on top and refrigerate 8 hours.

title: chicken casserole pie
directions: Put chicken, soup, broth and eggs in casserole dish.
Mix milk, oleo and flour and pour over chicken mixture.
Bake 45 min. to 1 hour on 350 degrees until brown.

title: hot tomato sauce
directions: Simmer tomatoes and peppers until mushy.
Run through food mill.
Add salt, sugar, vinegar and spices in bag and simmer until it thickens.
Bottle in sterilized jars.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
Drain and add soup. Simmer.
Add lima beans and noodles and cook slow for 30 minutes.

title: jello dixie lollipops
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water.
Let stand to cool for 15 minutes.
Pour into Dixie cups.
Refrigerate until firm, at least 3 hours.
Carefully peel away cups.
Using a knife dipped in warm water, cut each gelatin cup horizontally into 3 round slices.
Insert straw half into each gelatin slice to resemble a lollipop.
Makes 12 pops.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar, beat in eggs.
Stir in bananas and butter, add dry ingredients and walnuts.
Stir only until moist. Turn into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Store overnight before slicing if desired.

title: merk's coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla; add eggs singly, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and baking soda together; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream. Spread 1/2 of batter in 10-inch greased tube pan.
Cream butter, cinnamon and brown sugar together.
Add nuts; mix well.
Dot batter mixture in pan with nut mixture.
Cover with remaining batter.
Dot with remaining nut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes after baking.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together until mixture is thickened. Easy and delicious!!!!!

title: genny's pecan pie
directions: In a small bowl, mix together the sugar and flour until well blended. In a large bowl, mix all of the ingredients together, including the sugar and flour mixture. Pour into the shell and bake until firm or until a knife inserted into the center comes out clean. Bake in a 300° oven for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: grape juice crush
directions: Mix juices and sugar, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Just before serving, stir in ginger ale.
Serve over ice.

title: banana nut layer cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (8-inch) layer pans.
Start oven 10 minutes before baking at 350°.
Sift flour and measure; resift 4 times with soda and salt.
With silver fork, quickly crush bananas to fine paste.
Add lemon juice and stir in buttermilk.
Cream shortening with wooden spoon; add sugar gradually and cream thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with banana mixture in 3 or 4 portions, beginning and ending with flour, and beating well after each addition.
Fold in nuts.

title: tomato salsa canned
directions: Combine tomatoes, onions and peppers.
Mix paste with vinegar and add; stir thoroughly.
Mix together dry ingredients and add to mixture when hot.
Cook until thick.
Pour into jars and process 10 minutes at 5 pounds of pressure.
Yields 5 to 6 quarts; 10 to 12 pints.

title: fresh green bean salad
directions: Clean and cut string beans at an angle.
In 12-inch skillet, put string beans in 1/2-inch boiling water.
Bring to a boil over high heat again.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 10 minutes or until barely tender.
Drain beans well.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, eggs, milk, margarine, sugar, vanilla and salt. Pour into buttered baking dish.
Mix topping ingredients and spread over sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until topping is brown.

title: cajun red beans and rice
directions: Sort, rinse and soak red beans according to package directions.
Combine all ingredients except rice and cook covered for 4 hours at low boil on stove top or 10 to 12 hours in crock-pot.

title: peanut butter popcorn
directions: Boil sugar, honey and syrup in heavy saucepan for 2 minutes. Blend in vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour over 3 quarts popped popcorn, nuts (peanuts, almonds or cashews are good).
Don't make too much popcorn or syrup gets spread too thin.

title: salmon log
directions: Mix salmon and cream cheese well.
Add lemon juice, onion, relish and salt.
Mix well.
Make log or ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: emma's krumkaker
directions: Whip eggs and sugar.
Add butter which has been melted and cooled.
Add water and the remaining ingredients.
Bake in a krumkake iron.

title: sausage balls
directions: Other spices may be added for spicier taste.

title: potato-carrot soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add onion and saute until browned.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Add to onion with potatoes and carrots.
Add salt, pepper, celery salt and bay leaf; simmer until potatoes are tender.
Stir in evaporated milk. Blend water with flour and stir into soup.
Heat and stir until slightly thickened.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Remove shells from shrimp, leaving shell on tail section.
Devein, wash under running water and drain on paper towels.
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch baking dish in oven. Add salt, garlic and 1 tablespoon parsley.
Mix well.
Arrange shrimp in single layer in baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Turn shrimp, sprinkle on lemon peel, lemon juice and remaining parsley.
Bake 10 minutes.
Arrange shrimp on heated platter.
Pour garlic butter over all.
Garnish with lemon wedges.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Drain canned fruits thoroughly.
Toss bananas in lemon juice. Add to drained fruits.
Add pie filling and gently mix together. Serves 12.

title: banana split pie
directions: Slice bananas into bottom of crust.
Spoon softened ice cream on top.
Spread to flatten.
Freeze for 3 hours.
Top with unheated hot fudge, dollops of whipped topping, pineapple, chopped nuts and maraschino cherries.
Serve immediately or can be frozen.

title: spicy spud chicken
directions: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees. Coat a 9 X 13 baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Place the melted butter in a shallow dish. In a large bowl, combine the remaining ingredients except chicken. Dip chicken pieces into butter, them potato mixture, coating well. Place the chicken in baking dish and bake for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: nut cups
directions: Soften butter and cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix together.
Add flour to form a soft dough.
Chill overnight.
Form into 30 walnut size balls.
Place each ball into mini muffin pan. Press into form of each cup.

title: caesar salad
directions: Make dressing, oil, garlic, pepper, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and anchovy; mix well.
Arrange lettuce after it's been washed and dried.
Pour over lettuce.
Sprinkle on cheese and add croutons.

title: strawberry snowball cake
directions: Cut cake in half and tear one portion into small pieces. Spread pieces evenly in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Soften cream cheese. Mix Dream Whip as directed on package.
Add sugar and softened cream cheese to Dream Whip and mix well.
Spread the mixture over the pieces of broken cake.

title: pineapple banana bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Mix in nuts and set aside.
Combine eggs and oil with the dry ingredients.
Add bananas, pineapples and vanilla.
Mix well. Spoon into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.

title: cheesy macaroni and ham
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese according to package directions. Add soup and ham; mix well.
Put mixture into small baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: divinity candy
directions: Stir sugar, corn syrup and water over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cook, without stirring, until mixture forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
In mixing bowl, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Keep beating while pouring hot syrup in a small stream into egg whites.
Add vanilla; beat until mixture holds its shape and becomes slightly dull.
Fold nuts in.
Drop mixture from tip of buttered spoon onto waxed paper.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Blend until appearance of biscuit mix.
Spread 3/4 of this mixture on bottom of pie shell.
Combine cornstarch and sugar.
Add egg yolks and gradually add to cornstarch and sugar.
Mix well, then cook in heavy saucepan until mixture thickens.
Add vanilla and margarine. Pour into a pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients; add celery seed.
Add vinegar, parsley and boiling water; cook until thick.
After dressing is cooked, remove from stove and add mustard.
Pour over cooked, peeled potatoes.
Add chopped celery and hard-cooked eggs.

title: six week muffins
directions: Mix together first five ingredients.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all at once
in
bowl (for 1/2 this amount, use 1/2 cottage cheese and	small
Cool
Whip).
Chill
until ready to use.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Add cocoa to sugar; mix up good, then add milk, salt and water.
Cook all together until forms a soft ball in a little cold water, then beat well until starts to get cool.
Add peanut butter.
Beat until thickened, then pour in greased platter (grease platter with butter).
Let cool 30 minutes, then ready to serve.

title: fruity ice cream punch
directions: Combine thawed frozen juice concentrate and club soda in a punch bowl.
Spoon in ice cream.
Serve immediately.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add last 2 ingredients.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Sprinkle marshmallows on bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine strawberries and Jell-O.
Let set a minute.
Combine rest of ingredients; pour batter over marshmallows.
Spoon strawberry Jell-O mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sweet potato pecan pie
directions: Cook and mash sweet potatoes.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl, stirring until well blended.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 375° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: golden eagle peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, water and syrup until it spins a thread.
Add raw peanuts, a pinch of salt and butter.
Cook until it spins another thread.
Remove from heat.
Add soda and stir, pour at once in shallow pan and spread to desired thickness.
When cooled, bend pan until candy releases pan.
Break into pieces.

title: chocolate fudge pudding
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients plus 2 tablespoons cocoa.
Add milk, shortening and vanilla.
Mix only until smooth; add pecans.
Pour in greased shallow pan, 9 x 9-inches.
Mix brown sugar and remaining 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Sprinkle over mixture in pan. Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix with buttermilk until you get the consistency. Bake about 30 to 35 minutes at 400°.

title: creamed garden soups
directions: Saute onion in butter; add flour and milk; blend smooth.
Add vegetable variation; blend to smooth.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Put sour cream, lemon juice, sugar and bananas in mixer and beat until smooth.
Fold in pecans, strawberries and cherries. Pour into large flat casserole and freeze.
Before serving, let set at room temperature for a short time; cut into squares and serve.

title: one bowl cake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and cocoa, then add other ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Preheat oven to 350° to 375°. Bake 30 minutes or until done.

title: garden pasta
directions: Heat oil in large frying pan and saute garlic and onion over medium heat for 2 minutes or until slightly golden.
Add tomatoes; stir and cook for 3 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in buttered quart dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Stir 3 times.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, celery, carrots and salt in large kettle.
Cover with water and boil approximately 30 minutes (until tender).
Mix milk and cream of chicken (or mushroom) soup together in separate bowl.
Reduce heat first, then add milk mix. Stir constantly until mixed well.
Add butter.
Let simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: christmas cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup nuts.
Refrigerate until firm, then shape in a ball and then roll in nuts.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl; stir well and set aside.
Combine sugar and oil in a medium bowl.
Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer 2 minutes or until well blended.
Add eggs, beat until light and lemon colored.
With mixer running at low speed, add flour mixture alternately with banana, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Blend well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted comes back clean.
Cool 15 minutes in pan on a wire rack.
Remove from pan and let cool completely on wire rack. Yields 16 servings.

title: tomato ketchup
directions: Cut up	tomatoes
and
onions before measuring. Mix and put in 1/2 cup
salt.
Mix
and
let
set	2
hours.
Drain in colander. Mix
with
sugar and vinegar. Boil 25 or 30 minutes or to desired thickness. Can and seal.

title: chasen's famous chili
directions: Wash beans and place in a bowl.
Add cold water to two-inches above beans.
Soak overnight.
Simmer, covered, in same water until tender.
Add tomatoes and simmer five minutes.
Saute green peppers slowly in salad oil for five minutes.
Add onion and cook until tender, stirring frequently.
Add garlic and parsley.

title: beef with snow peas and mushrooms(bo xao dau hoa-lan)
directions: Prepare the rice and set aside.
Soak mushrooms with hot water until soft, about 20 minutes.
Drain; rinse well, remove the stems and cut into quarters.
In a wok or skillet over high heat, add 1/2 tablespoon of oil and onion.
Stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add beef, garlic, m.s.g, soy sauce and pepper into the wok.
Stir-fry until the beef is cooked, about 2 minutes.
Remove to a plate. Return the wok to high heat and add the remaining oil.
Add mushrooms and carrot; stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add oyster sauce and chicken stock and cook until reduced by half.
Add snow peas and cook for 1 minute.
Add beef mixture to the wok and cook just to heat through.
Serve with rice.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: harvest carrot salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, tossing well.
Cover and refrigerate before serving.

title: vegetable rice casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover.
Chill and serve.

title: cold pepper steak(excellent for summer buffets)
directions: In 12 x 8-inch baking dish, combine the first 6 ingredients. Add steak.
Coat with mixture.
Marinate, covered, 8 hours in refrigerator.
Broil 30 minutes on broiling pan, turning once. Cover and refrigerate to serve cold.
Makes 8 servings.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water according to package directions. Drain.
Set oven to 375°.
Add butter or margarine, egg, diced cheese, milk and seasoned salt to taste while macaroni is hot.
Mix well.
Bake about 45 minutes or less until browned.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Boil potatoes until done; drain well.
Cream the egg, butter, sugar and flour.
Mix with potatoes.
Place in refrigerator until chilled.
Spoon into small balls, using a medium marshmallow in center.
Fry or bake at 350°.

title: claudette macaroni
directions: Boil macaroni.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish add beaten eggs and
cut
pound
Cheddar
cheese
in cubes, then add 2 sticks of margarine and black pepper to taste.
When macaroni is done, drain
and
add milk.
Pour into dish and stir until thick.
Slice the other pound of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until bubbly and brown.

title: yellow pickled squash
directions: Prepare squash, onions and peppers.
Let set for 1 hour.
Boil vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Add squash and boil for 5 minutes.
Place in jars.
Seal.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line pan sides with Doritos.
Mix soups together.
Layer crushed Doritos, chicken, jalapenos, soups and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° until cheese and soups are heated.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Add tomato soup, beans, water, celery and peppers.
Add chili powder if desired.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for about 1/2 hour or until celery is tender.
Serve over cooked rice. Serves 4.

title: tunnel-of-fudge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease Bundt pan. Cream butter in large bowl at high speed. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Gradually add sugar; continue creaming at high speed until light and fluffy. By hand, stir in flour, frosting and nuts. Pour batter into greased tube pan. Bake 60 to 65 minutes. Cool 2 hours. Remove from pan.

title: strawberry delite pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, lemon juice and first sugar substitute and chill.

title: apricot jam
directions: Combine dried apricots and water.
Soak 1 hour.
Cook, slowly, until tender.
Cool.
Cut into small pieces.
Add crushed pineapple with juice, sugar and liquid from cherries.
Mix well.
Cook slowly, uncovered, stirring often, until thick and clear.
Add pieces of cherries.
Cook a few minutes longer.
Pour into jars. Seal or cover with melted paraffin.
Makes 8 to 10 cups.

title: seafood hot dish
directions: Crush potato chips and save 1/3 for topping.
Combine other ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and cover with remaining chips.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy potato soup(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; set aside.
Saute onion.
Cook potatoes in water until tender.
Do not drain water.
Stir in salt and milk.
(I add leftover mashed potatoes if I have any, about 1/2 cup.)
Puree.
Heat, but do not boil.
Garnish with crumpled bacon and parsley.

title: cheese cake
directions: Chill 1 can of milk in refrigerator for a couple of hours. Crumble graham crackers, about 30 crackers.
Add oleo and sugar. Mix well.
Use mixture to line pan and save enough for top, 1/2 cup.

title: mexican dip
directions: Place in slow cooker or fondue pot.
Serve warm with Doritos or tortilla chips.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine beans and seasoning mix.
Spread bean mix evenly in 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Layer remaining stuff in order given.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to boil, stirring constantly, then boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over popped corn.
Mix well.
Turn into large roaster or baking pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and break apart.

title: squash souffle
directions: Make medium white sauce with butter, flour and milk.
Add 1/2 cup cheese and squash; season to taste.
Stir in slightly beaten egg yolks; then add sauce.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Last, put in buttered baking dish with buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake 25 or 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: purple cow
directions: With a big spoon, get ice cream out of box and put in blender. Pour grape drink over the ice cream, push one of the buttons until the ice cream and grape drink are mixed real good.
Pour into a tall glass and drink up!

title: homemade rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and butter; cool.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add cooled milk mixture and 3 cups flour; stir until smooth.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Put mixture on a lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic.
Add any additional flour, if necessary.
Place mixture into a buttered bowl and butter top of dough.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk, approximately 1 hour.
When ready, punch down dough.
Let it rest for about 10 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend or mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour in greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Any combination of fruits and nuts may be added.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: snack balls
directions: Place rice and grated cheese in bowl and mix.
Pack a ball of the rice and cheese mixture around each cube of cheese.
Add butter, salt, pepper and mustard to egg before beating.
Dip the rice and cheese balls in egg mixture first, then dip in bread crumbs.
Deep fry for 7 minutes.
Remove and let drain and cool on paper towels.

title: carne guisada
directions: Brown stew meat.
Add oregano, ground comino and diced tomatoes.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add green beans.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Serve over white rice.

title: beet pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, water, sugar and salt.
Bring to boil for 15 minutes.
Add cooked beets; simmer 5 minutes.
Use pickling spices, if desired.

title: lizzies holiday cookies
directions: Cut up fruits, nuts and raisins.
Put all together in a bowl with 1/2 cup flour and mix well to keep fruits from sticking together.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add spices.
Add whiskey, milk and rum.
Add this to fruit and nut mixture.
Mix well.
Add flour and mix well.
Grease cookie sheets and drop by teaspoonful, one at a time.
Bake at 275° for approximately 12 to 15 minutes.
When cooled completely, store in airtight cans.
Will keep for weeks.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, mash and season.
Add sour cream, soup, butter, carrot, onion and add herb seasoning, crumbled.
Spoon into well-greased casserole dish, size 9 x 12-inch.
Spread a few herb seasoning crumbs to top.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add sugar and cocoa and beat by hand until blended.
Add oil, milk, coffee, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed with mixer.
Will be a watery, very thin batter.
Pour into greased and floured 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
When removed from oven, cover with wax paper until cool.
Frost.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and salt. Rub in butter. Add milk. Spread batter evenly in a greased pan.
Pour over batter the cherry and sugar mixture which has been brought to a boil. Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream, ice cream, milk or pudding.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Pour boiling water over poppy seed and let stand until cool. Add remaining ingredients to poppy seed mixture.
Beat for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured angel food or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Do not stand pan upside down to cool.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Bake in Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: bacon-wrapped chestnuts
directions: Wrap bacon around water chestnuts.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour. Mix brown sugar with ketchup.
Pour over chestnuts and bake for 2 hours at 275°.

title: creamy green onion spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve with crackers.

title: chinese chicken pasta salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, soy sauce and seasonings in a large bowl. Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8.

title: easy chili
directions: Saute onion. Brown hamburger. Mix all ingredients together. Season to taste. Simmer for 15 minutes. Serve hot.

title: club chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour.
Add broth, milk and water.
Cook and stir over low heat until thick.
Add salt, rice, chicken and vegetables.
Pour into greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: marinated pea salad
directions: Stir the first 7 ingredients together; boil for 1 minute.
Set aside to cool.
Add remaining ingredients to the cooled mixture; toss lightly.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: wedding punch
directions: Place rhubarb and strawberries in large kettle.
Add the water and sugar.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat to a simmer and cook until rhubarb is soft.
Add strawberries and return to boiling. Remove from heat.
Cover and let sit for 10 to 15 minutes.
Strain (discard pulp) and refrigerate.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat after each one.
Add vanilla.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325° in large loaf pan.

title: bread pudding
directions: Grease baking dish.
Set oven for 350° on middle shelf.
Break 2 eggs in a bowl; beat until bubbly.
Add honey or sugar and vanilla to egg mixture.
Beat.
Add milk slowly.
Continue to beat the mixture until well blended.
Break the bread into 8 small pieces.
Pour egg mixture into baking dish and press bread pieces into mixture.
Let soak a minute or two.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until puffed up and golden brown.
Let cool.
Enjoy!

title: onion baked fillets
directions: Cut fish fillets into serving size portions.
Sprinkle salt. Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and Ranch salad dressing mix.
Dip fish into mixture, then roll in crushed onions.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix together in a large bowl and leave overnight in refrigerator.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Cook the egg yolks, lemon juice and 1/4 cup of cream in a double broiler, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Let the mixture set until it is cold.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Let stand for 24 hours after mixing.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Slice squash and onions.
Cover with cold water and salt.
Let stand for 2 hours; drain.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Prepare broccoli and rice according to package directions. Combine cheese, mayonnaise, soup and egg. Drain broccoli. Work rice and broccoli
in with the soup mixture. Place in buttered dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven and top with crushed crackers and melted butter. Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Boiling water added last thing.
Just fold in water, don't beat.
(Batter will be thin, but don't add anymore flour.).
Cake will be stiff when baked.

title: marbleized mint bark
directions: Melt chocolate chips and set aside.
Melt white chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in candy cane.
Pour onto foil lined cookie sheet.
Drizzle with melted chocolate.
Gently zigzag with a metal spatula through both layers.
Let stand until hard.
Break into pieces.
Store tightly covered.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, salt, celery salt, turmeric and dry mustard in saucepan, bring to a boil and pour over zucchini and onions.
Let
stand
one
hour,
stirring occasionally. Pack in hot sterilized jars and seal.
Oh, so good.

title: microwave yankee potato nachos
directions: Arrange potatoes in a 9-inch pie plate, overlapping slices. Loosely cover and microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes (until tender).

title: pork chop skillet dish
directions: Brown chops in shortening and drain.
On each chop place a slice of onion, green pepper and 1 tablespoon rice in center of ring.
Pour tomatoes around meat.
Distribute celery.
Cover; heat to simmering.
Lower heat.
Cook 1 hour.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients into a 4 cup jar with lid.
Shake well.

title: creole eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant.
Cut crosswise in half inch thick slices, then into quarters.
Cook in boiling salted water 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Drain thoroughly.
Mix in tomatoes and onion.
Add salt, pepper, basil and sugar.
Pour half of mixture into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with half of the cheese.
Repeat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Combine the cheese spread and the Bisquick.
Shape into a roll and roll in the sesame seed.
Chill for 2 hours. Slice 1/4-inch thick slices and place on a lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: overnight salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except whipped cream in a large bowl. Fold in whipped cream last. Place some cherries and pecans on top as garnish, if desired. Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Wash the beans; soak in the quart of lukewarm water overnight or 6 to 8 hours. Put beans in a saucepan. Add salt, mustard, molasses and 3 cups of the boiling water. Cook until beans reach boiling point, then boil for 3 minutes. Pour into a casserole. Spread bacon on top. Cover and bake at 300° for 4 hours, then add remaining 2 cups water and bake 2 hours more. Uncover the last 1/2 hour of baking to brown the top.

title: chocolate drops
directions: Melt semi-sweet chocolate in microwave.
Keep it stirred, then when melted add nuts and peanut butter.
Stir well.
Drop onto waxed paper on a cookie sheet.
Put in freezer, then remove into a bowl with a lid.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together, then form into loaf shape.
Place in rectangular bread pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Pour off fat and serve.
Meat loaf can be topped with additional catsup and/or bacon.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Brown meat in Dutch oven.
Drain off fat.
Stir in water, tomatoes, carrots, mushrooms, barley, celery, onions, garlic and oregano.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until barley and vegetables are tender.
Season to taste.
Stir in Velveeta until melted.
Garnish as desired.
Makes six 1 cup servings.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Combine brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt together in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes (stir consistently).
After bringing to a hard boil, take off heat and stir in the baking soda.
Pour over popcorn that has been placed in a roasting pan or large baking pan.
Mix tighter until will coated.
Bake at 250 degrees for 1 hour stirring every 15 minutes. Cool before storing.
Store in air tight container.

title: apple puff
directions: Beat egg and add sugar.
Sift dry ingredients and fold into eggs.
Add apples, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 8-inch pie dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bring to boil over medium heat. Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Grill chops over coals for 30 minutes, or until half done.
Brush with sauce.
Grill for 15 to 30 minutes more.

title: clam chowder, minced
directions: Cook with water, boil 1/2 hour.
Mash cooked veggies; add milk, clam juice and clams; thicken with flour mixed in water.
Simmer 15 minutes on low heat, top with dry parsley.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, mix together sugar, flour, oleo, baking powder and milk.
Let stand.

title: aztec casserole
directions: Brown meat. Add chili powder, onion, bell pepper, jalapenos and corn. Layer Doritos, sliced Velveeta cheese and meat mixture; end with Doritos and cheese on top. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: frozen orange jello
directions: Put jello in bowl.
Add 1 cup hot water, sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add juice and pineapple.
Put cheese in another bowl. Add second cup of hot water, a little at a time, to cheese until all is used up and cheese is smooth.
Mix with jello mixture and put into 8 or 9-inch square dish.
After it is set, sprinkle with nuts.

title: fruit-nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add cream cheese and whip with mixer.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.
Serve on lettuce with mayonnaise or just plain.

title: chocolate refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix powdered sugar, margarine and egg.
Mix in flour, cocoa and salt.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour, but no more than six weeks.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in bread pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: popsicles
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and Kool-Aid in boiling water; add cold water. Pour into paper cups and place in a freezer.
When mushy, put in a plastic spoon or stick.
When frozen, peel off paper and eat. May use molds.

title: steak diane
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan.
Add mushrooms, onion, garlic powder, salt, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook and stir until mushrooms are tender.
Add parsley;
keep sauce warm.

title: beef salad
directions: In saucepan, mix first 7 ingredients.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Cool.
Toss with beef and onion.
Chill.
Drain, reserving marinade.
Place greens in a large bowl.
Top with beef and onions. Combine sour cream with reserved marinade.
Toss with greens and beef.

title: ginger beef
directions: Slice beef lengthwise into 1 1/2-inch strips.
Cut strips crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.
Toss beef, cornstarch, 1 tablespoon oil, salt, sugar, white pepper and 1 tablespoon soy sauce in a plastic bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Cut green onions diagonally into 1-inch pieces.
Heat wok until very hot.
Add 2 tablespoons oil.
Rotate to coat sides.
Add beef, ginger and garlic.
Stir-fry for 3 minutes or until beef is brown. Add green onions and 2 tablespoons soy sauce.
Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Serve over steamed white rice.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients and put into greased bread pans.
Makes 2 loaves.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Wash and scrape carrots.
Cut or slice 1/4 inch thick.
Cook in boiling salted water; drain.
Cool.
Combine carrots with onion rings and green pepper in large bowl.
Combine soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Bring to a good boil; stir.
Pour hot mixture over vegetables.
Cool.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and blend with sour cream.

title: chili
directions: Brown onion and beef in saucepan.
Add beans, tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili powder, salt, bay leaf, paprika and cayenne pepper. Cover; let simmer for 1 1/2 hours on low heat.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients and set aside.
In mixer, blend shortening, sugar and eggs (one egg at a time); beat well.
Add zucchini and vanilla and milk (alternately with dry ingredients). Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover with glaze.

title: spanish salad
directions: Drain beans well.
Add dressing; let set for 2 hours (better overnight).
Combine head of lettuce, tomato, onion and cheese. Toss salad.
Last, add corn chips, crumbled well.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces.
Place all ingredients in cooker and close securely.
Cook 20 minutes at 15 pounds pressure.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain fruits.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate. Serves approximately 8.

title: aunt grace's chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together the 3 cans of soup and mayo in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place raw chicken breasts, cut in half, or long strips into soup mixture.
Press down to cover with sauce. Place cheese slices on top.
Then sprinkle with crumb dressing mix and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until chicken is done and top is brown.

title: baked meatballs
directions: Mix onion soup and water; simmer 5 minutes.
Pour 2 tablespoons tomato sauce into a cup.
Add garlic salt, thyme, pepper, oregano and parsley; mix well.
Add herb mixture to ground beef and mix until blended.
Add remaining tomato sauce to onion soup mixture. Shape meat into balls into a 2-quart casserole.
Pour soup mixture over meatballs.
Bake, covered, at 350° for about 45 minutes. Uncover, bake until browned.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Last three ingredients, mix over heat until melted.
Pour over first three ingredients.
Mix well, then pack into greased tube pan.
Let set overnight.
Run knife around edges of pan; turn cake onto plate and cut.
Tastes like popcorn balls.

title: fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, peel and dice apples, add oranges, fruit cocktail, pineapple and bananas. Quarter cherries and add for color and about 3/4 cup of coconut. Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil. This sauce is especially good for chicken and ribs cooked on the grill.

title: cherry-o cream cheese pie
directions: In medium size bowl beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Gradually add sweetened condensed milk and stir until well blended.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into pie crust and cover with chilled cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate 2 - 3 hours before serving.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cook cauliflower in boiling water for 2 minutes.
Combine all ingredients; chill before serving.

title: polish chop suey
directions: Brown meat, drain off fat.
Add soup, water, French onion soup, celery; cook all together until meat is done.
Cook 10 minutes only the noodles.
Layer sauerkraut, noodles and meat sauce until all mixtures are used up.
First bake at 350° for 1 hour, then at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: hens reggae
directions: Spray a 3-quart casserole well with a nonstick spray.
Whisk broth and soup until smooth.
Stir in rice and onion and mix well. Remove fatty pads and skin, if desired.
Arrange hens, cut side down on top of rice mixture.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spray a sheet of tinfoil and cover the casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon squares
directions: Sift together 2 cups flour and the powdered sugar.
Cut into butter until mixture clings together.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove and cool.

title: caramel pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until light and fluffy.
Add half of the sugar (3/4 cup), flour, butter, salt and milk.
Mix well and heat in top of double boiler until lukewarm, stirring occasionally.
While mixture is heating, caramelize remainder of sugar, stirring frequently.
When sugar is caramelized and boiling rapidly, pour in the egg mixture, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour cooled mixture into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: apple-raisin dressing
directions: Combine apples, celery, sugar, butter and water in saucepan. Bring to boil. Cover and cook 5 minutes. Combine bread and seasonings. Combine chicken broth and egg; add to bread. Add hot apple mixture; toss with fork to mix. Turn into buttered 1 1/2 quart loaf pan or casserole. Bake, uncovered, in moderate oven (350°) for 35 minutes (10 to 15 minutes longer gives a crisper top). Serves 6.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Heat oven
to
Lightly
grease pie pan; sprinkle bacon bits and
cheese
on bottom of pan.
Pour egg mixture on top. Bake until	golden brown, or a knife comes out clean, 50 or 60 minutes.
Let
stand
for
minutes.
Refrigerate any leftover. (I mix the eggs in a blender.)

title: cheese chili cubes
directions: In a large mixer bowl beat eggs with electric mixer until light, 4 to 5 minutes.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to eggs and mix well.
Fold in Jack cheese, cottage cheese and chilies.
Turn into greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes.
Cut in small squares.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen appetizers.

title: upside-down raisin carrot cake
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 1/2 cup syrup.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine in 10-inch ovenproof skillet.
Blend in brown sugar and arrange pineapple over sugar mixture and top with 1/2 cup raisins. Beat remaining 1/4 cup margarine with sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and carrots.
Combine dry ingredients.
Beat 1/3 dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Beat in half reserved syrup until blended.
Repeat, ending with dry ingredients.
Fold in remaining 1/2 cup raisins.
Pour batter over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before inverting on a serving plate.

title: sweet and sour cabbage(german style)
directions: In a large skillet saute cabbage and apples in butter for 6 to 8 minutes until cabbage is tender-crisp.
With spoon stir in vinegar, sugar and salt.
Cook 2 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: bacon hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cut each slice of bread into 3 pieces.
Using the soup as is, spread on each piece of bread.
Roll the bacon over the bread. Put all small rolls on cookie sheet.
Freeze.
After frozen, store in bags until ready to use.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, until browned.

title: cheese-garlic biscuits(like red lobsters)
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms; beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix margarine and garlic powder; brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Serve warm. Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: banana pudding dessert
directions: Combine crushed pineapple with prepared pudding.
Place about half of vanilla wafers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Spread half of pudding mix on top.
Cover with sliced bananas. Add another layer of vanilla wafers, then remaining pudding mix. Cover and chill about 5 hours.
Before serving, spread top with whipped topping.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: grilled hamburgers
directions: Sprinkle Crazy Dave's Salt and Spice on hamburger meat and prepare into patties.
Grill.

title: apricot delite salad
directions: In a saucepan, put apricot Jell-O (dry) with crushed pineapple (with juice).
Heat until boiling.
Take off stove and add cream cheese, which has been cut into small pieces.
Stir until cream cheese is melted.
Add baby food and put into refrigerator until congealed a little.
Then add Cool Whip and refrigerate until firm.
May be decorated with nuts and Mandarin oranges.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unwrap caramels and melt on low heat with margarine and evaporated milk.
While those are melting, make cake mix as directed on box.
Pour 1/2 of cake mixture into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven, pour melted caramel mixture over, then sprinkle on chocolate chips.
Pour remaining cake batter on top; spread to cover.
Bake for another 20 minutes.

title: weight watchers spicy beef and vegetable stir-fry
directions: In a small bowl, combine the beef broth, soy sauce, cornstarch and mustard and stir until the cornstarch is dissolved.
Set aside.
Cut the broccoli into bite-size pieces.

title: mom's tater tot casserole
directions: Fry chicken legs (any parts will do, but legs look better). Place in clean canning jars.
Seal by placing in a canner.
As needed open and fry just enough to get that crispy taste back. Serve.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour three 8-inch layer pans. Sift together flour and spices. In mixing bowl, combine oil and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat. Add hot water, then fold in flour mixture. Stir in potatoes, nuts and vanilla. Combine thoroughly. Pour batter into pans and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese banana pudding
directions: Cream
the
cheese;
add
Eagle Brand milk.
Add 2 cups milk. Add vanilla pudding mix; beat until thickens.
Add Cool Whip. Layer wafers, bananas
and pudding.
Top with wafers or Cool Whip.

title: pepper relish
directions: Quarter peppers and onions and chop finely in food processor. Drain well.
In large pot cover onions and pepper with boiling water.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Drain and press remaining water out. Make syrup with vinegar, sugar and salt.
Add pepper and onion mixture to syrup.
Cook for 20 minutes at slow boil, stirring occasionally.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Fill smalll baking cups less than 1/2 full.
Drop tablespoon of cream cheese mixture in the middle.
Do not stir!!!
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes and cool.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients, except nuts and parsley.
After blending, add nuts and place in refrigerator for 2 days.
Form into balls and roll in parsley.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Mix the jello and boiling water.
Add raspberries, applesauce and lemon juice.
After salad is set, frost with topping of Marshmallow Creme mixed well with cream cheese.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine milk, eggs and sugar.
Fill baking dish with bread cubes and pour mixture over it.
Bake at 350 degrees until firm (appx 45 minutes).

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix soups and milk.
Put cooked rice in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish. Add chicken pieces.
Pour soup liquids over and lightly mix. Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over all. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: egg rolls
directions: Mix all the ingredients in large bowl.
Wrap mixture in wrappers according to package directions.
You can substitute ground pork, chopped shrimp or ground chicken instead of ground turkey.
Deep fry in oil until they float to top or golden brown.

title: chaffee fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Melt bakers chocolate in the water. Combine sugar, Mazola and egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Combine liquid, dry and chocolate mixtures.
Bake for 1 hour.
In a double boiler, melt chocolate bits and butter.
Spread over cake.

title: salisbury steak for two
directions: In a bowl, combine the egg, bread and onion.
Crumble beef over mixture and mix well.
Shape into two patties.
In a nonstick skillet over medium heat, brown patties on both sides in oil. Drain.
Combine the soup, water, mushrooms and pepper.
Pour over patties.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until meat is no longer pink.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix
all
ingredients.	Store in an airtight container. Add 2 to 3 teaspoons to 1 cup hot water.

title: barbara's lemon meringue pie
directions: Beat egg yolks well, stir in lemon juice until well blended. Stir egg mixture into milk, blend well.
Pour into pie plate. Beat egg whites, add cream of tartar, and sugar, beat until stiff. Pour on pie.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until golden brown. Serves 6.

title: alabama venison chili
directions: Brown meat; add all ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until desired thickness.
Serve with crackers or cornbread.

title: sloppy jacques
directions: Brown meat.
Drain and stir in flour, then soup.
Simmer 2 minutes until thick and hot.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and beat in the sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat briskly.
Then blend cocoa and water together.
Add the cocoa mixture, flour and nuts and mix all. Pour in a buttered 9 x 9-inch square baking pan and bake for 35 minutes at 325°.
When cold, cut into squares.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the oleo, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Add vanilla; beat well. Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition. Stir in flour. Spoon mixture into greased 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: marinated carrot salad
directions: Steam sliced carrots until tender; cool.
Mix all other ingredients well.
Place carrots in a bowl.
Pour mixture over carrots.
Cover.
Marinate 24 hours.
Keeps in refrigerator up to 1 month.

title: venetian style liver
directions: Coat liver with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Set aside. Saute onions in oil in a large skillet until tender.
Add liver and saute 1 to 2 minutes on each side or until browned (should be slightly pink inside).
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Take a packet of crackers and 1 stick of butter; blend in blender to crumb.
Spread this over casserole and put back in oven to brown slightly.

title: whole wheat pumpkin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine sugar, pumpkin, eggs, oil and water.
Beat at low speed for 1 minute.
Sift together both flours and next 6 ingredients.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Spoon into lightly greased muffin pans (2 1/2-inch diameter).
Bake for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: finnish coffee bread
directions: Combine scalded milk, sugar and butter in a large bowl; cool to lukewarm.
Add salt, eggs, cardamom, yeast dissolved in water and 5 cups flour.
Stir well.
Add more flour in 1/2 cup increments until dough forms a ball.
Turn out onto floured board. Knead well, adding additional flour as necessary, until dough is dull, elastic and not sticky (approximately 10 minutes).
Coat a large heat-resistant bowl with vegetable oil.
Place kneaded dough in bowl and turn to coat with oil.
Cover with a clean damp dishtowel (not terrycloth) or plastic wrap.

title: aunt minnie's jello divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and cook to hard ball (252°), stirring occasionally.
Do not overcook.
Combine egg whites and gelatin.
Beat until mixture forms peaks.
Pour hot syrup in thin stream into egg whites and beat until candy loses gloss and holds shape.
Fold in nuts and/or coconut if desired.
If using pan, use 9-inch square, greased or drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.

title: drunk ham
directions: Combine all ingredients except bay leaves, ham and white wine.
Place bay leaves in bottom of pan.
Place ham on top of bay leaves.
Spread paste over ham.
Add white wine in bottom of pan. Bake at 300 to 325° for 20 minutes per pound of ham, basting frequently.

title: terrific turkey lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray bottom of large skillet with Pam. Crumble ground turkey into pan; add onion.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat 5 to 7 minutes or until turkey is lightly browned.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Cook over low heat 15 minutes. Reserve 1 cup meat sauce.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Put sweet milk, sugar and Crisco in boiler.
Place over heat and let it come to a good boil.
Remove from heat; let cool until it is just barely warm.
Add 1 quart of the flour and beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Add yeast, that has been dissolved in a small amount of warm water.
Set aside until double in bulk, then add the other quart of flour.
Put in refrigerator.
