Keep dough pushed down until chilled.

title: beet jello salad
directions: Mix last 2 ingredients together.
Make jello; add beets and pineapple and vinegar.
Pour into square dish.
Let set until hardened.
Cover with a mixture of cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Cut in squares.
(I cut in squares and then add a spoonful on each square.)

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add salad oil and beaten eggs. Combine soda, cream of tartar, salt and flour.
Add to first mixture.
Roll cooled dough into balls (walnut size).
Dip in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet and crisscross to flatten with a fork or potato masher.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
They freeze well.

title: stuffed cabbage(low in cholesterol and makes about 12.)
directions: Cut out cabbage core and steam in hot water, core side down. Peel leaves to dry.
Mix hamburg, rice, 1/2 can tomato soup, garlic, onion, salt and pepper.
Roll mixture in cabbage leaf, stem side outside.
Put 1/2 can tomato soup in crock-pot; layer with cabbage leaves, then cabbage rolls.
Add 2 cans tomato soup.
Cook 6 hours.

title: belgian bread pudding with lemon sauce
directions: Soak crumbs in milk, add sugar, butter, beaten eggs and flavorings.
Mix.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Bake 350 for 40 minutes or until solid.

title: sauteed vegetables
directions: In frypan saute vegetables except the tomatoes in oil.
When they become soft, add butter, tomatoes and salt and pepper.
Saute a little longer and serve.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Combine 2 cups sugar, oil and eggs; beat well.
Combine flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add this to sugar mixture with buttermilk.
Stir in nuts.
Pour the batter into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
While cake is cooking, combine 1 cup sugar, water and butter.
Bring to boil for 5 minutes.
Pour this mixture, while still hot, over cake.

title: cheddar nut bread
directions: Combine, egg, Carnation milk, water, salt, baking mix, cheese and nuts.
Mix vigorously 30 seconds or until blended.
Spoon into buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake
in moderate oven at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: sausage cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Brown sausage with onion and drain. Combine meal, eggs, corn, milk and oil.
Pour half of mixture into iron skillet.
Sprinkle sausage mix and cheese.
Pour rest of batter on top.
Bake 30 or 40 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for 1 cup of chopped pecans.
Form into ball and roll in remaining pecans.

title: spiced sweet potato fries
directions: In a large bowl, combine oil with salt, cinnamon and cayenne. Stir in sweet potatoes until each piece is well coated. Arrange sweet potatoes in a single layer on a baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Turn potatoes; bake until lightly browned, about 10 minutes. Remove from oven; place on serving platter.

title: chocolate reese's cups
directions: Mix sugar, butter and peanut butter with a mixer until well blended.
Shape into balls and chill.
Melt chocolate chips, butter and paraffin.
Dip the chilled balls with toothpicks into chocolate mixture.
Yields 50.

title: sausage squares
directions: Cook sausage until done. Drain off the excess liquid and crumble up. Stir in cream cheese until mixed well. Place 1 package crescent rolls in bottom of baking dish. Spoon and spread sausage and cream cheese mixture over rolls. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top. Cover with package of crescent rolls. Bake at 350° until done (brown). Serve warm - hot.

title: potato lasagna
directions: Melt butter and saute onion until tender; set aside.
In boiling salted water, cook lasagna noodles for 4 minutes.
Add cold water to make warm.
Set aside.

title: pralines
directions: Mix sugar, milk, water and Karo.
Cook to a hard boil. Set aside.
Add oleo, vanilla and nuts.

title: souvlakia(greek skewered steak)
directions: Cube meat into 1-inch pieces. Wash and prepare vegetables. Skewer each one in order:
green pepper, mushroom stem, onion, meat, tomato and continue until skewer is 3/4 full.
Cap with mushroom.
Lay in a flat pan and sprinkle with the rest of the ingredients.
Broil 5 minutes on one side. Turn and broil 4 minutes on the other side.
Can serve on rice pilaf.

title: beef and macaroni casserole]
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Add salt, pepper, mushroom soup, tomato sauce and water.
Cook macaroni in boiling water until tender.

title: pineapple cream cheese pie
directions: Drain the pineapple. Combine cream cheese and milk, then add the Key lime juice; blend well. Stir in pineapple. Pour into shell and chill 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and make into loaf.
Butter bottom of pan lightly.
Add catsup to top of loaf.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour or done.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Saute ham, onion and celery in oil until onion is tender in medium saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients except rice; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; cut in half lengthwise.
Combine salt, vinegar and water; heat to boiling.
Pack cucumbers into clean jars.
Add 2 sprigs dill weed and 4 peppercorns to each jar.
Pour vinegar solution over cucumbers to within 1/2-inch of top.
Immediately adjust covers if jar manufacturer directs.
(Most do not need adjustment.) Process 10 minutes in boiling bath.
Makes 6 to 7 pints.

title: banana temptations
directions: Peel bananas and cut in half.
Then slice lengthwise.
Melt butter in skillet on low heat.
Add brown sugar and stir until melted.
Add bananas or plantains.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover and cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Turn over and cook 2 to 3 minutes more.
Serve warm!

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each one.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Add sifted flour and salt; mix well.
Bake in a well-greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Start in a cold oven.

title: mexican hominy
directions: Place hominy in baking dish; add chili which has been heated. Add chopped onions, then cheese.
Top with chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve lime Jell-O as directed on box.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan and let set until hard.
Dissolve lemon Jell-O with 1 cup of boiling water.
When warm, but not hot, mix in cream cheese and add the sugar, pineapple and nuts.
Mix well.
Score the already hardened layer of lime Jell-O with a fork.
Pour the lemon mixture onto it and let it harden in the refrigerator.
Mix the strawberry Jell-O as directed on box.
When slightly cool, pour over lemon layer and return it to the refrigerator.
When completely set, serve with a teaspoon of mayonnaise.

title: strawberry salad with pretzel crust
directions: Melt butter and mix with pretzels, sugar and pecans.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Beat cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar together and spread over cooled crust.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Dissolve Jell-O in water, add frozen strawberries and stir until Jell-O begins to thicken.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or more.

title: sweet 'n sour beans
directions: Simmer all but beans in skillet for 10 minutes.
Add beans; bake in large casserole for 2 hours at 325°, covered.
Serves 8.

title: 6-week bran muffins
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Beat eggs (good) and add to oil and buttermilk.
Add to all dry ingredients and mix well.
Store in refrigerator overnight before the first baking.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix cake mix, flour and jello (dry) add oil, nectar and eggs, one at a time.
Mix.
Add
lemon
extract.	Grease	and flour tube pan or Bundt pan
well.
Bake
at
325° for 1 hour. Remove from pan while
slightly
warm
and
dribble icing over cake.

title: pickle pies
directions: You just have to roll it, and then you have to smash it.
Then you put some stuff in it and
then you cook it.
You put it on the stove and cook it.
Then you take it off and freeze it and then make it warm.
Then you eat it.
That's all.

title: chocolate oatmeal peanut butter no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, milk and cocoa in medium-sized saucepan.
Heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Let boil 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cool for 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper, pressing lightly.
Cool until hardened.
Makes 3 1/2 to 4 dozen if doubled.

title: maple syrup dumplings
directions: Mix the syrup with the water.
Bring to a boil.
Mix the dry ingredients and cut in the fat (as in making pie dough).
Add the milk and mix.
Drop by teaspoons in the hot syrup. Cover and boil slowly, without lifting the cover, for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple chicken wings
directions: Dip chicken wings in eggs (beaten);
coat
with
flour. Fry in	oil
15 to 20 minutes.	Lay chicken wings
in
a
pan neatly. Combine the first 6 ingredients in a bowl
to
make a sauce;
pour sauce over chicken wings.
Bake at	350°
for
30 minutes.	 Turn chicken wings over before
removing
from
the oven.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. With electric mixer, beat butter and 1/2 c. powdered sugar. Add vanilla. Combine flour, salt and nuts; stir into sugar mixture. Roll dough into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 15 minutes until lightly brown. While hot, roll in reserved powdered sugar (1-1/2 cups). Cool on a rack, and then roll again in powdered sugar to coat. Cinnamon may also be added to the coating. Makes at least 4 dozen cookies.

title: oven baked eggs
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Beat eggs, sour cream, milk and salt.
Stir in onion.
Pour in baking dish (9 x 13 x 2-inch).
Bake until eggs are set, but still moist (about 35 minutes).

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars well.
Add well-beaten eggs and vanilla and beat well.
Add sifted flour, soda, oats and nutmeats. Form into rolls and wrap in wax paper.
Put in refrigerator until thoroughly chilled.
Cut very thin and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 10 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Combine cake mix, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and butter.
Spread half of batter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°. Meanwhile, melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Pour chocolate chips over baked dough.
Spread with caramel mixture, then 1 cup of nuts.
Spoon remaining cake batter over layer of chocolate, caramels and nuts.
Sprinkle remaining nuts on top. Bake 20 minutes.
Cool, then cut in squares.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Put the dry sugar in a skillet over high heat.
Stir constantly until it browns lightly.
Remove from heat, let cool a few minutes, add the other ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until it will form a soft all when dropped into cold water. Remove from heat, add 1 Tablespoon vanilla and beat until its cool, and thick enough to spread on cake.

title: potato mix-up
directions: Boil potatoes until soft enough to pierce easily with a fork; drain.
Cook broccoli per package directions.
Mash potatoes until chunky with spoon or hand masher.
Mix all ingredients together. Put mixture into microwave or oven until cheese melts.

title: fig preserve cake
directions: Cream butter and add sugar.
Sift flour into sugar box (without jarring, remove 2 tablespoons of flour).
Alternate addition of flour with eggs.
Add vanilla, fig preserves and pecans.
Pour cake batter in greased and floured tube pan.
Place cake in preheated oven.
Bake 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: robbie's caramel apples(microwave)
directions: You will need wooden sticks.

title: boston baked beans
directions: In
mixing
bowl
mix catsup, sugar, syrup and mustard. Brown small
onion,
chopped,
in little oleo.
Mix onion with beans. In baking dish put a layer of beans and onion mixture, then a layer
of
sauce
mixture, rest of beans, then rest of sauce mixture.
Cover
top
with
strips
of
bacon.
Cook for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325° or 350°.

title: sugar-free fruit dessert
directions: Mix undrained fruit cocktail, pineapple and sliced bananas together.
Stir in instant pudding until well blended.
Store in refrigerator.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Grease a 6 x 12-inch dish; line with unbroken crackers, both on sides and on bottom.
Slice a layer of bananas on bottom.
Mix pudding and milk; mix with whipped topping.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over bananas.
Top with crackers, bananas and remaining pudding mixture.
Cover with crackers; top with whipped topping.
Chill.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients.
Knead dough on floured board.
May either pinch off and roll in hand (as making biscuits) or roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Place all of the ingredients into a 4 or 5-quart ice cream freezer.
Then fill with milk to the fill line.
You can add malt powder (optional).

title: sue's punch
directions: Slowly add cranberry juice to sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Mix all ingredients and chill before serving.
Add ice ring just before you serve.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Spread potatoes evenly over bottom of well oiled casserole. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Break corned beef in fairly large pieces.
Spread evenly over the potatoes in layers.
Combine soup and water.
Blend thoroughly.
Place in small saucepan over low heat.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Pour over meat and potato mixture and cover.
Bake in moderate oven, about 325°, for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.
Serve hot.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Separate the stalks from bunch of celery.
Wash well and dry thoroughly.
Cream the cheese, adding a little milk or orange juice until creamy consistency.
Stir in nuts.
Fill each celery stalk with mixture.
Refrigerate.
(If you wish, you can put the stalks back together, tie, chill and then slice into pinwheels.)

title: pecan puffs
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Gradually add sugar, beating constantly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° until done.

title: golden sweet potato boats
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash sweet potatoes.
Bake one hour until done.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Carefully scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact.
In bowl, beat pulp, evaporated milk, margarine, vanilla and salt until fluffy.
Fold in bananas and pecan pieces.
Stuff shells with mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° until heated through.
Makes 8 servings.

title: preserved watermelon rind
directions: Peel thin green rind from melon and remove the soft pink meat. Cut remaining pieces in 2-inch cubes; cover with water and cook until tender, then drain.
Combine the sugar, vinegar and 1/2 cup water in a large covered kettle.
Boil over a moderate flame 10 minutes.
Add cloves in a spice bag and simmer for 1 hour.
Add melon cubes and simmer gently for 1 1/2 hours, or until the melon is transparent.
Put the rind in sterilized pint jars.
Cover with hot syrup and seal.

title: easy casserole
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper. Add chopped onion and spread into bottom of 8 x 12 pan. Add drained beans evenly over meat. Spread diluted soup over beans. Top with Tater Tots. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook and stir onion in 1 Tbsp. butter in large skillet on medium heat until tender.
Add rice, soup, broccoli, and Cheese Whiz.
Mix lightly.
Spoon into 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Toss remaining 1 Tbsp. of butter, melted and bread cubes, sprinkling over casserole.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: substitute for sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine powdered milk and water.
Stir until smooth. Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Add 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir and cool.

title: mission trail chocolate pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees. Beat eggs in large bowl using electric mixer on medium speed for 15 seconds. Add syrup, vanilla, flour and brown sugar and beat for 15 more seconds. Stir in chocolate chips and pecan halves with a large spoon. Pour pecan mixture into frozen pie crust. Bake on center oven rack for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean. Serves 10.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together until creamy.
Add milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour into freezer.
This makes 1 gallon of nice textured ice cream.
(If milk does not fill freezer up to line for freezing, add enough water to fill and stir.)

title: shrimp creole
directions: Heat oil in a large, heavy pot.
Stir in flour and make a medium brown roux.
Add onions, celery, bell pepper and green onions; saute until limp.
Add garlic, tomato sauce, tomatoes, bay leaves, black pepper, thyme, basil, salt and cayenne.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add Worcestershire sauce; simmer for about 20 minutes. This dish improves upon resting several hours.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mix alternately with milk.
Spread batter in bottom of well-greased 9-inch square pan.
Combine sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Core tomatoes, cut into 3/4-inch slices.
Drain lightly on paper towel.
Season with pinch of salt.
Using 3 dishes, into one dish put flour.
In a second dish, lightly beaten eggs.
In a third dish, mix cornmeal, Parmesan, red pepper, salt and black pepper.
Heat oven to 200°.
Coat tomato slice with flour; dip into egg.
Coat with cornmeal mixture.
Heat 3 tablespoons of oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes per side.
Add more oil as needed to avoid sticking.
Place fried tomatoes on paper towel-lined baking sheet.
Keep warm
in a 200° oven until ready to serve.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and mix with salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze cabbage and add carrots and pepper.

title: cherry bounce
directions: Make in summertime end of June when sweet cherries are in season.
Put cherries in large glass jar; add hard candy and whiskey.
Let set in a cool dark place until Christmas.
Strain and put back into whiskey bottles.
Can use over ice or mix a shot of Cherry Bounce with 7-Up.
Very good.

title: tortillas
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder and shortening together.
Pour small amount of warm water into flour.
Knead flour together. Only add enough water to where the flour stays together and forms a ball.
Preheat wrought iron skillet or some form of baking utensil on top of the stove.
Make small, round balls; roll out with rolling pin into a circle.
Cook in wrought iron skillet at a medium to high flame.
Cook on both sides.
Flip tortillas with tongs or fork.
Serves 6 to 8 persons.

title: crescent roll chicken
directions: Mix cheese (1 cup), soup and milk.
Pour half the mixture into casserole dish.
Separate rolls and place cut up chicken in rolls and roll up, tucking in edges.
Place into casserole dish, then spoon other half of mixture over rolls.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with all ingredients except use only 1/2 of the nuts in the mixture.
Roll the cheese ball in the remaining nuts.

title: sour beet tire shreds
directions: Scrub and peel raw beets; shred.
Put all ingredients, except salt and pepper, in heavy saucepan.
Cover and cook over medium heat about 10 minutes, or until beets are tender but still crisp. Stir twice with fork during cooking.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Makes 4 servings .

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Quarter small potatoes (as many as desired).
Deep fry until tender; drain well.
Put on cookie sheet; sprinkle with grated American cheese and bacon bits.
Bake until cheese is melted at 350°.
Serve with Ranch dressing.

title: hanky panks
directions: Cook meat, drain and add other ingredients.
Cook until sausage is cooked and cheese is melted.
Spread on party breads until ready to use.
Broil until spread starts to brown and bubble.
Serve hot.

title: popover shells
directions: Chill custard cups 2 hours.
Sift flour and salt together. Mix eggs, milk and butter.
Add to flour mixture.
Fill cold cups 1/2 full.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 400°.
Start in cold oven.

title: pineapple carrot bread
directions: Beat together eggs, oil, butter, sugar and vanilla until foamy.
Stir in carrots and pineapple.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir until just mixed.
Pour into two buttered and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: chicken of the gods
directions: Cut ham julienne 1/4 inch thick; wrap breast over ham.
Dip in whipped egg and roll in bread crumbs.
Sprinkle with butter.
Place in pan and cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serve with chicken fricassee sauce.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine apple and lemon juice and set aside.
Bring to a boil remaining ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Strain.
Add to apple and lemon juice.
Heat and serve.

title: spinach salad
directions: Put all ingredients in blender until smooth. Refrigerate until well chilled.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a Bundt cake pan. Combine all ingredients; beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix and marinate overnight.
Serve with slotted spoon.

title: fresh peach pie(no-bake)
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook to a boiling point and liquid mixture is clear.
Add peach jello; stir until dissolved. Cool.
Slice peaches.
Mix with glaze and place into baked pie crust.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: winter squash with sweet spices
directions: Cut off squash, peel, remove seeds and strings.
Cut flesh into 1-inch pieces.
Combine garlic, pepper, cinnamon, ginger, sugar, oil and water in a large skillet.
Bring to a simmer.
Add squash; stir until coated.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bring to a boil. Cover and cook over low heat, occasionally stirring gently, until squash is tender, 30 minutes.
Remove garlic, chop and return to pan.
If sauce is too thin, uncover and cook 2 to 3 minutes longer or until it thickens.
Taste and adjust seasonings.
Serve hot. Serves 3 to 4 servings.

title: berry good jello dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Stir in frozen berries.
Chill until slightly set; fold in whipped cream.

title: homemade apple dumplings
directions: Combine 1 c. sugar, spices and 2 c. water.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add butter.
Remove from heat and let sit.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Combine all of the above in large pot and bring to boil. Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: soy sauce chicken
directions: Place chicken in a greased casserole dish.
Mix sour cream, soy sauce and pepper.
Spread over chicken.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Add enough turkey broth to keep moist after baking.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Sprinkle both sides of brisket with onion, celery and garlic salts.
Place in a glass baking dish and pour bottle of liquid smoke on top.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt margarine in loaf pan.
Pour remaining ingredients over melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or when toothpick comes out clean.

title: dawn's garlic breadsticks
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl.
Add honey and garlic powder and mix well.
Gradually add flour, beating until smooth. Knead 3/4 to 1 cup additional flour into the dough until smooth and elastic (about 10 minutes).
Divide mixture into 4 dozen equal parts.
Shape each into an 8-inch long rope.
Place on greased baking sheet (not Teflon).
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle lightly with coarse salt.
Let rise in
warm place, free from drafts 30 minutes or until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden.
Transfer to cake rack and brush with melted butter (add garlic powder to butter to taste for a more garlic intensity).

title: chicken and cheese enchiladas
directions: Fry tortillas in vegetable oil for about a minute on each side.
Warm enchilada sauce in a pan.
Slightly grease a casserole dish with butter or shortening.
Lay a tortilla in the casserole dish.
Spoon enchilada sauce on the tortilla.
Then sprinkle on some chicken, cheese and olives.
Roll up tortilla and place, seam side down, in the casserole dish.
Repeat for each tortilla.
Pour remaining sauce, cheese and olives over enchiladas.
Cook, uncovered, for about 25 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas cranberry pudding
directions: Cream the butter and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together and add to the creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in the cranberries and pecans.
Turn into a greased 6-cup Pyrex bowl or mold and cover with foil.
Press foil tightly around edge and secure with string.
Place mold on a rack in a kettle and pour enough water into kettle to come halfway up on mold.
Bring water to a boil and cover tightly.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Steam for 2 hours.
Let stand for 10 minutes, then unmold.
Serve with Eggnog Dessert Sauce.
Pudding may be refrigerated for several days or cooled, wrapped and frozen for several months.
Thaw in refrigerator, if frozen, then wrap in foil.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: orange and spice tea
directions: In a saucepan combine water, cinnamon and cloves.
Bring to boiling; remove from heat.
Add tea bags; let stand 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Stir in orange juice and brown sugar; heat mixture through. Pour mixture through a wire strainer into 4 mugs or cups.
If desired, serve with orange slice quarters.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: creamy chicken rice
directions: Combine soup and water; whisk together.
Bring to a boil. Take off heat; add rice.
Let stand 10 minutes; serve.
Can be made over campfire.

title: ham casserole(leftover cooked ham)
directions: Make cream sauce with margarine, flour and milk; stir in salad dressing and remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: berry cobbler
directions: Combine flour, 1 2/3 cups sugar, baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Add milk and 3/4 teaspoon melted butter.
Stir until smooth. Spread batter over bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam (nonstick vegetable spray).
Sprinkle berries over top.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Put margarine, oil and water in saucepan and bring to a boil. Let cool.
Add sugar, flour and cocoa.
Mix. Add dry ingredients to wet; cool mixture.
Pour onto 18 x 11-inch cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Fudge Frosting recommended.

title: deep dish sugarless apple pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, liquid sweetener, salt, lemon rind, lemon juice, nutmeg, cinnamon and apple slices.
Place in a 9-inch deep pie plate.
Combine flour and salt.
Cut in margarine until it is the consistency of corn meal, then blend in water.
Roll out as for pie crust and place on top of apple filling.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 35 minutes, until crust is brown.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a boil, slowly, stirring often.
Continue to simmer for approximately 1 hour (stir often), until milk begins to thicken.
Remove from stove.
Stir in vanilla.
Cool and sprinkle with cinnamon, if desired.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water, using a spoon.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
You can make up batter ahead of time and then bake.
Grease muffin pan and fill about half full.
Bake at 425° for around 20 minutes.

title: yummy mound bars(microwave)
directions: Microwave butter in 12 x 8-inch glass baking dish, about 1 minute or until melted.
Stir in crumbs and sugar until combined. Press mixture firmly into bottom of dish.
Stir together coconut and condensed milk.
Spoon over crust.
Spread evenly.
Microwave Medium (1/2 power) uncovered 9 to 11 minutes or until heated through, rotating dish once.
Microwave chocolate pieces in uncovered glass bowl on High for 2 minutes or until softened. Stir until smooth.
Spoon onto coconut mixture.
Spread to cover. Refrigerate to set chocolate, about 1 hour.
Cut into bars.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Place lettuce in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass pan.
Layer celery, eggs, peas, peppers, onion and bacon, salting each layer lightly. Mix together mayonnaise and sugar; spread over the top as you would frosting.
Top with grated cheese.
Chill 8 to 12 hours or overnight.
You may add a layer of cooked, chopped meat of your choice.

title: kerrville spinach casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate surprise
directions: Combine pudding and Eagle Brand milk.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
In a square Pyrex dish, layer sliced bananas, vanilla wafers, pudding mixture and chocolate syrup.
Repeat layers!

title: oven crisp eggplant
directions: Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: burgogi
directions: Slice meat very thin.
Add all ingredients in small bowl and mix together with hands for at least 5 minutes.
Let set for 1 to 2 hours.
Prepare a large frying pan at high heat until pan gets very hot. Then put half of prepared meat in frying pan and stir-fry quickly for 5 to 10 minutes.
Do other half the same way, then serve hot.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Test with toothpick.

title: cheesy broccoli ham strata
directions: Cover bottom of buttered 8-inch square pan with half of the bread cubes.
Layer ham, thawed broccoli and cheese over bread. Top with remaining bread cubes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix together dressing and preserves in bowl.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour mixture over chicken and cover with foil. Marinate in refrigerator, preferably overnight.
Cook chicken, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Add as much pineapple as desired, along with the amount of juice you desire.
Check to see if basting is necessary.
Continue cooking for another 10 to 15 minutes, or until tender.

title: mashed garlic potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes and garlic in a large pan for 15 or 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Return to the pan.
Add remaining ingredients and mash.
Yields 4 servings.
Has 180 calories, fat free.

title: chicken salad(very good)
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water 5 minutes.
Dissolve in hot bouillon and cool. Stir slowly into the mayonnaise. Add other ingredients.
Mold.
Put carrot curls and olives in the center. May cut in squares and serve on lettuce.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, margarine and 1 egg together.
Press in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese, 2 eggs, chocolate chips and nuts; pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for only 30 minutes.

title: mushroom puffs
directions: In a medium size skillet, melt butter and saute mushrooms and onion over medium heat until golden, stirring occasionally; drain. Heat broiler.
In a medium size bowl, beat cream cheese, egg yolks, parsley and seasonings together until smooth.
Stir in mushroom mixture until combined.
Spread evenly on party bread slices and sprinkle with paprika.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes or until lightly browned and puffed.
Serve immediately.

title: mexican omelet
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Saute green pepper, onion and bacon in a skillet.
Add eggs and seasonings.
Cook over medium heat until omelet is partially set; top with cheese.
Cook until cheese is slightly melted; pour picante sauce over top.
Cook until cheese is melted.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan lightly.
Spread bottom of pan with 1 cup nuts.
Spread coconut over nuts.
Mix cake mix according to directions and spread over coconut.
Mix margarine, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Drop by teaspoon over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: linguine with tuna and tomato sauce
directions: Put the oil, onion, garlic and celery into a heavy saucepan and saute about 1 minute.
Sprinkle with salt and sugar and saute for another 3 minutes.

title: easy cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl; stir just until moistened. Pour into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 17 to 20 minutes or until golden.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: cherry crunch pie
directions: Drain cherries, reserving 1/2 cup of syrup.
Dissolve gelatin, sugar and cinnamon in boiling water; add reserved syrup.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in cherries, nuts and food coloring.
Chill in pie shell until firm.
Garnish with Cool Whip, if desired.
This recipe comes from Hills and Pines Garden Club, Raleigh, North Carolina.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add ground beef; don't brown.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spread 3 cups cabbage in baking dish. Cover with meat mixture.
Top with remaining cabbage; pour soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dill pickles
directions: Prick each cucumber with a fork and put them in clean, hot qt. jars.
Add 1 clove of fresh garlic and 1 sprig of fresh dill to each qt.
Combine the vinegar, water, and salt in a large pan and bring to a boil.
Pour boiling solution into jar to cover the cucumbers.
Seal tightly. Fresh grape leaves may be put over the cucumbers before sealing, if desired.

title: spinach crescents
directions: Note:
Can add 1 cup Ricotta cheese to mixture before spreading on dough for extra flavor.

title: chocolate icing
directions: In a saucepan, combine all but vanilla and cook until sugar dissolves.
Cook slowly to soft ball stage.
Add butter and remove from heat.
Place in cool water and add vanilla.
If icing gets hard, add hot water.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll out pastry to 1/8-inch thick and cut into 8 (6-inch) squares.
Make a paste of margarine, spices and brown sugar. Place apple in center of each pastry square.
Put jelly in cavity and spread paste over each apple.
Moisten edges of pastry and bring points together over apple, sealing firmly.
Roll leftover pastry, cut in streamers and place across top of dumplings.
Place in large greased baking dish and bake at 375° for 30 minutes. While dumplings are baking, make a syrup of water, sugar, food coloring and fruit juices.
Simmer to dissolve sugar.
Pour over apples and bake 10 to 20 minutes longer, basting frequently to give a pretty glaze.

title: hummus
directions: Process sesame seed several minutes until consistency of coarse peanut butter.
Add garlic cloves, their oil and lemon juice. Blend, then add drained garbanzos.
Add salt, cumin and sugar, then process until smooth.
Add very little water for sandwich spread, a bit more for dip.
Add a dash of cayenne pepper, if you like heat. Before serving, add chopped parsley for color and flavor.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Melt together sugar and brown sugar.
Mix all together and simmer.
Add cabbage rolls.

title: scallops in fresh tomato sauce
directions: In medium bowl, toss scallops with lemon juice.
Wipe mushrooms; slice lengthwise, right through stem, about 1/8-inch thick.
Toss with scallops.
If using fresh tomatoes, scald in boiling water; peel; remove seeds; cup pulp coarsely.
In 2 tablespoons hot oil in 8-inch skillet with tight fitting cover, saute half of shallots and parsley with the garlic just until golden.
Add tomato, salt, pepper, thyme and oregano.
Cook, over low heat, covered, 20 minutes, stirring occasionally to break up tomatoes.
Uncover and cook 5 minutes longer.
In 3 tablespoons hot oil in large skillet, saute remaining shallots and parsley, stirring about 5 minutes.
Add scallops and mushrooms.
Cook over high heat, uncovered, 10 minutes, shaking pan and stirring frequently.
Stir in tomato mixture.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Serve at once.
Nice with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix with bread crumbs, then add to stem mixture.
Use 2 or 3 tablespoons whipped cream.
Add just enough to hold it together. Butter bottom of mushrooms and place on a cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper lightly.
Stuff mushrooms with filling.
Top with grated Swiss cheese and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: swedish hots
directions: Mix all ingredients together in blender or mixer.
Cover skillet thinly with grease.
Let cook until dry on top and turn only once.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook meat and onion in skillet until meat is browned.
Add enchilada sauce and soup.
Blend well.
Break corn tortillas (either soft or crisp) into several pieces and line casserole dish.

Add layer of meat mixture and cheese; continue to layer tortilla, meat and cheese until you end with cheese on top. Either bake in 350° oven for about 25 minutes or cook in microwave for 5 minutes; turn and cook for 5 more minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter together. Mix with Crispix.
Put in paper bag.
Add powdered sugar and shake together.

title: champagnebrod(jam filled strips)
directions: Strain apricot preserves into a small bowl; thin with brandy and reserve.

title: fruit soup
directions: Cook tapioca in water until transparent.
Mix in boiled fruit and remaining ingredients.
Simmer over low fire for 3 or 4 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
(Norwegian.)

title: four pepper pasta
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, in saucepan, prepare angel hair pasta as label directs.
Drain; return pasta to saucepan.

title: tuna fish salad
directions: Drain tuna.
Break into pieces.
Combine next six ingredients and mix lightly.
Serve on lettuce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pie crust mix
directions: Sift together flour, salt and sugar.
Cut in half the shortening with two knives or pastry blender until mixture resembles corn meal.
Cut in remaining half of shortening until mixture resembles small peas.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator or a cool dry place.
Makes about 8 cups.

title: cottage cheese squares(varskeciai)
directions: Mix together in a large mixing bowl all ingredients except the butter.
Form into a large ball and place in refrigerator overnight or leave in freezer for 1 hour.
Cut into 4 parts for ease of handling and roll into 4 balls.
Roll out dough into 4 long sections approximately 1/2 inch in diameter.
With your fingertips, flatten the rolls approximately 1/4 inch thick.
With a knife, cut into 1-inch squares.
Place into rapidly boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain and place into serving bowl.
Pour melted butter over the top and serve hot.

title: old fashioned scones
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder, the 2 tablespoons sugar and salt.
With a fork, cut in the butter until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in eggs and cream to make a stiff dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured board and knead lightly until dough sticks together.
Divide into two parts.
Roll each part out to make a circle about 6 inches in diameter and 1-inch thick.
Cut each circle into quarter wedges.
Arrange on baking sheet about 1 inch apart.
Brush tops with reserved egg white and sprinkle with the 2 teaspoons sugar.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately.

title: raisin sauce
directions: (I always double this recipe.)
Mix together and cook over low heat and stir until thickened.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Blend sugar and margarine until creamy.
Add flour, vanilla and pecan meal.
Shape dough into fingers.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for about 20 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix chicken, vegetables and soups well. Place in 9 x 13 casserole dish. Mix flour, milk and melted butter. Pour on top. Bake at 350° until top is golden brown.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Cook beans ahead of time.
Cook ground beef in saucepan until brown.
Add green pepper, onion, tomatoes and spices or seasonings.
Mix cornbread as directed on box.
In deep dish baking pan, layer ground beef mixture and pinto beans, rotating both until pan is full, then pour cornbread over the top and bake in oven until cornbread is baked.

title: aunt vita's stuffing
directions: Saute ground beef until redness is gone from meat.
Do not cook with onions, etc.
Mix all ingredients together and stuff turkey.
Do not add any additional seasoning, not even salt.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Cut cabbage, onions and green pepper.
Bring sugar, vinegar, celery seed, salt and dry mustard to boil.
Remove from fire and add Wesson oil.
Pour over cabbage, onion and pepper.
Place in refrigerator.
Keeps well for several days.
Serves 10.

title: lots of apples apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar and honey.
Add oil, vanilla, eggs and nuts. Sift together the dry ingredients and add to the apple mixture. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add all other ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Drain fruits, save liquid.
Combine pudding with fruit juice. Fold in pineapple and oranges.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: wedding pound cake
directions: Put all the ingredients into the large bowl of an electric mixer.
Beat at medium speed for a full 20 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or 9 x 12-inch pan for a sheet cake.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Bring water to boiling. Put in shrimp and cook only 3 minutes. Drain (shrimp need to be cleaned and deveined either before or after cooking). Combine mayonnaise, Parmesan cheese, Worcestershire, lemon juice and Tabasco in a bowl. Add shrimp and stir well. Add artichoke hearts and mix gently. Place in ungreased casserole. Top with crushed Ritz crackers. Bake in preheated 400° oven until bubbly and crackers are slightly browned. Serves 4.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Set jello according to package (any berry flavor).
After jello is set, run fork through it to make chunks.
In large bowl, layer jello, sliced bananas and broken cookies; add whipped cream. Repeat layers and top with coconut.

title: tabouli(grain salad)
directions: Soak the wheat in water for about 15 minutes to soften.
Drain well, squeezing out all moisture.
Toss parsley, mint, cucumber, tomato, scallion and soaked wheat together in a serving dish. Coat with lemon juice, oil and salt and mix well.
Garnish with olives if desired.
Chill salad.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put ice and salt over sliced onions and cucumbers.
Let stand for 3 hours.
Drain good.

title: siamese chicken
directions: Combine ginger, garlic, soy sauce, sherry and oil in shallow glass bowl and add the chicken.
Stir well and let marinate for 2 hours at room temperature or 8 hours in the refrigerator.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Wash broccoli and cherry tomatoes and put aside and drain. Combine oil, vinegar and spices; mix well.
Pour mixture over broccoli.
Garnish with cherry tomatoes.
Place in refrigerator. Baste intermittently with sauce.
Marinate for at least 2 hours. Now enjoy.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Mix the milk, water and pudding together.
Refrigerate pudding mixture for 5 minutes.
Bring the strawberries to a boil, then add jello.
Let them cool completely.
Add Cool Whip to the pudding mixture.
Break the cake into small pieces.
Layer a tall glass bowl with half the cake, then half strawberries and then half the pudding mixture.
Repeat the layers.
Garnish with strawberries.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix first three ingredients and boil for 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add Jell-O, boil 2 minutes.
Pour into jelly glasses and cover with melted paraffin.

title: moist meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and put in greased loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Grease 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Layer tortillas, refried beans, olives, cheese and enchilada sauce.
Repeat layering again.
Top with plain tortilla.

title: wheat rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add egg.
Add yeast mixture (dissolved) to sugar, shortening and egg mixture.
Stir. Add 1 cup wheat flour, 1 cup white flour and salt.
Beat 1 minute. Stir in 1/2 cup hot tap water.
Add remaining flour needed to make dough stiff enough to handle.
Cover and let rise until double. Punch down.
Form into rolls and place in greased pan.
Cover and let rise until double.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 375° oven. Makes 16 rolls.

title: swiss oatmeal(breakfast treat)
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Cream sugar, shortening, oleo and vanilla.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Beat in flour, alternating with buttermilk.
Fold in egg whites and coconut.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) cake pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs, onion, salt and pepper.
Pour over broccoli in shallow dish (8 x 8-inch).
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Add melted butter to stuffing and spoon over top of casserole.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
In another mixing bowl, combine eggs, bananas, oil, buttermilk and vanilla; add to flour mixture, stirring just until combined.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 5-inch baking pan (large loaf pan).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until bread tests done.
Cool on wire rack.
Yield:
1 loaf.
Recipe does not double very well.

title: rocks cookies(drop cookies)
directions: Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: brown sugar shortbread puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat brown sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg yolk; blend well. Add flour. Stir until mixture forms a smooth dough. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown and set.
Yields 4 dozen cookies.

title: chicken squares
directions: Cook (boil) chicken.
Take off bone and cut in small pieces. Soften cream cheese and blend with milk.
Add chicken and seasonings to cheese mixture.
Take crescent rolls and press two together.
Put 1/2 cup of chicken mixture in the middle of one. Turn the 4 corners up and press together.
Brush top with melted butter and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake according to temperature on roll package, for about 30 minutes, or until golden brown on a cookie sheet.

title: 100% whole wheat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl.
Scald milk and mix in oil, honey, molasses and salt.
When milk is cool, add to yeast and stir.
Stir in flour, a bit at a time.
Turn out on floured board and knead.
Let rise in covered bowl until doubled. Punch down.
Separate into 2 or 3
loaves and shape loaves.
Let rise in bread pans 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 2 cups.
Bring to boil.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Add 1 cup cold water. Add pineapple and blueberry; congeal.

title: banana salad
directions: Cook until thick; then cool.
I use a double boiler so I don't have to stir so often.
Put a layer of pudding in dish; cover with sliced bananas.
Then add another layer of pudding and another layer of bananas.
Cover entire top with chopped pecans.

title: christmas trees
directions: Mix batter as for cupcakes.
Bake in greased and floured cone-shaped Dixie cups.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Put all ingredients in mixer except pecans. Add pecans last. Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip and chocolate shavings, if desired.

title: butter crisps
directions: Cream the oleo and butter and add sugar, egg yolk, vanilla, salt, flour, nuts and egg white.
Mix all together and spread with spatula on ungreased 16 x 14-inch cookie sheet.
Set aside until you whip slightly egg white.
Spread with pastry brush across top of cookie dough.
Sprinkle nuts on top of egg streaked dough. Bake at 275° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until brown.
Cut in squares as soon as you take from oven but do not remove from pan until cold.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Add sauce and hamburger to noodles; salt and pepper to taste.

title: tom clark's sweet potato biscuits(makes about 4 dozen)
directions: Boil and skin the potatoes.
Place in a large bowl and mash with the sugar and Crisco. In a separate large bowl, blend together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend wet mixture to dry.
If too dry, add water.
Make into biscuits and place in greased foil pie tins. Cover with foil and freeze at this point or let rise for 20 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes or until slightly brown on bottom.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Put ingredients in blender at low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into an ungreased 9-inch pie pan.
Let set 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with Angel Flake coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: cheesecake
directions: Press graham cracker crust mixture into a 10-inch spring-form pan; set aside.
Beat cream cheese at high speed of electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until set.

title: creamy peach pie
directions: Melt marshmallows with orange and lemon juice in double boiler.
Stir until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream and peaches. Pour into pastry shell and chill.
Garnish with sliced peaches.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed until well blended.
Add 2 eggs.
Mix well.
Pour batter into pie crust.
Bake for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
For best results, refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over vegetables, grapes and sunflower seeds.
Mix well.
Refrigerate for an hour before serving.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir into sugar mixture. Add pineapple and vanilla; drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hungarian goulash(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Brown round steak in oil in electric frying pan or heavy skillet.
Add salt and pepper.
While browning, dissolve bouillon cubes in 2 cups boiling water.
Add hot bouillon to browned beef. Add bay leaf, cloves, garlic powder and cayenne pepper.
Cook slowly (simmer) for 2 hours.
Add water as needed.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Add water, if needed.
Simmer 45 minutes.
In a separate bowl, cream together softened butter, flour and paprika until smooth.
Slowly stir into meat and vegetables.
Stir gently until liquid is thickened.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cover bottom of dish with chicken.
Pour mixed vegetables, soup and broth over chicken.
Add chopped onion and celery salt. Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix melted margarine, flour and milk together.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This is a quick fix recipe and tastes just like chicken pot pie.
Husbands love it.

title: white bean bacon soup
directions: Heat oil in medium size nonstick saucepan.
Add onion, garlic and bacon.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add half the beans, the thyme, carrots and chicken broth; cook 3 minutes.

title: chocolate sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter, gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Combine four, cocoa, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add boiling water, mix well.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Sift flour.
Add 1 teaspoon soda and 1 teaspoon salt.
Then add sugar, margarine and oil.
Mix with eggs.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla and fold in chopped apples, nuts, dates and coconut.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Can bake in tube pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serve with whipped topping and cherry on top.

title: ham tetrazzini
directions: Combine flour, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and paprika in paper bag.
Add meat; shake to coat.
Reserve flour mixture.
Heat oil in heavy kettle.
Brown meat on all sides. Remove meat.
Saute onion and garlic in same oil.
Return meat to kettle; add broth, 1/2 cup water, tomatoes, salt, pepper and caraway seed.
Cover; simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Blend 3 tablespoons reserved flour mixture and 1/2 cup water; add to kettle.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add sour cream; heat, but do not boil.
Toss noodles with butter; serve hot with goulash.

title: eggless applesauce cake
directions: Sift flour before measuring; mix in order given and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
By adding 1 cup mixed candied fruit, this makes a delicious fruit cake.
It can be baked in loaf pan or cupcakes.

title: texas fare
directions: In a low casserole, arrange layers of sliced onion, sliced pepper, sliced tomatoes and kernel corn.
Top with frankfurters that have been cut into 2-inch rounds.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
If frankfurters brown too fast, cover with foil.

title: romaine lettuce salad
directions: Mix all ingredients to taste.
Toss with Honey Dijon Ranch or Raspberry Vinaigrette salad dressings.

title: overnight coleslaw
directions: Sprinkle one cup sugar over cabbage, pepper and onion. Heat remaining ingredients until boiling and pour over cabbage mixture. Cover tightly and refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: roasted potato salad
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Place potatoes on a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown, stirring once.
Mix dressing, bacon, eggs, onions, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Add potatoes and mix lightly.
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 6 servings.

title: double batch kate's sweet pickles
directions: Double amount of cukes, just make sure you have enough syrup to cover cukes after you have packed jars.
You may have to make some more, some cukes will take more some will take less, depends on how you pack jars.

title: easy salad
directions: Mix all.
Refrigerate 2 or 3 hours.
Serve on lettuce.

title: dirt recipe
directions: Cream together margarine, cream cheese and sugar.
Add 2 packages of pudding.
Beat.
Add milk and Cool Whip.
Grind 1 large package of Oreo cookies.
Layer in cake pan with pudding and cookies.
End with crushed cookies.
Chill overnight.

title: broccoli cheese roll-up appetizers
directions: Coat frozen bread well with vegetable oil and thaw bread in a sealed freezer bag (about 4 hours).
Mix remaining ingredients. Roll out thawed bread into rectangles 7-inches wide and 10-inches long on floured bread board.
Spread mixture on each triangle. Roll up each triangle jelly roll fashion and seal edges (roll should be 7-inches wide when finished rolling).
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 10 minutes and then slice lengthwise first and then across like you would fresh bread; this will give you finger size pieces.

title: homemade tortilla chips
directions: Cut stack of tortillas into 8 wedges each.
Spread wedges in a single layer on baking sheet.
Sprinkle with cumin and salt.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, turning after 5 minutes.
Make sure you watch them closely, you don't want them brown.
Store in airtight container.
Use your favorite salsa or dip.
Twenty chips are a serving.
Contains 1 fat gram and 100 calories.

title: chicken and almonds
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Heat oil in large skillet and brown almonds.
Remove to paper towel and put aside.
In oil, cook chicken 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Then, add green onions, celery, pea pods, mushrooms, water chestnuts and soy sauce.
Cook 2 minutes, still stirring.
Add 1 cup chicken broth, bring to boil and cook 5 minutes.
In meantime, mix cornstarch with remaining broth and after 5 minutes, add to skillet and stir until sauce is thickened, then add to almonds.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Boil and cut chicken breasts into bite size pieces, set aside. Cook broccoli and drain (do not cook soft).
Arrange in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place chicken pieces on top of broccoli.
Sprinkle almonds on top of chicken.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice and pour over entire dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with bread crumbs.
(I usually put some of the cheese with the bread crumbs.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. (Allow more time if frozen or refrigerated ahead of time.)
Fresh broccoli may be used.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add beaten eggs.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add in small portions to other ingredients.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Bake for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° in large greased and floured tube pan.

title: holiday chicken for a crowd
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Put the chicken into a deep casserole.
Brown the mushrooms.
Mix the 3 cans of soup thoroughly and do not dilute.
Pour over chicken.
Put browned mushrooms on top.
If you can, refrigerate overnight to enhance the flavor.
Before baking, add white wine.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand 10 minutes. Add sugars and butter.	Stir until butter melts.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add	flour, soda, salt and cocoa and mix well.
Add 1/2 package
chocolate	chips.	Pour
batter
into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and remaining chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: meringue pineapple bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together well and put into a well greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat mixture down firmly.

title: pier 4 mushrooms("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Slice mushrooms after cleaning.
Combine mushrooms with all other ingredients and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Drain and serve.

title: don truitt's first prize chili
directions: Cook beef in a large skillet or heavy pan until meat loses redness. Remove. Cook onions and garlic separately and return beef to pan. Stir in tomato sauce, wine, chilies, salt, cumin and Bitters.
Partially cover and simmer 1 hour or more to desired thickness.
(Tip:
A grated potato is a good thickener and won't show or taste.)
Add beans, if desired, and simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes. Serve with chopped onion, grated Cheddar and dollops of sour cream in each bowl. Freezes well.
Yields about 2 quarts.

title: fruit kabobs and dip
directions: Stick two different fruit cubes on a toothpick.
Set on plate around dish of dip.

title: fresh strawberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray with nonstick vegetable shortening a 6 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Toss berries lightly with sugar and lemon juice and place in baking dish.
In a bowl, combine biscuit mix, melted margarine, eggs and milk.
Lightly mix with a fork and spoon-drop dough over berries.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until crust is golden brown.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chicken or turkey cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together real well.
Add chicken broth and/or juice from chicken or turkey.
Do not make it real soupy. Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: quick doughnuts
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended. Knead about 10 times. Roll, cut and fry. Glaze, frost or roll in powdered sugar.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pie fillings.
Add fruit cocktail and oranges.
Fold in Cool Whip and chill.
Use a 13 x 9-inch dish.

title: english pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Toss lightly with mayonnaise. Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: pizzeria casserole
directions: Cook pasta for 7 minutes, drain.
Combine pizza sauce, pepperoni, and 1 c. cheese in 1-1/2 qt. casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake for 35 min. covered or until bubbly hot.

title: sugar-free banana muffins
directions: Beat egg, oil and milk.
Stir in bananas.
Mix dry ingredients together and stir into banana mixture until flour is moistened. Fill muffin tin 1/2 full.
Bake about 23 minutes.
Let cool about 15 minutes before removing from pans to let texture firm up.

title: jerusalem kugel
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 1 teaspoon salt in about 3 quarts water and bring to boil.
Add the spaghetti and cook until al dente, about 5 minutes.
Drain well and set aside in saucepan.
In a medium size saucepan, heat the oil and 1/2 cup sugar.
Stir constantly until sugar turns very dark, almost black, about 10 minutes.
Cool.
Pour hot caramel into pasta immediately and mix well.
Cool slightly.

title: creamed corn
directions: Cut corn from cob.
In skillet, put butter, corn, cream, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cover.
Simmer 6 to 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Crush crackers and mix with margarine.
Cook vegetables and drain.
Put in baking dish.
Mix onion, celery, mayonnaise and cheese.
Spread over other vegetables.
Top with crackers mixed with margarine.
Bake 20 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake 5 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sticky buns
directions: Put nuts in bottom of 9 x 13 greased pan.
Put frozen rolls on top.
Sprinkle with dry pudding mix.
Melt margarine and brown sugar and pour over top of rolls.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap and let rise until morning or until doubles in size.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 20 minutes.
Check frequently to keep from over browning.
Turn out onto platter nut side up.

title: barbecue sauce(great on ribs)
directions: Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes.
Great on ribs!

title: chili
directions: Chop onions, garlic and jalapeno pepper.
Mix all ingredients except beans.
Simmer 2 hours on low.
Add beans and cook 1 more hour.

title: oven barbecue
directions: Cut meat lengthwise, not quite through, into 8 slices.
Place in greased shallow baking dish.
Mix Hunt's sauce, water and seasoning.
Pour over meat.
Arrange potatoes around meat.
Bake in hot oven (425°), about 30 minutes, basting occasionally.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: no-bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate until cool.
Cut into squares.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Spread over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: betty's bread pudding
directions: Bring raisins to boil; simmer 15 minutes and drain.

title: easter eggs
directions: Mix together using only enough liquid (milk or cherry juice) to mix.
This should be firm enough to shape into eggs.
Allow to chill.
Shape into eggs or candies.
Chill, then dip into Chocolate Mixture.

title: potato cabbage soup
directions: Stir gently and return to heat.
Do not boil.
Add 2 tablespoons vinegar (if desired) for a sharper taste.

title: party pinwheels
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread on tortillas.
Sprinkle on celery and olives.
Roll and wrap lightly.
Chill 2 hours.
Cut off roll ends.
Cut rolls into 1-inch slices.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine vegetables in a greased 11 x 7-inch casserole dish. Pour sauce mixture of soup, cheese, onion and sour cream over vegetables and stir. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Melt margarine and mix in crumbled crackers and slivered almonds. Sprinkle topping over casserole and bake for about 10 to 12 more minutes. Watch carefully as the cracker mixture browns very quickly.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine beef, crumbs, egg and 2 teaspoons bouillon; mix well. Shape into 1 1/4 inch balls; brown in large skillet.
Remove from pan; drain fat.
In skillet, combine preserves, lemon juice and 2 teaspoons bouillon over low heat.
Cook and stir 10 minutes.
Add meatballs.
Simmer, uncovered, about 10 minutes.

title: chicken breasts eden isle
directions: Line deep baking dish with dried beef slices.
Wrap bacon around chicken breasts and place in baking dish.
In blender, cream the soup, sour cream and cream cheese.
Pour over chicken breasts.
Cover with lid and bake 2 hours at 325°.
Serve on a bed of rice.

title: squash casserole for
directions: Place squash, zucchini, onion and water in 3-quart microwave-safe casserole dish.
Cook, covered on High about 10 minutes, stirring once.
Drain.
Mix together cheese, yogurt and chili peppers.
In 12 x 8 x 2-inch casserole, layer half of squash mixture, half of cheese mixture, then half of the chips; repeat layers.
Cook at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in an oblong cake pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Turn oven off; pour 4 cups miniature marshmallows on top.
Return to oven until marshmallows melt, then top with topping.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add liquids and mix thoroughly. Bake in loaf pan at 325° for one hour.

title: fortune cookies
directions: You will need fortunes on paper slips.

title: baked beans for four
directions: All in the bean
pot.
Add water until pot is 3/4 full. Set bean pot in deep pan with water.
Keep adding water during baking so it doesn't boil dry.
Bake 5 hours at 350°.

title: old-fashion egg bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Pour into hot greased shallow baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: nana's best veggie dip
directions: Blend all ingredients in food processor or blender.
Combine until smooth.
Serve with fresh veggies.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Boil, de-bone and chop chicken.
In 1/2 cup chicken broth, cook onion and bell pepper.
In large mixing bowl; mix onion and bell pepper with chicken.
Add chili powder, soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Line bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish with cut tortillas.
Pour soup mixture over tortillas in layers.
Add grated cheese on top.
Cook 30 minutes at 350° until cheese melts.

title: peanut buster bar
directions: Mix Oreo
cookies
and	oleo
well and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Over cookie mixture add softened ice cream.
Top ice cream
and	cookie mixture with fudge topping and peanuts. Freeze. Top with whipped cream before serving if desired.

title: tigers milk punch
directions: Blend on high in blender the strawberries, ice cream and milk until smooth.
Pour mixture into a small punch bowl.
Just before serving, pour soda into milk mixture.
Stir gently to mix.
Serve.

title: lemon sauce
directions: 1. Bring to boil stirring constantly.
2. Serve over pudding.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Prepare pie crust and line a 9-inch pie pan with bottom crust. Melt butter in large skillet.
Add flour as you would for gravy. Slowly add broth to make the gravy base.
Make sure base is thick. If you need to, add some cornstarch.
Add Veg-All (drained), cooked meat, salt and pepper, if desired.
Pour into pie shell and add top crust.
Pinch edges and cut several slits in top.
Bake in a 400° oven for 45 minutes or until crust is brown.
Let cool to warm before serving.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat until light.
Add milk and melted butter with other ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole at 350° until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spanish meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly the beef, 1/3 cup of sauce and remaining ingredients.
Spread in ungreased loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch. Spread remaining sauce over loaf.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape in a loaf.
Let set overnight or approximately 6 hours in refrigerator.
Cook approximately 2 hours at 325°.
Serve with a salsa sauce.

title: coq au vin
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Brown chicken breasts.
Mix all ingredients and pour over chicken.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Serve over rice or sliced French bread.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix well the sugar, peanuts, syrup and salt in a 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Microwave on Cook for 7 to 8 minutes.
Stir well after 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla and mix well.
Cook 1 minute more. Check for hard crack (or 300°) stage.
Add soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour mix onto a lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Cool 1/2 hour and break into pieces.

title: pork chops creole
directions: Brown pork chops lightly in 2 tablespoons oil in large skillet. Saute garlic, green pepper and onion in 2 tablespoons oil in small skillet. Add tomatoes, thyme, salt and pepper. Add pork chops to sauce. Steam, covered, for 30 minutes or until tender.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix, pour in pricked pie shell and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or 1 hour.
(Check time with your oven temperature.)

title: custard pie
directions: Mix sugar with the well beaten eggs.
Add milk, vanilla and mix well.
Place in 10 inch unbaked pie shell.

title: all-bran muffins
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well, then add nuts.
Stir lightly to blend nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: easy brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat in 2-quart pan.
Stir until melted.
Stir sugar into chocolate.
Stir in eggs and vanilla until completely mixed.
Mix in flour until well blended. Stir in nuts.

title: crab quiche
directions: Combine mayonnaise, flour, eggs and milk.
Mix until blended. Stir in crab meat, shredded Swiss cheese and onions.
Pour into 2 pastry-lined pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fireside coffee mix
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Store in an airtight container to make 1 cup.
Use 2 1/2 tablespoons to 1 cup boiling water.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut up broccoli.
Cook bacon until crisp, then crumble.
Chop red onion.
Add all to raisins.
Mix Miracle Whip, vinegar and sugar.
Mix into other ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Good made the day before.

title: veal goulash
directions: Trim veal and cut into large cubes.
Saute onions in olive oil until clear; add veal and saute.
Add paprika and veal stock and stir until blended.
Add herbs and garlic to veal mixture and add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until tender, approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Before serving, blend cornstarch with sour cream and add to goulash.
Top each serving with a dollop of sour cream and sprinkle with paprika.
Can be served with spaetzel or on mashed potatoes or rice.
Fantastic!

title: baked apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add water.
Combine the flour, sugar, butter, cinnamon and salt together in your food processor or by rubbing with your fingers until fine crumbs are formed.
Spread the mixture over the apples. Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes uncovered.
Serve cold topped with ice cream.

title: yogurt sauced peaches
directions: In blender, combine cottage cheese, skim milk, sugar, lemon juice and cardamon.
Cover and process until smooth.
Fold in yogurt; chill.
At serving time, using a paring knife, peel, pit and slice peaches.
If you use canned peaches, drain.
Divide peaches among 8 sherbet dishes.
Spoon sauce over peaches.

title: party rye pizza
directions: Cook sausage (not too brown).
Add other ingredients and stir until cheese melts.
Spread on 2 loaves of party rye.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell. Cook at 350° until firmly set, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken cordon bleu(microwave)
directions: Place chicken breasts, one at a time, between sheets of plastic wrap.
Using the flat side of a meat mallet or rolling pin, pound to 1/4 inch.
Sprinkle each with salt.
Cut cheese into 8 sticks, each about 1 inch long.
Cut ham in half.
Roll cheese inside ham slices.
Place ham-cheese roll on chicken breast.
Beat egg and water in bowl.
Coat chicken breasts with flour; dip
into egg mixture.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Microwave for 5 minutes on High.
Turn rolls over and cook for 5 to 6 minutes on High or until chicken is done.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Cool and remove meat from bones. Cook spaghetti until tender.
In skillet, melt butter and saute onion until tender.
Add mushroom soup and about 1 cup of broth off chicken.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer spaghetti, chicken, cheese and sauce.
Top with more cheese and bake 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars and 1/2 stick butter 1 minute in baking dish. Cream all the remaining ingredients.
Put batter over melted chocolate and swirl.
Bake 7 minutes.

title: raisin rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir well. Pour into a greased 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Place in a pan with 1-inch water.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, melted butter and sugar.
Spread in pan and bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Beat until smooth cream cheese and sugar, then add whipped topping.
Spread over cooled crust.
Chill.
Mix gelatin and boiling water.
Add strawberries.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
I put a layer of Cool Whip on top and sprinkle finely chopped pecans on it.

title: steak san marco
directions: Cut steak in serving pieces and place in skillet; cover with onion soup mix and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with spices, oil and vinegar.
Simmer, covered, 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Add all dry ingredients to oil and eggs.
Blend everything and pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for about 70 minutes.
Allow to cool in pan.
Slice and serve with cream cheese or sweet butter.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into ball, then roll in chopped nuts or paprika. Serve with crackers.

title: coconut fruit bowl
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in sour cream and salt. Chill overnight.
Serves 8.

title: broiled barbecue spareribs
directions: Boil spareribs for about 40 minutes.
Soak in sauce for 30 minutes and broil.	Boiled spareribs can be frozen.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake according to package in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prick top of cake with fork and pour Kahlua over cake.
Let this soak in (should be left overnight).
Make mousse according to directions. To assemble, crumble 1/3 cake and place in the bottom of a glass bowl.
Layer 1/3 mousse, then 1/3 whipped topping and 2 Skor candy bars which have been broken into small pieces.
Repeat layers. Make in punch bowl or trifle bowl.
Skor is hard to find, so you may want to use Hershey's almond bars.

title: hot and honeyed chicken wings
directions: Cut off and discard wing tips.
Cut each wing in half at joint.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: saucy carrots
directions: Mix carrots and undiluted soup to cooked, drained carrots while still hot.
Combine other ingredients.
Add to carrots; chill.
If sweetener needed, add 1/4 to 1/2 cup honey or NutraSweet.

title: caribbean dessert
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and oleo.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine 2 eggs, cream cheese and sugar minus 1/4 cup.
Pour over cake mix.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle 1/4 cup powdered sugar on top.
Cool in refrigerator. Cut into squares, 30 pieces.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: For crust, cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Combine 1 egg, Parmesan cheese and margarine.
Stir in hot spaghetti.
Press mixture evenly into bottom and up sides of a 9-inch pie plate.

title: cammie's baked pork chops
directions: Tenderize both sides of pork chops very well with meat tenderizer.
(May add pinches of garlic, salt, onion salt and pepper).
On stove, heat mushroom soup until creamy (add a little milk).
Pour into baking dish.
Place chops in dish and spoon soup over.
Add can of mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage, vegetables and almonds.	In sauce pan boil water add dry soup and rice.
Remove from heat and let sit 10 minutes.
Combine meat, vegetables, rice and soups.
Place in 9 by 13 inch pan; and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: stuffed cabbage head
directions: Trim off outside of cabbage.
Cook in boiling water 45 minutes, or until almost tender.
Remove cabbage from water and drain.
Reserve 1/4 cup cabbage water.
Core cabbage, making a cavity through cabbage.
Blend meat, onion and garlic powder; add 2 tablespoons tomato sauce.
Stuff mixture into cabbage.
Place in deep pot.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over cabbage.
Cover; cook about 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from heat and serve with sauce. Yields 4 servings.

title: sonia's yummy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. In large mixing bowl, cream together butter and powdered sugar. Add eggs and beat again until light and fluffy. Combine dry ingredients, except nuts, gradually. Add dry ingredients and vanilla to creamed mixture. Sprinkle nuts on bottom of lightly greased 9 x 5 x 4 loaf pan. Pour batter into pan. Sprinkle nuts on top and bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes and then turn out on wire rack to cool.

title: barbecue sauce for ribs
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Low heat simmer until thick.

title: herb-roasted chicken
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients, mixing well.
Set aside.
Cover potatoes with water in a small saucepan and cook, covered, over medium heat until tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Cut potatoes into bite-sized pieces and return to the saucepan.
Add celery, pimento and parsley to the pan.
Toss gently.
Add 2 tablespoons of the tarragon-oil mixture and again toss gently. Set aside.

title: oil pastry
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Measure flour by dip, level, pour method. Mix flour and salt.
Add oil; mix with fork until it looks like meal.
Sprinkle with water; mix with fork.
Gather dough together. If too dry, add 1 to 2 tablespoons more oil.
Press into ball. Divide almost in half.
Use larger half for bottom roll.
Fill trim.
Roll top.
