Cut slits; place over filling.
Seal with water, flute.
Bake with favorite fruit recipes.
To prevent overbrowning of edges, cover with 1 1/2 strips aluminum foil.
Remove strips 15 minutes before end of baking.

title: steak san marco
directions: In a large skillet, arrange meat.
Cover with soup mix and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with oregano, garlic, pepper, oil and vinegar. Cover and simmer about 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Can also be done in oven at 350° until done, about the same time.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Drain all vegetables.
Thinly sliced green onions.
Mix all vegetables together.
Mix sugar with vinegar (you can use half tarragon and half wine vinegar or half malt and half regular vinegar).
Add mixture to vegetable.
May add black pepper if desired.
Refrigerate salad at least 24 hours before serving. Pour off some of marinade or use slotted spoon to serve.
Keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: pizza pasta
directions: Bring water to a rolling boil. Add 1 tablespoon salt and 2 tablespoons oil to water. Add spaghetti; cook 6 minutes or until barely tender. In large skillet, brown ground beef. Then add pepperoni, spaghetti sauce and Italian tomato paste. Mix well. Add 1/2 cup grated cheese, bell pepper, onion and mushrooms. Mix all ingredients together. Bake in 3-quart baking dish with lid. Top with 2 cups cheese. Bake in microwave 15 minutes or until hot all the way through and cheese is melted.

title: sausage stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blot sausage dry with paper towel and combine with cheese, salad dressing, olives or mushrooms and pepper.
Lightly grease a mini (or regular) muffin tin and press 1 wrapper in each cup.
Brush with oil.
Bake 5 minutes until golden.
Remove from tins.
Place on baking sheet.
Fill with sausage mixture.
Bake 5 minutes until bubbly.
Makes 4 dozen. Very good; time consuming.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix rice, sugar and margarine together.
Beat eggs in milk and add to the first mixture.
Pour into a buttered baking dish and bake at 400° for approximately 35 to 40 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: In
medium
saucepan,
boil
eggplant
and onion for 10 minutes
in
about 2-inches of water.
Drain thoroughly.
Beat egg yolks
with
wire
whisk, pour over bread cubes and gently mix and let
stand
for a few minutes.
Add cheese, egg yolks and bread to drained eggplant and onion.
Mix gently but well. Turn into greased
x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 35 to 45 minutes, until lightly browned on top.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Lightly butter 2 loaf pans or tube pan. In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Gently fold in all but 3 tablespoons of flour 1/4 cup at a time.
Toss blueberries with lemon rind and remaining flour.
Fold into batter and pour into pan(s).
Bake 1 hour and 30 to 50 minutes, depending on pan size.
Cool completely before unmolding.
Let stand overnight before serving.
Can be prepared several days ahead and can be frozen.

title: butterscotch topping
directions: Mix together egg yolks and half and half.
Add brown sugar and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add butter until melted. Stir constantly.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add molasses and egg.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Roll in small balls, dip into sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Makes about four dozen.
If dough is too sticky to handle, add a little more flour.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: In a saucepan, combine milk, rice, sugar and salt. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes. Add raisins and vanilla. Cover and bake 15 minutes longer. Sprinkle with cinnamon, if desired. Serve warm or chilled. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: veal chassuer
directions: Dredge veal in flour.
Saute in olive oil.
Brown on both sides.
Add mushrooms and shallots until wilted.
Add Madeira sauce, 1 1/2 cups water, tomato paste and sauce mix.
Mix well. Simmer 10 minutes.
Add tarragon.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, oats, milk, eggs, onion, cheese and seasonings. Mix.
Press meat mixture into 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pour off drippings.
Spread pizza sauce over meat.
Bake 10 more minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cook 3 more minutes.
Garnish with green pepper rings.

title: barbara's basic punch
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except the ginger ale, in a large bowl or pot.
Chill.
Just before serving, transfer the mixture to a punch bowl and add the ginger ale.
Yields about 4 quarts.

title: frog-eye salad
directions: Cook R&F Acini Di Pepe as packaged directs; drain.
In a heavy sauce pan beat egg with wire whisk until foamy.
Stir in sugar, flour, salt and reserved pineapple liquid.
Over low heat, cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
In large bowl, combine Acini Di Pepe with egg mixture.
Chill thoroughly, about one hour. Stir in pineapple, fruit cocktail and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream.
Cover, chill thoroughly.
Stir before serving. Refrigerate leftovers.
6-8 servings.

title: sausage roll-ups
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Separate and lay crescent rolls flat. Place in center of each roll one sausage, 1 teaspoon grated cheese and 1/2 teaspoon onion.
Roll up tight and seal edges all the way around so cheese doesn't bubble out and burn roll.
Place 2 inches apart on sheet.
Bake at recommended degrees and time according to crescent roll package directions.

title: coconut delight
directions: Mix flour and butter until crumbly.
Add nuts and mix.
Spread evenly on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Mix with mixer and spread evenly over crust.
(Use knife not rubber spatula.)
Mix pudding per instructions on box.
Add coconut and coconut flavoring.
Pour over cream cheese spread. Make up 1 envelope Dream Whip topping.
Sprinkle with nuts and coconut for topping.
Refrigerate.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Wash, dry and core apples.
Cut into eighths with peel left on.
Add cider, sugar, cinnamon and cloves to crock-pot.
Cook on low for 15 to 20 hours, covered.
Put in blender and pick out lumps, if necessary.
Cook again in crock-pot on high, uncovered, until thick, 5 to 6 hours.

title: no knead dinner rolls
directions: Mix and cool to lukewarm milk, sugar, shortening and salt. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water and add to milk mixture; mix well. Blend in egg. Add gradually, 1 cup at a time, the flour. Mix until well blended. Cover and store in refrigerator at least 2 hours or until needed.

title: curry wurst(straight from germany!)
directions: Slice sausage and brown in butter; add onion and pepper cut into medium sized pieces.
Cook until tender.
Sprinkle with curry powder when ready to serve.
This is good served with rice.
Bon appetit!

title: beach day casserole
directions: *Or try cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 cup Burgundy wine.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and oleo. Mix with other ingredients. Chill. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream margarine and cheese.
Add flour, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add rice cereal and mix with hands as dough is very stiff.
Roll into walnut size balls and flatten into cookie with fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 7 to 8 dozen.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine in large bowl all dry ingredients.
Combine pumpkin, oil and water.
Beat eggs and add to oil mixture.
Make a well in flour mixture. Add oil mixture and stir until well mixed.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test with toothpick.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Cool on rack.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: deb's buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Beat the egg and buttermilk and combine with sifted ingredients with several swift strokes.
Do not overbeat.
For thinner pancakes, add a little more buttermilk.

title: chocolate cake icing
directions: Put magarine in pan.
Add milk and cocoa.
Let margarine melt and bring to a boil, stirring.
Add powdered sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Bring to another boil.
Add vanilla flavoring to taste. Remove from heat, beat until cool.
Spread on cake.
Makes delicious icing.

title: yogurt glazed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sprinkle garlic salt, paprika and basil over chicken pieces.
In small bowl, stir 1/2 cup yogurt and soy sauce until creamy.
Place chicken in a shallow baking dish.
Brush with yogurt mixture.
Bake uncovered 20 minutes.
Turn chicken over and baste with juices.
Bake another 20 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
In a small bowl, stir 1/2 cup of yogurt and flour until creamy.
Spread over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over chicken.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Melt shortening over low heat; cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to first mixture and mix well.
Chill.
Then roll into 1-inch balls; place on a greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes (8 for chewy, 10 for crispy).
Remove from cookie sheet; place on wire rack to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Dice 4 slices of bread; place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a bowl, combine celery, onion, pepper, chicken, salt and mayonnaise and pour this over diced bread.
Combine eggs and milk; place 6 slices of bread on top of mixture.
Pour egg and milk mixture over all.
Spread soup on top; sprinkle cheese over all.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
After baking, allow casserole to set 15 to 20 minutes before cutting.

title: panettone
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Stir in 1 teaspoon sugar.
Stir in eggs, 1/2 cup butter, 1/3 cup sugar, salt, vanilla and grated lemon peel.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except melted butter, mixing to form stiff dough.

title: kids' favorite shepherd's pie
directions: After meat is cooked and drained, put back in pan and add soups, milk and seasonings.
Heat until blended.
Put into 2 1/2-quart casserole and top with mashed potatoes.
Layer some shredded Cheddar on top and bake at 325° until heated through, about 45 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions; then drain.
Cook onion and pepper (optional) in butter or margarine until tender.
Add flour and blend.
Add milk.
Cook over low heat until thick; stir constantly.
Add pimento, soup and tuna.
Stir together.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet tomato sauce
directions: Scald tomatoes and remove skins.
Quarter and cook until soft and well separated (20 minutes at least).
Add sugar, salt and bread, broken up in pieces.
Then cook for another 10 minutes, stirring often.
Have tomatoes simmering on medium heat.
Do not burn!
They are ready for jars at this point.

title: smoked sausage hawaiian
directions: Saute green pepper, onion, tomatoes and sausage in butter. Combine cornstarch, ginger, vinegar, soy sauce and preserves. Stir into sausage mixture.
Cook over low heat until sauce thickens.
Mix in pineapple chunks and heat.
Serve with rice.

title: chili tuna
directions: Put in pan and bring almost to a boil (if it boils it will ruin taste).
Add 4 ounces tuna to mixture.
(Very good when you want something hot and quick.)
One serving = 4 proteins, 1 vegetable and 10 optional calories.

title: lemon freeze
directions: Combine corn flake crumbs, butter and 2 tablespoons of sugar in 8-inch pie pan; mix well.
Reserve 2 to 4 tablespoons of crumbs for topping.
Press crumbs evenly and firmly around bottom and sides of the pan.

title: microwave oven yummy fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together in microwave oven on High for about 1 1/2 minutes.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs well.
Add the sugar slowly, along with the vanilla and salt.
Pour the melted butter and chocolate into bowl slowly, stirring well. Blend in the flour.
Pour into a greased 8 or 9-inch glass pie pan.
Microwave on High for three minutes.
Turn dish and cook three minutes longer.
Cool and serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
This pie freezes well.

title: toast points
directions: Cut crust off bread and cut into triangles.
Spread melted butter and seasonings over bread.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Bake 2 hours.
Store in tight container.
Serve with dip or other appetizers.

title: chocolate cheese ball
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften.
Melt chocolate chips and combine with cream cheese with a mixer.
Add powdered sugar, vanilla and a few chopped nuts.
Refrigerate until firm.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with plain cookies.

title: baked cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes until light brown and bubbly.
Add a dash of paprika on top for eye appeal.
Serve with Melba toast or chips for dips.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except reserved oleo and bread crumbs.
Put in a well-greased casserole.
Sprinkle top with crumbs and oleo.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: holiday cheese cake
directions: Beat the cream cheese, sugar and flour together until light and fluffy.
Gradually add lemon juice and egg product.
Mix well. Add lemon yogurt and mix thoroughly.
Pour in prepared crust. Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes, until center is set.
Cool. Serve with whipped topping on top.

title: pea pods and peppers
directions: Steam pea pods until crisp-tender.
Drain.
Cook and stir red peppers and onion in oil and margarine in 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat until peppers are crisp-tender, about 3 minutes. Stir in pea pods, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir until pea pods are hot, about 1 minute.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt together.
Add Crisco and mix until crumbly.
Beat egg slightly. Add the water and vinegar. Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Divide into 5 portions.
Chill before using.
Will keep in refrigerator for 3 days or freeze.

title: creamy chicken primavera
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken in butter.
Add vegetables, pasta and water.
Cover and simmer 7 to 9 minutes, until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat thoroughly.
Can be served over rice.

title: bake all night cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until real stiff.
Add sugar gradually and continue beating at low speed.
Add flavorings, chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto foil-lined cookie sheet.
Place cookies in preheated oven. Turn off oven and let stand (without opening) at least 5 hours or all night is best.
Makes 2 or 3 dozen.

title: walnut refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream the oleo, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Mix in nuts.
Shape dough into 2 long rolls 2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill overnight. Cut into 1/8-inch slices and bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: meatball soup
directions: Shape ground beef into tiny meatballs.
Brown onion and meatballs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: zesty macaroni and cheese
directions: Grate all
three
cheese
blocks.
Boil
macaroni until soft. Drain and rinse macaroni with hot water and pour into a large pan. Melt butter
in pan, then gradually add the cheese until all of the
cheeses
have
melted.
Pour milk, stirring consistently. Add
stewed
tomatoes,
salt
and black pepper. Pour macaroni into a
large
baking
dish,
spreading evenly. Lightly sprinkle paprika
and parsley flakes.
Preheat oven at 350° and bake for 30
to 45 minutes.
Serves approximately 12 to 15.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to box directions.
Cool and tear apart. Layer cake, pudding (mixed), strawberries and pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip.
Can be put in any bowl, but looks very pretty in a punch bowl.

title: slush
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in hot water.
Add pineapple juice and lemonade; mix well.
Pour in container and freeze.
Remove from freezer a few minutes before serving time.
Spoon into punch bowl and pour ginger ale over it.
Makes about 26 cups.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cook peaches, juice and tapioca until thickened.
Combine batter and pour over fruit in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: In a small saucepan, saute mushrooms, celery, green peppers and onion.
Add 1/4 cup chicken broth, pepper and herbs.
Simmer 5 to 8 minutes.
Add remaining broth, cooked rice and cooked chicken.
Mix together and pour into baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: chili buns
directions: Mash egg yolks.
Chop very finely the egg whites, onion, pepper and olives.
Grate or dice finely the cheese.
Mix all together and spread mixture in hot dog buns.
Wrap in foil.
Before serving, bake for 20 minutes in hot oven.
Makes 10 buns.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add egg.
Mix in peanut butter, soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in flour and oatmeal.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (9 x 12-inch pan).
Sprinkle on chocolate chips.
Wait 5 minutes then spread.

title: baked stuffed scallops
directions: Mix butter, crackers and clams.
Pour over scallops into a square, glass casserole dish.
Pat down.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves 4.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve sugar and Jell-O in hot water.
Add other ingredients and chill in refrigerator.

title: chicken with asparagus sauce
directions: Dip chicken in egg, then in bread crumbs to coat.
Heat oil in a 10-inch skillet over medium-low heat.
Add chicken and cook 15 minutes, turning occasionally, until browned and opaque in center. Remove from skillet and keep warm.
Reduce heat to low.
Mix soup, milk and water in the skillet and cook, stirring often, until hot.
Spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: eggless fruit cake
directions: Boil raisins, sugar and water together 20 minutes, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well, then bake layers in 9-inch cake pan.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cool and remove from bones and cut into bite size pieces.
Cook broccoli just until it's beginning to get tender (will finish cooking while baking).
Mix together soup, water, mayonnaise, cheese and turmeric.
Butter 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer broccoli, then chicken.
Pour soup mixture over broccoli and chicken.
Top with seasoned bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40
minutes.
Let set 15 minutes before serving.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks with sweetened condensed milk and ReaLemon juice and mix together. Pour into prepared crust.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Chill. Spread with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: quick easy lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion together.
Drain grease from beef.
Add the spaghetti sauce to drained beef.
Cook lasagne noodles.
Follow directions on box.
Layer as follows: bottom up, noodles, Parmesan cheese and cottage cheese, meat sauce mix, Mozzarella cheese.
Makes about 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lizzie's egg cheese
directions: Bring fresh milk to a boil, then add sour milk or buttermilk and beaten eggs.
Bring to a boil again; add salt to taste.
Drain in cheesecloth and pack into a cheese mold.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup of coconut into bottom of pan, then the chopped pecans.
Mix the German chocolate cake mix like it says on the box.
Pour over coconut and pecans. Mix the softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and softened butter. Pour over cake mix.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken noodle parmesan
directions: In 3 quart saucepan, combine soup, milk, cheese and pepper. Add noodles and chicken.
Over low heat, beat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with parsley.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup

title: instant pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in glass container with tight cover and refrigerate.
Will keep 3 months.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine and bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: southwestern rice dish
directions: Prepare rice according to package.
Brown beef or turkey and onion.
Stir in remaining ingredients,
except rice and cheese. Remove from heat.
Add cooked rice.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls in bottom of pizza pan. Top with sausage, hash browns, onions, green peppers and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour over pizza. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese-raisin nut bars
directions: Butter a 9 x 9 x 2-inch square pan.
Heat margarine, marshmallows, cream cheese and cinnamon in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cereal until thoroughly coated.
Pat into pan; cool.
Cut into 2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Makes 24 bars.
May use 40% Bran and Uncle Sam's cereal in place of Raisin Nut Bran, then add 1/2 cup walnuts or almonds.
May add 1/2 cup coconut.
May use chocolate chips instead of raisins (1 cup).
Omit cinnamon.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift into ungreased 8-inch square cake pan the flour, sugar, soda, cocoa and salt.
Make 3 holes in dry ingredients.
In hole #1, put vanilla; in hole #2, put vinegar; and in hole #3, put cooking oil.
Pour over all 1 cup water.
Mix well with a spatula or spoon.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Recipe may be doubled and baked in 9 x 13-inch pan.
This is a moist chocolate cake. Needs no frosting and is quick to prepare.

title: shirley's cabbage
directions: Mix all together.
Add a little vegetable oil to skillet.
Fry slowly.
Add water and simmer until done.

title: w.w. pancake
directions: Mix in 2-cup bowl in order listed.
Spray pan with low-fat spray.
Heat.
Mix well.
Makes 1 pancake.

title: cranberry nut pudding pie
directions: Spread cranberries in bottom of buttered 9 inch pie plate. Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Beat egg until thick, gradually adding granulated sugar, beating thoroughly.
Add flour and melted butter.
Pour over cranberries and bake at 325 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until creamy.
Add next 4 ingredients; mix well, then add last 3 ingredients.
Press into ungreased pan. Bake at 300° for about 15 minutes.
Frost while warm.

title: three day pasta salad
directions: Day 1: Cook vermicelli as directed and mix with oil, lemon juice, seasoned salt and Accent.

title: vanilla ice cream(sue morris - oklahoma)
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Sift flour with sugar.
Add gradually by tablespoons to eggs until all has been added.
Continue beating until mixture becomes thick like divinity candy.
(This long beating serves as cooking for flour.) Add cream and vanilla.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: In a small bowl, combine first 7 ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into pie shell.
Top with chopped pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.
Chill and serve with whipped cream.

title: cool pineapple pie
directions: Mix and press; chill.

title: pineapple-cream cheese salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water until dissolved; add cold water. Mix all other ingredients to this and mix well.
Let congeal, stirring occasionally.
Marshmallows may be added to Jell-O and hot water.

title: lazy soup
directions: Throw all ingredients into pot and cook until cabbage is done.

title: cucumber salad dressing
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Use these proportions to make an amount sufficient for the amount of sliced cucumbers.

title: ma's sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine.
Beat eggs, milk and vanilla. Add to creamed mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients and fold in with wet ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for at least an hour. Roll out dough on a floured surface and let grand children cut out cookies.
Decorate with colored sugar, sprinkles and candy or you may use icing after baking.
Bake in a 350° to 400° oven until done.
Sweep the sugar from the floor that doesn't quite make it to the cookies.
Wipe little hands and faces before parents arrive and enjoy the best cookies ever!

title: herbed chicken saute
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Brush over chicken.
Saute in nonstick skillet until lightly browned and thoroughly cooked.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place in casserole.
Top with 2 cups cornflakes mixed with 1/2 stick margarine or cover with French fried onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes covered, 15 minutes uncovered.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Open bag of cranberries and put them in colander or sieve. Wash under cold water.
Shake off excess water.
Pick over the cranberries to remove stems or spoiled berries.
Put berries in heavy saucepan.
Add water.

title: spaghetti with olive oil and garlic(spaghetti all' aglio e olio)
directions: Cook pasta in salted
water according to package directions. Heat oil in small pan and add the crushed garlic.
Add black pepper and heat
until
garlic
is
golden.
Remove from heat.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Mix water and 100% Bran; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and 100% Bran mixture.
Add dry ingredients all at once to mixture and All-Bran only until moist.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes in cupcake tins.
Makes 1 gallon of mixture. Keeps for 6 to 7 weeks in refrigerator covered.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Pour off grease.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Shake flour in large size (14 x 20-inch) oven cooking bag and place in greased baking dish. Place floured beef in bottom of bag.
Combine remaining ingredients, pour over beef, then add package of seasoning mix and add 3 cups of water.
Close bag with nylon tie; make 6 slits in top of bag.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add butter and milk.
Beat all together.
Add the next 4 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in three 9-inch pans.

title: holiday banana bread
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Add flour.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan for one hour and 15 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread dough out on oiled pizza pan.
Bake 8 minutes on bottom rack in 450° oven.
Cut Prosciutto into strips.
Mix Ricotta and lemon peel.
Spread or drop Ricotta mixture on pizza crust. Arrange Prosciutto, peaches and grapes over Ricotta.
Combine sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over pizza.
Bake about 5 minutes, until fruit is warm.

title: mushroom business
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter for a few minutes.
Remove; drain. Saute onions, celery and bell pepper until tender.
Paint 4 to 5 slices of bread (remove crust) with melted butter.
Cut into 1-inch squares and line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bread with mushrooms, peppers, onion and celery.
Add salt and pepper.
Add another layer of crumbs.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add to milk and pour over casserole.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Before cooking, cover casserole with soup.
Add buttered bread crumbs and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour or until cheese is brown and bubbly.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: broccoli-cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Arrange in an 8-inch square or 1 1/2-quart pan.
In saucepan, melt margarine; blend in flour and salt and stir in milk.
Heat in microwave on High until mixture boils and thickens. Blend in cheese and pour over broccoli.
Cook, uncovered, in microwave 5 minutes or until bubbly and heated through.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, cornstarch, flour and milk.
Cook until it begins to thicken.
Beat 3 egg yolks; add 1 cup of the hot mixture and stir thoroughly.
Add back to the rest of the hot mixture and cook, stirring all the time until it thickens.
Remove from heat; add 3/4 cup coconut and 1 tablespoon butter.
Stir and pour into a 9-inch baked pie crust.
Beat 3 egg whites; add 5 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread on top of pie and brown in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: steak barbara anne
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour until tender.
tags: cream of onion soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Sift together two times the flour, corn meal, soda, cream of tartar, salt and sugar.
Add egg, butter, sour cream and milk. Mix thoroughly and pour in 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
This is an old recipe.

title: daddy hillyers hunters eggs
directions: Beat raw egg.
Mix sausage and 1/2 of bread crumbs well. Season boiled eggs with salt and pepper; pull off part of sausage mixture (about golf ball size) and flatten in your hand.
Roll boiled egg in beaten egg and wrap completely with sausage, leaving no holes.
Roll sausage covered egg in beaten egg again and in bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables and water chestnuts; combine all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Crush one tube of Ritz crackers; mix with one stick of melted butter.
Sprinkle on casserole dish for topping.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Bake at 350° until done, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mama's fruit pies
directions: Cut Crisco into dry ingredients; stir in evaporated milk and egg.
To complete the dough, roll out walnut size balls to make small circles of thin crust.
Fill with apples, peaches or other fruit.
Fold over and press edges together.
Fry in deep cooking oil.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix and drop with a spoon onto waxed paper.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix yeast and water.
Let set aside for 5 minutes.
Add buttermilk.
Set the liquid mixture aside.
Combine dry ingredients and cut in shortening until it looks like peas.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients.
Mix together with a fork until all are moistened.

title: corn light bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add buttermilk.
Heat shortening in loaf pan until very hot.
Add batter and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove from oven and let cool in pan for 30 minutes.
Serve either hot or cold.
This is good with ham, barbecue or spareribs. Makes 1 loaf.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in large bowl and mix well with fork. Add shortening and mix well until crumbly.
In a small bowl, beat together with fork the water, vinegar and egg.
Combine the 2 mixtures, stirring with fork until all ingredients are moistened. Wrap in waxed paper.
Put in plastic bag and freeze to keep for further use.
Will make 2 large double crust pies.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 to 1 cup of pecans.
Form into 1 large or 2 small cheese balls.
Mixture will be sticky. Using your hands, roll in chopped pecans until outside is covered. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, butter, sour cream, cream of chicken, cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no-bake sweet marie bars
directions: In saucepan, heat corn syrup, butter, sugar, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Remove from heat and stir in nuts and cereal. Press into bottom of greased 8-inch square baking dish.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and carrots.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix and add dressing, made with 1 cup mayonnaise and 2 tablespoons sugar.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in order, except the nuts and egg whites.
Beat well.
Add nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes. Let cool before turning out of pan.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease large baking dish.
Evenly spread can of cherries over bottom of dish, then spread pineapple over cherries.
Pour dry cake mix over pineapple.
Slice sticks of margarine on top.
Sift through cake mix to avoid lumps.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: t. j. soup
directions: Place all ingredients in pot and cover with water (enough to cover vegetables).
Boil for 10 minutes; cover and simmer until vegetables are soft.

title: apricot daisy bread
directions: Heat first 5 ingredients until warm.
Add eggs, yeast and enough flour for a stiff dough.
Knead until smooth.
Place dough in a greased bowl; let rise until double.
Punch down; let rise for 10 minutes.
Roll dough into a 14-inch circle.
Using a beverage tumbler, in center make 4 cuts at 12-3-6-9 o'clock marks. Cut each section into 5 strips; there will be 20 total.
Twist 2 strips together, forming to strips.
Remove and reserve 1 strip. Coil remaining strips to center to form daisy.
Remove tumbler. Coil reserved twist in center.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: bavarian green beans
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a saucepan, including the bacon drippings.
Cook on medium for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat; add Rice Krispies cereal and stir until well coated.
Press mixture evenly into a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in water to cover; cook until tender.
Cool.
Reserve broth.
Skin and bone chicken.
Cut in small pieces.

title: mamie eisenhower's fudge
directions: Beat until everything is melted.
Pour out onto waxed paper and allow to set for 3 hours.
This recipe makes quite a lot so have a large place to pour it out.

title: sausage breakfast bread
directions: Simmer raisins in a little water for 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain well and set aside.
Mix uncooked sausage and sugars until well blended.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, spices and baking powder.
Stir soda into coffee.
Add flour mixture and coffee alternately to meat mixture, beating well after each addition.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Keeps indefinitely in refrigerator.
Good served warm or cold.

title: kim's chocolate eclair cake
directions: Beat pudding, sugar and milk until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip. Grease 9 x 13-inch pan lightly with margarine.
Place layer of whole graham crackers on bottom of pan; top with half of the pudding mixture and add another layer of graham crackers.
Add the rest of the pudding mixture and finish with another layer of graham crackers.
Ice with Chocolate Icing.

title: deluxe potatoes
directions: Mix altogether and top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes that have been mixed with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Make night before and refrigerate overnight. Cover with foil or Saran Wrap until ready to bake.

title: margaret's
directions: Mix confectioners sugar, maple flavoring and milk until it is stiff as frosting.
Place a little on each cracker and 1/2 walnut on top.

title: thai carrots
directions: Stir all together. Put in carrots and marinate in refrigerator for 24 hours. Serve cold.

title: finger paints
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in 3/4 to 1 cup of cold water.
Add hot water to cornstarch mixture.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly, until it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Blend in gelatin.
Add liquid detergent and stir well.
Divide into 5 or 6 portions.
Add food coloring.

title: peach schnapps cake
directions: Mix well in mixer.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in well-greased and floured Bundt pan in 325° oven.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender; drain. Combine noodles, drained tuna, mayonnaise, vegetables and salt. Blend soup and milk.
Heat through; add cheese.
Heat and stir until cheese melts.
Add to noodle mixture.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 425° for about 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Using broccoli florets only, combine all ingredients.

title: fannie's pound cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs until creamy.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Combine sour cream, Miracle Whip and sugar. Stir in vegetables and cheese.

title: cheese roll
directions: Cream and make into a roll.
Cover with chopped pecans.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; bring to boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Stew chicken in 2 1/2 quarts water.
Simmer several hours. Should have 2 quarts broth; remove skin and bones and reserve meat.
Mix milk, 1 cup cooled broth, egg, salt and baking powder into flour.
Mix and work in flour until stiff enough to roll. Roll out dough on a floured surface, fairly thin.
Cut into 1-inch strips and drop, one at a time into the remaining boiling broth in pot.
Cover and cook (do not stir) until dumplings are tender and done.

title: milky way chocolate ice cream
directions: Melt candy bars and marshmallows in 1 cup milk.
Add other ingredients.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix all ingredients (except pecans). Roll in 2 logs and chill. Cut in slices (1/4-inch). Place on greased cookie sheet. Add 1/2 pecan on top of each, if desired. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: casserole shashlik (kabobs without skewers)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Place cubed lamb in 1-1/2 qt. casserole. Top with sliced onions and raisins; sprinkle with spices. Cove and bake until lamb is very tender 1 to 1-1/2 hours. Serves 6.

title: washboards
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add water and vanilla, then dry ingredients.
Mix in coconut and chill dough at least 2 hours.
Roll into balls and flatten into an oblong about 1/4 inch thick and press each cookie lengthwise with floured fork to give washboard effect.
Bake 10 minutes in 400° oven.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and oranges,
peel and all.
Reduce water for jello by amount of juice.
Add sugar to jellos and let partially set.
Add other ingredients.
Can use pineapple for variation.

title: pecan tarts
directions: With hands, mix the cream cheese, margarine, flour and salt. Break into little pieces the size of marbles and fit into well greased tart pans.
Mix together brown sugar, chopped pecans vanilla and egg.
Fill tarts with mix.
Bake to 350 degrees. Makes 36 - 40 tarts.

title: cole slaw
directions: Refrigerate 12 hours before serving.
Leftover slaw can be pushed under liquid and served over a period of 5 to 6 days.

title: sourdough breadgroves, texas
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl to make stiff dough.
Grease another large warm bowl.
Put dough in bowl and turn so oil is on side and top.
Cover lightly with warm towel and sit overnight. (Do not refrigerate)
Punch down dough on floured paper and divide into 3 parts.
Knead a little and place in oiled pan turning to oil sides.
Let rise 4 or 5 hours without covering.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Brush top with oleo.

title: cherry pecan bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar, butter and eggs until light and fluffy.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together. Stir in chopped nuts and cherries.
Combine cherry juice, orange juice and water.
Add dry ingredients to sugar mixture alternately with liquid.
Blend well.
Grease and flour the bottom, but not sides, of loaf pan and spoon batter into it.
Push batter into corners, leaving hollow in center.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking 1 hour at 350° or until tester comes out clean.
Cool before turning out on rack and let stand overnight before slicing.

title: german style carrots
directions: Place oil in saucepan, then add sliced carrots and top with onion.
Sprinkle sugar, herbs, salt and pepper over top.
Put lid on pan and simmer for 20 minutes or until tender.
Do not add water.
If necessary, add a little oil.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables and bouillon in water to cover in saucepan until tender; drain.
Add milk to vegetables.
Blend margarine and flour.
Stir into soup.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat.
Add cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Do not boil. Yields 10 cups at 300 calories per cup.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Combine ingredients, except corn tortillas.
Simmer soup slowly.
Before serving, crisp tortilla strips in skillet with small amount of oil.
Add to soup before serving.

title: low-fat tofu burgers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place tofu in large bowl and mash with a potato masher.
Add oats and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Shape into patties and place onto a nonstick baking sheet.
Bake 20 minutes on first side, then turn and bake an additional 10 minutes on the other side.
Makes 8 to 9 patties.

title: fruit sauces(sugar-free)
directions: 6 medium apples, peeled, cored and sliced
